Glenumbra, the westernmost region of High Rock, contains the city-states of Daggerfall and Camlorn, the great cemetery of Cath Bedraud, and the wild areas of Hag Fen, Glenumbra Moors, and the forests of Daenia.
Situated at the head of the strategic Iliac Bay, Stormhaven is the geographic center of High Rock, and also the home of the great trading city of Wayrest, capital of the Daggerfall Covenant.

This northwestern region of High Rock contains some of the province's most dramatic terrain, including towering, flinty crags, windswept moors, and narrow canyons. Many folk find the environment oppressive, even threatening.

The ashfall from the volcanoes of the Velothi Mountains and from great Ash Mountain itself is Stonefalls' bane and benefit, fertilizing the soil where the land isn't too arid to grow crops. It was here that the recent invading army from Akavir met its bloody end.

The fertile valleys of Deshaan are home to lush fungal forests, deep kwama mines, and broad pastures where netches and guar graze. But all pales before the magnificence of Mournhold, home of the Tribunal and capital of the Ebonheart Pact.
Malabal Tor is the northwest region of Valenwood, on the coast of the Abecean Sea and the Strid River estuary. Its capital is Silvenar, the spiritual home of all Wood Elves.

This region takes its name from its most famous feature, the Bangkorai Pass, which has served as High Rock's defense against the wild raiders of Hammerfell for countless generations. The uplands north of the pass and the desert to the south are both ruled from the port city of Evermore.

One of the "Old Holds," Eastmarch was among the first regions of Skyrim settled by the Nords when they arrived from Atmora. Its capital, Windhelm, is the oldest continuously inhabited human settlement in Tamriel, and was founded by Ysgramor himself.

Skyrim's southernmost hold has a relatively temperate climate, thanks to northern mountains that block the frigid gales of the Sea of Ghosts, and warming volcanoes in the Velothi Mountains to the east. Its capital is Riften, on the shores of broad Lake Honrich.

Though there are fertile fields on the coast near the capital city of Sentinel, it is the arid expanses of the interior that have captured the hearts of the rugged Redguards. The Alik'r is rich in mineral resources, but its fierce creatures and harsh terrain are daunting to most.
As the region of Valenwood farthest from all other realms, Greenshade's graht-oak forest is virtually pristine, the Tamriel jungle at its most primeval. Its capital is the trading port of Woodhearth.

On the border with Morrowind, the Shadowfen region has had more contact with Tamrielic civilization than most of Black Marsh—due primarily to the activities of the Dunmeri slavers who once operated out of the city of Stormhold. Now the Argonians are back in charge.

The second largest of the Summerset Isles, Auridon has always served the High Elves as a buffer between their serene archipelago and the turmoil of Tamriel. The Altmer of Auridon have been hardened by generations of repelling invaders, pirates, and plagues.

Once known simply as Northern Valenwood, this region that borders Cyrodiil and Elsweyr has seen so much bloody warfare since the fall of the Second Empire that it's now known as Reaper's March, even to its battle-scarred inhabitants.

This region is the southern heart of the Wood Elves' great forest, and home to more of the gigantic graht-oaks than any other part of Valenwood. Its capital, now also the capital of the entire Aldmeri Dominion, is Elden Root.

It's important everyone feels their voices are heard. How would you like to proceed?
The Hands of Northmoor and the Magis Order all have a stake in this, as do the staff of the graveyard. Given your prior dealings with them, who do you think will best serve us?

Pierric?  He disappeared just two nights ago, during his watch. He didn't raise any kind of alarm, which I find strange—Pierrick was as vigilant as any man I've known. I can't help but fear the worst.
Taken? By Werewolves? I cannot believe it... he... I...

There's nothing for it. I will mourn him when there is time. Please, could you go to the barracks - they're only makeshift, a house near the northeast tower - to pick up his personal effects and deliver them to his betrothed, Guendeline?
A Cultist in the Barracks?  Very odd.  Not like Pierric at all to be mixed up in such things.  nnPerhaps there is more here than meets the eye.

You could either speak to Guendeline or Vireche.nnGuendeline is Pierric's fiancee.  She might know if he had some shrouded secret.  nnVireche is an exiled witch from the Beldama Wyrd. If anyone knows anything about cults in this town, it'd be her.

The King of Worms is known to us. He and the necromancers who follow him are our greatest foes.nnTake the unclean thing to the statue of Arkay outside and burn it. Perhaps, with Arkay's blessing, we can put an end to this blasphemous graverobbing.
Honest Pierric?  Consorting with Cults?  Surprising. I know a thing or two of the cults near Crosswych.nnBring me ten hag's toes and perhaps I'll be in the mood to share my knowledge.
I know what you're thinking.  Quit staring at my feet and get moving.  You can find a clutch of Hags southwest of town.
My Pierric?  What am I to do?  The doctor bids me not to leave my house, but has yet to diagnose my illness... I feel so weak...
What do you want?  I have a long, grueling trial ahead of me, I cannot afford distraction.
Yes, of course, you're right... I must return.  I don't know what came over me before...
They intend to... raze Crosswych?  What about my Gwen?  This was not what they told me...
She is... with child?  I... I didn't know.
Could you speak to Doctor Severain on my behalf?  Whatever is plaguing me, I need to know if I am to help Pierric!
A bear once killed my sister.

Child?  But Pierric and I are not even wed... nnPlease, you must deliver this note to him.  I admit I saw him one evening returning from north of town, but he would say nothing of where he had been... please, hurry!

Ah, Guen.  I am not "holding something back," but due to the circumstances surrounding her condition I need to be certain of the diagnosis before I make a pronouncement.  If you could collect a reagent for me I could complete the necessary testing.
Ah yes... Begging your pardon, but I fear I need to test you to see if you are all that you - LOOK OUT!
Ah, it is as I suspected.  Gwen is pregnant.  Given her circumstances, I don't know that she'll take well to the news; I'd be inclined to wait until Pierrick returns to inform her, myself...
Ah!  The final ingredient.  The Wyrd will soon regret my exile.  Now, on to young Pierric.
He wasn't the carefree hero his companions thought.  He may have been lured into joining the Cult of Ulorion - they can be very persuasive when needs warrant.

They meet in a cave to the north.  Ancient magic makes quick work of the likes of you, so use caution.  I have a copy of their plans you may take - they don't bode well for Crosswych, I'm afraid.nnYou'll find the plans near the mantle.

I was going to give her a necklace. I designed it myself. But bandits stole my design, along with the gem and silver I had saved for so long to purchase.nnOh, perhaps Mother was right and I should get a love potion, instead.

Indeed he was - but no longer.  He disappeared just two nights ago during his watch. He didn't raise an alarm, which is odd - Pierric is as vigilant a man as any I've known.  nnI can't help but fear the worst.
Who are you?  Why have you slain my personal guard?  What do you want?
I have no time for interruptions, soldier, speak quickly.
Ah, Elsie.  There's a story there - it's not about Elsie at all, my friend, but the Wyrd.  Bad blood with them and Roch, and I can see both sides, to tell you the truth.
I hid during the attack. I saw the cultists smash into a shrine behind the cave wall, then seal it.
They intend to... raze Crosswych?  What about my Gwen?  This was not what they told me...
She is... with child?  I... I didn't know.
Bold yet reasonable.  It appears I have no choice in the exchange... Here.  Take them.
What!  My messenger will burn if he failed to deliver my orders!  Here, take this to your Captain.  Hurry!
It is unfortunate you must die.  The Throne has use for such sly agents.  Guards!
I'm part of the Fighter's Guild... I do odd jobs outside the mines. There were far too many cultists for me to face, though. Sometimes the best plan is to live and fight another day.

If we destroy the webbing, we can use the ram to bash our way into the shrine and stop them.nnWhen you're ready, hit that webbing with all you've got! They'll probably try to stop us, so prepare for anything.
They used a battering ram to get inside the shrine. They disabled it after opening the wall, but if you can protect me, I think I can get it working again.

Alaric? Aye, I know him. Poor lad. His parents vanished a month ago. I'd knew he'd run away, but not where.nnI'll keep Alaric safe. This camp... disturbs me. nnCan you go west and see if you can find the camp? Find out what you can about the place.
Put up your weapon or die.
Thetis the Poisoner.  He lives in the woods to the southeast.  I bought the poison from him; surely he would provide the antidote, for a fee.
If I don't leave Grayborne I'll be killed?nnRoche is a hateful fool! I'm no threat to anyone; ask around the village if you don't believe me.
Please! Don't turn me in. I'm just doing what I need to survive - you don't know what it's like at camp. Let me go - I'll be good from now on, promise!
You... you're a real jerk, you know that?
My parents? I... I have none. I live at our camp, with the other children. Mother Murk gives us everything we need. Wanna see?
Ahunno.  I live out at the camp.  No parents there.
Oh good! I'll put these to use at once. If I could impose upon you once again, please deliver these potions I've just finished to Inquisitor Bieller of the Lion Guard.
Hmm.  Never thought of that.  I'll tell you what, if you bring her a bouquet of Lacelilles I'll think about joining the Watch.  As long as my post is in town...

Then you've wasted your journey. I know Tristan worries for us, but I'm not leaving this swamp until I find my daughter. In case you haven't noticed, I can take care of myself. If you want to help us, help me find Isabelle, first.
Curse the Divines!nnI suppose I've nothing left to lose, I may as well join the Watch.  Tell Frelie Morascel I'll report in the morning.

Our soldiers here are dying. We have to send them on their journey without worry that the horrors of undeath will prevent them from reaching their rest. Please, go find symbols of Ar'kay so that he may watch over them.
Really? You seemed so sure … so confident!nnPlease tell me you haven't given up!
If i'm to join any Watch, I'll accept no position less than Captain of a Watchtower. I was Captain of the Guard in my homeland, and in a real city to boot - not some speck on the map.
Lorlinai is like no woman I've ever known. She's perfect. I know a way to make myself young again, to be with her at last… but should I?

The cheek! I know nothing of this man's past! I, for one, will not relinquish my tower to *any* man.  The northwest tower is helmed by one of my most trusted... The northeast tower, on the other hand...

Varik is not my ideal Captain, yet I cannot humiliate him or he is likely to leave the Watch, making this an even exchange at best.nnPerhaps you could speak to Varik, gauge how attached he is to his post.  We can proceed from there.
I don't know. If we do this, I'll forget everything — my ex-wife. My former life. I love Lorlinai but those are good memories. Perhaps you should talk with Lorlinai before we make a decision.
I've had a good, long life, but my wife is dead many years. I'm lonely. All my life, I've never forgotten my Lorlinai, and now I've so little time left.
You're right. We'll do it. Give me a moment alone with Lorlinai. I'll follow you shortly.
Immutably. I righteously defend Crosswych from what invaders may come from the northeast...
Only for a bit!  We've never been attacked on this front before...  Perhaps I would be better suited to a post within the city.
I'm not surprised. Varik's always been a commander in his head, but has no heart to back it up. nnGo tell Saul that if he'll have it, the northeast tower is his to command.

You must find it strange that I love a mortal, but it is his very mortality I love. Though he has been given only a few years of precious life, he longs to devote those to me. I know of a way to join him… yet I hesitate to sacrifice my immortality

He was young. He came crying to my pool. His water mixed with mine and I felt his pain. He had murdered to defend his people, and this burdened him. We talked into the night, and I found his soul unlike any I had ever encountered. I fell in love.
Mortal courage. Perhaps I will share it some day. We shall work together to walk this path. Look for me at a pool in the National Graveyard. Our path begins there.
I do not know if I can sacrifice so much. To know that I will age, and die — it terrifies me. Yet what is life without love? Should I become mortal? Would he love me if I did?
I heard the hermit in the forest was out trying to talk to the ghosts. I don't know what he's up to, but it can't be good. Who talks to spirits, you know?
Rumor has it a foreign mage of some kind has come to try and help. A Redguard, even! We don't see many of them around here.
A hermit? Can't say that I do. Although... if he comes into town at all, one of the town criers has probably seen him.
A Redguard? Here? That's something you don't see every day. Haven't heard of anyone like that, though, sorry. The blacksmith might have, though.
You must mean Claude. He's out there, day and night, trying to tell the spirits something about his grandfather or something. If you ask me, he's not quite all there.
Oh, the mage, Irama? Lovely girl. She's trying to bring the spirits away with her, in crystals. I hope she's up to the task.
Who are you to tell us where I can't live? You big doofus! You should go away now!
Indeed, I am. What can I do for you?
Very well, lets go meet this brigand you've apprehended.
Ah yes, he's been having this problem for some time, I just haven't had the resources to catch the thief. Did you have much luck?
We don't have much to give, but will part with what we can. Take one of the boxes along the back wall. It should provide basic first aid capabilities.
I am sorry, child. I am no priest of Arkay-- I know little about the undead.
Averos, that rabid cur, murdered King Ranser.  Sure as steel.nnThe fool!  His folly will bring war down upon us all, mark my words.
You've a ways to travel. I know of Gui - he's been helping with our wounded. You'll find him with the doctors at Camp Mercy, to the south. Are you sure this is how you wish to proceed?
Barnard does have a great deal of experience dealing with King's Guard's less - desirable, elements. It could work. Are you sure this is how you wish to proceed?
I can't say I'm comfortable with Ephin's methods, but they do produce results. I suppose any cost is warranted to ensure our soldiers are taken care of. Are you sure this is how you wish to proceed?
Well, that's the difficult bit.  I need a powder made from ground Wolf's Teeth.  Five should do it... I don't need to tell you how dangerous those beasts are.
Ranser's ghost is accusing her through the mouths of our citizens.  Use this to expell his shade from the possessed.nnDo this and you'll understand why I suspect Virolynn.
Thank you.  Give me a moment.
It is as I suspected.  Guendeline is with child.  Given her circumstances, I don't know that she'll take well to the news.
Me? With child? But Pierric and I aren't even wed!  Please, you must find him... give him this note - wherever he is, whatever he is doing, he must know that we are to be parents!

Pierric is not much like other men. He spent - spends - lots of time by himself, far away from town. I admit I saw him returning late in the evening from the direction of the Wrothgar Mountains on more than one occasion...

Do I look like I read? If it's parchment you're on about, you'd do better with a priest. They have the leisure for that sort of tripe.nnLast I heard, a sect devoted to Arkay set up in my old chapel. I'd say you should poke one of them about it.
While you were away my Watchers brought me news of the murder weapon.

gra-Muzgob? During my time at the chapel, I ran her off a time or two. Orc witch, if I remember. Had a thing for dead bodies.nnThought she was dead. Probably wouldn't stop her. Her old house is south of here. Maybe you'll find something there.

Weeping witch? I'd bet my bones she means the statue of Mara, behind the chapel. nnBad business, this. In my time, we kept the fallen safe. Still should. You want to end this, I'll back you. Meet me at Cath Bedraud. I've got a favor to call in.
Perhaps. My name is Claude. Who are you, and why are you asking me this?

Poor Seth.  Still trying to sell snakeskins to the snakes. He really should move on, but knowing him he'll stick with it 'till he's in the ground. In any case, here's the package - not that anyone in Crosswych will be able to afford anything in it.
Raising the dead? That may have been what riled the spirits here to begin with.nI may know where these instigators are. There is a camp to the north of here... I'll show you where it is on your map.
I am fine, thank you. While I appreciate your timely intervention, might I inquire as to what brings you so far off the beaten path?

<Curate Marcel's face darkens.>nThis blight will not be tolerated. I will help you in this task, but we must act quickly. I will need water blessed by Arkay-- you can find it in a tomb near here, where others of my faith are interred.
Once you have the holy water, light the brazier at the southernmost graveyard. I will meet you there, and we can set about this business.nNow go! Quickly!
We arrested the courier, but he must have hidden the weapon before we caught him on the road.
The good Baron told me to keep an eye out for the courier, and for you as well.
Elsie cured my son of chills once.

Missing corpses. Pah. How can I ask souls to die for Northmoor if we can't even bury them?nnA few years back I hung some bandits for graverobbing. They set up southwest of Camp Mercy. Go there and kick over some rocks. Maybe a snake will crawl out.
No matter what you know, there's nothing you can do, now. The ritual won't be stopped!
Roche and the Wyrd; there's a story there.nnAll I know is Roche's son was in Westtry, some months ago.  He came home wounded, and neither Elsie nor the Wyrd could save him.
Graverobbing? Is that why you beat me within an inch of my life? Look, it's like this. So maybe a few times we maybe dug up some bodies and maybe sold them to an orc. Don't murder me over it!
Some female orc - Jha gra-Muzgob. Don't know what she did with them and don't care. We're just trying to make a living. You want to murder someone, murder her!

Hmm. Was a gravedigger awhile back at Cath Bedraud, looting graves. Palo. Couldn't prove it, but I put the fear of Akatosh into him. Thefts stopped.nnIf anyone's connected to this Muzgob, it's Palo. Go shake him up a bit, see what falls out.

Barnard sent you? I'd never! I've not touched a grave save to bury the dead. Man's a lunatic! Said he'd break both my thumbs!nnI tell you, friend, I'm just an honest man trying to make a living. I certainly haven't been selling no bodies to no orc.

That wasn't me, swear on my mother's soul! It must have been gra-Muzgob! She knows I gave her up!nnLook, I'm just trying to make an honest living. I met her behind the chapel when I had a sale, all right? That's all I know! Please don't kill me!
The Lion Guard won't abide any witch.nnBut the Wyrd and Roch?  That story's more personal.  They took his son, you see.  No man can forgive that.
You can always trust the same snake to slither the same way. Good work.  I'll gather a few men. Meet us behind the chapel in the graveyard. You and I, we're putting a stop to this.
<The acolyte laughs, madly.>nThe Mistress is going to destroy Camlorn with a monster the likes no one here has ever seen! You have no hope! The Colossus will crush you!
It is hidden in the forest! You'll never find it! Mistress Jha has hidden it well.n<The acolyte spits.>
Now that's good ale...nnRoche's boy went to fight in Westry; when he came back he wasn't right.  Badly hurt, but more than that.  The Wyrd couldn't cure him.nnThen he disappeared.  Roche blames them.
My cow wouldn't give milk.  Elsie gave me some herbs for it, and now we have all the milk we could want.
Lord Ranser was murdered here in Camlorn on an official visit.
So.... you're the Glenumbra hero? I can't do much with this missive. I can tell you that there has already been a murder. You should report to Oron. He's Faharajad's representative here.
Lord Ranser was murdered here in Camlorn on an official visit from Shornhelm.
Lord Ranser was a "diplomat" from Shornhelm. Between you and me, he was a right bastard. Back in the war, he gutted old Ulorion of the Magis Order.
Oron is leading the investigation from Fahara'jad. He's a man serious about his business.
Fahara'jad? Where're you from again? He's the Lord of the Nine Crowns. Brought together the nine kingdoms. Married off all his daughters to do it.
Oron? He's back with Lord Sebastien in the castle.
"LORD" Sebastien is the Lord of Northmoor. He's married to Parvani of the Nine Crowns.
The Magis Order is my outfit and the army of Northmoor. We report to Lord Sebastien. The army was started by Ulorion, but is currently ruled by Lord Averos.

Oh, thank you! The bandits are hiding in the old ruins to the west. They took everything I had!nnAfter you retrieve my items, go see <<1>>. She's the blacksmith's apprentice. She can smelt them into a necklace that Guendeline will be proud to wear.
You're right. As Mother always says, drastic times call for drastic measures.nnThe alchemist Vireche Kel brews potions. Would you speak to her and see if she can make something to help?
I'll strike you a deal.  Help me win her and I'll join the watch.  That'd actually be kind of romantic... penning love letters from my post each night...nnAny ideas how I might win her heart?
If I had a gold piece for every time I've been asked that question ….

Possible, yes. But if it were easy, I'd be a wealthy woman.nnI can brew you such a potion, but I need the essence of a lovesick spirit. And the final concoction will be … volatile. As with all true love, there is some level of risk involved.
I gave the weapon to a second courier.  Her name is Katarin.  She took it to Aldcroft in Urvaius...nnI just wanted to return to my home in Glenumbra...

I can help with that-- I owe my brother one. I'm worried about getting there safely, though. With both bandits and aggressive wolves in the area, I'll need protection. Lord Jes at the Hands of Northmoor holdings in Camlorn could provide it.

Oh Isabelle, you look just a mess... and yes, friend, I will return with you, now that we've found my daughter. Just be warned. I did not have my sword before. I have it now. If I see that Lurker, I'm going to cut it apart, piece by bloody piece.
Oh praise the Divines, at last someone's come! This swamp is horrid, horrid! There are flies and snakes and leeches and... oh, it's just dreadful. Please, good knight, escort me back to my family!
What? No! What sort of twisted need is that?  Please leave me be!
Julien wants to give me gems? That is so sweet! nnI wasn't sure if he understood what I was hinting at the other night, but does this mean … does he feel the same way about me as I do about him?

Oh. I see. He didn't get the hint, after all.nnIf he's in love with Guendeline though, then it's for the best. In fact … here. Take the piece I was crafting for the Dorells. I was tempted to keep it, but maybe it will bring Julien happiness.
That's a bit odd. Why would he ask me to fashion a necklace for myself?

Gods! Such exquisite work! It's … it's beautiful! I had no idea Julien had such good taste. And I guess this means he has some coin, too!nnTell Julien that my feelings for him have grown. Tell him I love him and I will wait for him.
I've lived in this village my entire life.  I'm not going anywhere.
She did?  She likes me?? That's fantastic!nnI knew it already, of course.  You can just tell.
Of course not. With Guendeline's love behind me, there's nothing I can't face!nnI'll report to Frelie Morascel in the morning, on my honor. Thank you, friend.
I froze up. I knew what I had to do, but I froze up. Divines protect me. I've never seen anything so awful.
But sir... it's all I've ever wanted to do. You may be right, but... I'm not giving up. Next time I see a zombie, I'm hacking it to bits! Sir.
You're right. I believe you. I promise you sir, I will do better.

By Akatosh, I've never been so scared. Those things... they're monsters. What if I die, end up like them? I'm not cut out for this. Just tell Capel... something. Tell him I died. Either way, just let me leave.
For a friend, of course. Now let me see that. Yes, you found one! Nicely done!nnNow give me a moment and stand back. Love can be delicate and volatile, as you no doubt know.

A dash of this, a touch of that. Now the distilled essence of the lovesick spirit, and … success!nnA perfect potion to guarantee the affection of the person you love. Or, rather, the person your friend loves.
Divines forgive me for being such a coward.
I... I'll try, sir. I guess if you learned to fight those things... maybe I can too. Thank you.

Oh, thank you! I do so enjoy getting special gifts. I don't usually take potions from strangers, but you seem trustworthy enough. And it is from Julien. He's that peasant fellow, right?nnWell, bottom's up!
You have a good and kind nature.  I thank you for your mercy.
Oh, how sweet of you to ask! I'm surprised I never noticed you before. Are you new in town?

If there's anything I can do to help, please let me know. I wouldn't mind getting busy, if you ever want some company.nnBe a dear and come visit me again when you have the chance. I'll be counting the moments ….
Well, I do hope you'll be staying for a while. I'd love to get to know you better.nnWe could go for a walk under the stars. Or have a drink at the inn. They serve a lovely rabbit stew … for two.
Zombies, you say? Could have been worse. How'd my recruits do?

Deserter, eh? Lucky for him I've not the manpower to track him down. Still, better he leave now than in the thick of battle. You did as well as you could. Our force is healthier with him gone. Go tell Captain Arin what happened.

Died, with you and Mallery backing him? More than a few recruits 'die' on their first patrol, only to be found weeks later suckling their mothers. Still, I'll not question you. I've more important things to do. Go give Captain Arin your report.
Zombies, you say? Could have been worse. How'd my recruits do?
Oron is an official from the Nine Crowns.  King Fahara'jad sent him to find Ranser's killer before there's another full scale war between Shornhelm and Northmoor.nnHe is just inside the manor.
Admirably! Hah. More like their boot heels turned all sticky. Either way, they've tasted battle now, and when it comes again, it will taste less bitter. You've served them well.
Your deeds, and your words, will do more good than you know. They've tasted battle now and lived through it, which will make them stronger. You've served them well.

Shornhelm's military is invading ours.  Well, part of it.  Their military split after the last war.  Part didn't want to accept the peace with Northmoor.nnRanser was in Camlorn to prove he had nothing to do with the rebels.
Oron is an official from the Nine Crowns.  King Fahara'jad sent him to find Ranser's killer before there's another full scale war between Shornhelm and Northmoor.
A Reachmage in Glenumbra!  I heard of the goblin invasion, but a Reachmage that far south!  These are sinister times indeed.nnOron will want to see this.

That man was a devil.  He led every charge in the last war.  Stories claimed he couldn't die...  sure as steel, he's dead though.  I saw his body with my own eyes - run through with a blade of some kind.
Of course! She'd have no idea you're asking on my behalf.nnI'll wait right here for her response!
I suppose so. I'm not feeling well, so try to keep it brief.
The Kingdom of Nine Crowns is the alliance that High Rock joined years ago.  We are united with Hammerfell and the Orc nations of the Wrothgar Mountains.

What a peculiar question, my lady.nnI'm a practical woman. Love is only part of the equation. I have loved terrible men in my past, and don't intend to repeat the experience.nnI admire thoughtfulness and adherence to the customs of courtship.
No, I am a practical woman.  Love is only a part of the equation.  I have loved some terrible men in my past, and don't intend to repeat the experience!

The necromancer lashed out at me, with some kind of force. It hurts, but I have an idea of where she is now. There is some kind of ritual going on-- you must stop it! I'm afraid I will be of little help to you like this.
Then our course is clear!nnThe outskirts of town are rich with silver. Find some nuggets and bring them to Aubrey, the assistant blacksmith. Ask her to forge a delicate necklace for my love!
Averos? What's that overzealous fool want with me?

You want the sword too? Cursed thing! I don't have it anymore - it was bound for Aldcroft up north, so I gave it over to Katarin, a courier bound that way. Gods, I hope the Magis aren't after her too! Can you find her? nnBack to Glenumbra for me!
More than I'd like. Everyone here has a shady past of some sort or another. Crosswych attracts exiles from all across Northmoor, and they don't come here for the sights!
Well, for one, I wouldn't call it a 'town'.  It's a village, no matter what that fool Godwin says.  I won't be staying any longer than I must. I may relocate to Wayrest - now *there's* a city!
They're an odd lot, that much is certain. Crosswych attracts a diverse element. Makes for interesting days, if you don't mind the rather puerile drama.

Crosswych used to be home to the miners up at Khuras, but there isn't much work to be had there now.  Most of the villagers left for greener pastures, but I like it here.  It's quiet and safe - not counting the Werewolves, of course.

I know it's a town by the will of Godwin alone. I doubt the Magis Order even knows we exist - a blessing and a curse. Granted, we don't have to deal with their iron-handed rule, but we also can't get the protection we need from the Werewolf threat..

Most of the townsfolk are eccentric but harmless - with one exception: Vireche. Rumor has it she was thrown out of her conclave of witches because she violated one of their rules - she killed someone! nnI'd be careful around her.
Can't you see them? Werewolves... just lying in wait for a chance to pounce.nnThis much I promise - they won't catch me unaware. I'm ready for whatever they throw my way, cursed beasts.
So Veraul's cranking that brain of his again, eh? Very good. Here's what I've observed of Shornhelm movements from my vantage above the pass.
My scouts have delivered me what they can about Shornhelm movements on the ground. Take this parchment to Veraul and we'll see what he can do.

Reports? I'm a bit busy keeping the wounded alive, here. nnLook, if it will get you out of my tent, here's everything related to Shornhelm that my patients have rambled about in their fevers. Perhaps it will help Eagle's Watch stop this carnage.

I should have guessed. Tarrant thinks I'm poisoning his crops.  Known the man twenty years and he suspects me of such a thing! nnNo, it isn't me you should be questioning - it's whoever took up residence at the Biren farm after *their* crops failed.
They packed up and left after their ground went sour, but someone's living there still - I've seen the lights myself!
It *was*. I don't know what you think you're doing here, but unless you have business with the Lion Guard you'd best leave.
That isn't your concern. Keep to your own affairs, stranger - you do *not* want to raise the ire of the Lion Guard.
That's a ridiculous accusation, and the only one authorized to make ridiculous accusations around here is me. You'd do well to remember that.
Fine! My life is forfeit anyway.nn<The acolyte pulls a scrawled map out of his robe and sets it on the cart.>nnI hope, for both of our sakes, that you're confident in your ability to stop her.

That oaf! He can't even see devotion staring him in the face.nnI hope they both find happiness together, although I wouldn't hold out much hope. No one cares for Julien as I do, least of all that vapid Guendeline!

That's perfect! Completely unique and totally romantic! If Guendeline doesn't fall in love with me after receiving this, then there's no hope for us at all.nnWhat did Khalisah think? Was she glad that I took her up on her offer?
Feelings? For me? You can't be serious. nnI've known Khalisah since we were toddlers. She's like a sister to me. I mean, I love her dearly, but not like that … at least, I don't think I do.
All right. That's probably for the best. Otherwise, I'd always wonder what would have happened.nnTruth is, if Guendeline turns me down, I can always approach Khalisah.

All right. Maybe … maybe you're right. Maybe I've just been a fool this whole time, chasing Guendeline because she teased me when true love was right under my nose.nnWill you take the necklace back to Khalisah and tell her I was wrong?
Mother always said I was hopeless when it comes to this sort of thing. I never really thought about Khalisah in that way before.nnWhat do you think? Have I just been blind this whole time?

He … he does? You mean, he feels about me the way I feel about him?nnI don't know what to say. I thought my dreams were dead, and now you tell me that they have come true. Tell Julien to come to me. I must hear this from him.
Thank you, stranger! You've made me so... happy!nnIt's a shame I did such intentionally shoddy work on the necklace... but I shall wear it with pride nonetheless!
The phantoms haunting the Sanguine Barrows to the southeast. That's where I'd try, if I were you.nnThe lingering dead always have a broken heart or a lovelorn soul among them.
That old sop prattling on about it again, is he? Man's got no spine. The spirits, they don't bother no one. Just weep and shriek some nights. Breaks up the monotony of duty, as I see it.

Last man to look into it - he jumped off a cliff. Still, maybe you'll do better. Heh.nnGo inside, then. Talk to Bhogoth. Big orc. Nutty as a squirrel. Oh, the asylum guards are all on the line now, so the inmates are running things. Watch yourself.
That'll go well for you. Digging into spirit matters, that's best left for the priests.
From what I've heard those spirits weeping about at night, what happened here years ago is best left buried. Buried deep, deep down, if you get me. You'd be better off leaving it alone.
Tell me things, you say. Crush your head, they say. So many voices. Orders. Questions. Stop crying. Stop crying. Hate crying. Crying doesn't help.

You're the same? No. Still in one piece. Not in pieces. So many pieces.nnI throw it away, but the key comes back. Other took it, but jumped. You take it now. Make them stop talking. Key's to the west tower. Voices are there. They're asking for you..
I'm not cut out for this!  This is supposed to be the quiet tower... get away, you'll bring them to me!
I went first, after the lock. nnI gave the child his first taste.nnGoing my way leads to lies, nnWhile the wolf's fangs close with haste.

Gargast? He passes this way once each month, but I've not seen him of late. I fear I have no news of the Chamberlain, but I have other tidings: I've just gotten word from Oron that he needs your aid in Camlorn, as quickly as you can get there.
The others can't help you. The others can't give you what I can.
I killed many. So, so many. Find the blood I spilled in the pass below Eagle's watch, west of our lines. We'll see their curse undone.
I was last to offer blood,nnA hearty aperitif. nnFollow me where darkness dwellsnnAnd I'll tell the tale of grief.
The others can't help you. The others can't show you what I can.
To save his blood, I sacrificed my own. Look for me there, at the lone house west of Camp Mercy. See then how they hate me.
Guardians of noble blood,nnOffered the child all we had.nnI can offer only sword,nnAnd the fight for good turned bad.
The others can't help you. The others can't teach you what I can.
They were so many, we, so few. The child had to be protected. Look for me in the ruins southwest of Eagle's Watch. We'll find our answers.
Just because my assignment has been quiet for some months doesn't mean that we are immune from assault, and when that time comes, I will avail myself admirably!
If you would be so kind, please tell the Warden I'll resign my post here and take whatever he has on offer.
There is much you do not understand.  This is larger than the murder of one man...
It took an evil blade to kill a beast like Ranser.  Here.  Take this back to the investigator in Camlorn.
Too much.  You must alert Fahara'jad!

Those of us among the Wyrd knew of a cure for the disease which now consumes her.nnYou will need to collect Wolfsbane and Belladonna Berries which grow on the Spriggans to the south of here.  Please, you must be swift!
Come with me, quickly!  I can track him.
Thank you.  While I prepare the cure, you should speak with Virolynn while she has the strength to respond. She is in her bedchamber. Please, do not over tax her with questions.
Oh, yes. Pierric. He left me, disappeared without a trace... is it any wonder I found comfort in the arms of another?

I have to be honest, I'm trying to put that behind me. I haven't been feeling well, and Doctor Sevarain doesn't seem inclined to tell me what might be wrong with me. Could you speak with him on my behalf?
Me? With child? What will Julien think...

Pierric is not much like other men. He spent - spends - lots of time by himself, far away from town. I admit I saw him returning late in the evening from the direction of the Wrothgar Mountains on more than one occasion...
I must break it off with Julien. I am going to be a mother. If Pierric returns, I will be forever his wife.
I should slap you for implying it could  belong to anybody else.
What do you want?  I have a long, grueling trial ahead of me, I cannot afford distraction.
Yes, of course, you're right... I must return.  I don't know what came over me before...
Guen? Do you speak the truth - I am to be a father?
What do you want?  I have a long, grueling trial ahead of me, I cannot afford distraction.
Yes, of course, you're right... I must return.  I don't know what came over me before...
Oh, is she? I find it interesting that the person bringing me this information is the same one who fouled our sacred union...
A wise choice.  Go to Thetis the Poisoner, near Grayborne.nnThe poison is his, and he will know the cure.
Good.  Very good.  nnTake my tabard to Sergeant Gallmau on the way to Camlorn, tell him how I died and that Frey was brought to justice.nnBe careful; Frey had a gang who may be looking for you.

She was courageous and determined, that one.  nnHere, take her tabard.  Tell Sergeant Gallmau that you took care of Frey and that Barre has passed on.  He should be somewhere on the road between here and Camlorn.
At least her death wasn't in -nnLook out!

Foul wolves besiege us - unnatural beasts, risen from their graves! The undead things refuse to die, and their bite spreads a wasting disease. Too many of my men are afflicted or dead already. Without help, we're doomed for sure!
As a rule, they don't.  But these creatures are different - they stink of death and decay. By all rights, they should be long in their graves.
I believe you have unfinished business in Aldcroft...

Wayle and I were on patrol and tried to quiet down one of the damned "Hands of Northmoor" rabble-rousers, when the man, smelling like liquor, pulled a knife on us! He said he'd be a martyr for the cause and stabbed Wayle!
I'd appreciate it. I managed to stop Wayle here's bleeding, but I'm no healer.

Well, I was worried about ol' Wayle, and tried to stop that rebel as fast as I could... used a bit o' magic to do it, just a bit of fire to scare him so's we could get away. Next thing, a crowd of people is throwin' stuff at us and so we hid here.
I don't rightly know. I cast a bit of fire-- to scare him, y'see, and then tried to get away with Waylan. I heard a bunch of shouts that we'd killed him, but I didn't use that much fire, I know it!
She is in the belly of the beast.
That is completely a pop culture reference. FIRED!

When she visited, she brought sweet things and... ugh. They were bugs. She made us eat bugs. How could she be so evil? What she did to Alaric...nnWhen she left, she always went north. She went into the lake. Maybe... you could start looking there?

The Chamberlain was obviously an agent of the Shrouded Throne.  I expect you will find other agents in Aldcroft as well.nnReturn to Aldcroft and speak to Warden Godwin, perhaps he has news of Gargast's associates.

The Chamberlain was obviously an agent of the Shrouded Throne.  I expect he will has contacted his associates by now.nnReturn to Aldcroft and speak to Warden Godwin.  Perhaps he has spotted the Chamberlain.

Isaac... yes. I recall the boy. Never fails to deliver my powders dry and without delay. It would be a shame to lose him.nnShornhelm poison is primitive - not like mine. My standard curative should work. Take this. Apply it to his wound to cure him.
Follow me! Try and keep up!

I must now return to the High King.  Fahara'jad will pardon Sebastien - his valiant defiance of the Shrouded Throne will not soon be forgotten.nnYou should travel to Crosswych and dispose of Gargast's allies there.

The Chamberlain was obviously an agent of the Shrouded Throne.  I expect you will find other agents in Crosswych as well.nnWhen you reach Crosswych, speak again to Warden Godwin. Perhaps he will have news of Gargast's associates.

The Chamberlain was obviously an agent of the Shrouded Throne.  I expect he has contacted his associates in Crosswych by now.nnJourney to Crosswych and speak to Warden Godwin. He may have found news of the Chamberlain in your absence.

High Rock should have fallen centuries ago.  Our borders would shift with the seasons.  Books will claim High Rock persevered due to the steadfastness of its populace.  The truth was, until recently, viciously defended.

The Shrouded Throne are commanding rebels from Shornhelm and crushing our forces at Eagles Watch in Kingsguard to the north.  If they break through...  they must not.nnHurry to Eagles Watch and speak to Averos.
The Chamberlain passes through here once a month.  He never stays long and keeps to himself.nnIt is good you found me.  I received word from an Oron Nassir in Camlorn that you are needed there.
I can't even begin to express my thanks: you clearly need no test, because even if you were a werewolf, you'd be the kind I liked. I'll send word to the Warden that you are welcome in Crosswych.

I have placed a sound box of my own design to the south of Aldcroft. When activated, they attract Bog Lurchers. My intent is to allow wardens to wind the boxes and cull any Bog Lurchers who appear. I need you to enter the bogs and test my box.
Take this to the victim, administer it as soon as you can.  My poisons are not to be trifled with!
You fool!  You had my instructions... all that matters is Morgan Frey's death!  nnI'll take the antidote, and only hope I can find him again and repair both our failures.
I feel stronger already... I'll deal with Frey.nnGo and see if you can locate his henchmen.  They camp in the forest to the west, deep in the trees.  Keep them out of my way.
Frey's band of brigands have been terrorizing the roads here for months.  His contacts in Camlorn were selling the goods; I shut them down.nnHe murdered my brother and father in retaliation.

My mother's alive! Not that disgusting bog witch... my real mother! She told me all about the brave knight who saved her. nnMother said we're going to go to the caravan to stay. We're never going to be apart again. It's all thanks to you. Thank you!

Your warning's too late, I fear. Sebastian's hall is awash with royal blood! King Ranser of Shornhelm is slain. The Redguard emissary hunts the assassin, but I fear in vain. The Adamant Crown has cracked, and war will come of it, mark my words!
The Queen Mother will not speak with outsiders.

We have someone who takes care of us and gives us everything we need. Otherwise, we watch out for each other and are protected by Queen Mother's pets, the Dire Wolves. Although, lately, we have had some other problems.

Not much other then the source being tainted and the water unusable. Not only is it not drinkable, but I'd rather bathe in the bog waters. If you could help us cleanse the source, we'd be greatly appreciative.

Recently, they've become a nuisance to all of Northmoor. But they continue to become more of a problem and have ventured dangerously close to our camp. If you could help us rid of this threat, we'll provide you with anything we can.
Our water source has been tainted somehow... or by someone. It could be these bandits that have causing problems recently for all of Northmoor. Maybe you could help us?

Oron is his name I think. Some fine Redguard nobleman from Hammerfell across the sea, the High King's man. I hear he's leading the search for the assassin. He needs all the help he can muster - if you'd help set things right, seek him out.
She's the daughter of King Fahara'jad.  Their marriage solidified the alliance between Northmoor and Hammerfell.

Sebastien is King of Northmoor. That's this whole realm if you're confused, and he rules alongside Queen Maraya from Camlorn - the city where you're standing, in case you didn't know. A fine king, even if an Adamant Crown is higher than his.
He's back with King Sebastien in the manor.

Ranser was King in Shornhelm to the north. He warred with Northmoor for years, 'till the High King made him and Sebastien brothers. Many in Northmoor found that hard to bear. Seems someone's done something about it.

Who was King Ranser you mean. Ranser was King in Shornhelm to the north. He warred with Northmoor for years, 'till the High King made him and Vincentian brothers. Many in Northmoor found that hard to bear. Seems someone's done something about it.

Why, the Adamant Crown's our grand alliance! Eight kings and one High King, bound in an indestructible ring. All High Rock's joined the High King's union, conquered without a fight. It's unnatural, I tell you: to stand beside Redguards and Orcs...

Fahara'jad is his name, King of Hammerfell and the Redguards.  He forged the Adamant Crown.  He rules from Sentinel, across the Illiac Bay.  He bound all High Rock to his will without a single battle.

Do I look like a lord or baron to you? I'm a simple solder: all they told me was great guests were coming. Some new treaty, no doubt, King Sebastien and King Ranser making some deal under the Emissary's watchful eye.

Hah! Don't blame me. Blame Guillie. He's a filthy human being, and that's why his house is infested with rats... RATS. And what do they do when they can't find any food left in his house? They wander next door into mine!  I won't tolerate it.
Sebastian's hall is awash with royal blood! King Ranser of Shornhelm is slain. The Redguard emissary hunts the assassin, but I fear in vain.
Well, you'll have to take that up with Al'kari. She keeps roosters in her house... ROOSTERS! Guess what they do first thing every morning? You try sleeping through that!

That man was a devil.  He was the ruler of Shornhelm and led them when they invaded Northmoor years ago.  Stories claimed he couldn't die...  sure as steel, he's dead though.  I saw his body with my own eyes - run through with a blade of some kind.

Shornhelm's military split after the last war.  Part didn't want to accept the peace with Northmoor and recently began invading again.nnRanser was in Camlorn to prove he had nothing to do with the rebels.
Lord Ranser was murdered here in Camlorn while on an official visit from Shornhelm.
The Kingdom of Nine Crowns is the alliance that High Rock joined years ago.  We are united under one banner with Hammerfell and the Orc nations of the Wrothgar Mountains.
Oron is a representative of the Nine Crowns.  He was sent here by King Fahara'jad to lead the investigation of the murder.
He's inside the manor with Lord Vincintian.
Lord Vincintian rules Northmoor with the daughter of King Fahara'jad, Lady Maraya, at his side.
King Fahara'jad rules the Kingdom of Nine Crowns.  He resides in Sentinel, across the Illiac Bay to the east.
She's the daughter of King Fahara'jad.  Their marriage solidified the alliance between Northmoor and Hammerfell.
With you and Mother, I know everything will be okay. Lead the way!
Fantastic! Thank you, friend. Now if you'll excuse me, I need to go gather more rats.
Didn't say I didn't have rats. Said I didn't have a rat *problem*. Rats don't bother me none. They bother Al'kari, so *she's* the one with the rat problem!
I'd bet if you brought that big old black cat that lives behind the Barracks into her house, she'd take care of the problem quick.
Why should I?  You know what Al'kari has? ROOSTERS. Lots of them! At the crack of dawn every morning I'm awake whether I want to be or not. Now *that's* unneighborly!
Who are you? Who wants to know?
I'm ready! Just let me know when it's time to go!

Indeed, you have found him. I am Oron Nassir, vizier to the Golden Court of High King Fahara'jad. My king sent me to foster friendship between two worthy kings, but now one of them is dead. Now I am hunting a murderer and a coward. Can you assist me

We must cast our net wide, before this traitor runs far. No deed this dire can be done without leaving ripples. Inquisitor Danain is well positioned to hear of intrigues. Ask him if he heard any whisperings, before or after.
As I just arrived, I have yet to collect enough evidence to offer a specific task.nnFor now, speak with (name).  She/he is a notable citizen and may know something about Lord Ranser's murder.
He commands from Magis Order Headquarters - the barracks directly west of this Manor House.
Baron Avon is a noble here in Camlorn and an official of the Hands of Northmoor.
The Hands of Northmoor is a local militia.  I believe they were formed to protect the people of Northmoor from the Magis Order.

They call Danain an inquisitor: of an order devoted to fighting evil and dark sorcery. His struggle against darkness doubtless gives him some insight into who may have done this evil deed. It would be worth knowing who he might suspect, yes?
I know a Hand well - name of Barnard. Did a right fine job cleaning up the bandits here, before he moved out to Eagle's Watch. If you're thinking of joining them, you could do worse.
The Hands of Northmoor? I honestly don't know much about them, but the ones I've met have treated me far better than those Lion Guard ruffians. They seem like stand up folk.

Bah, those layabouts are nothing more than too-rich nobles playing a game of soldiers. They'd crumble under real attack. The Lion Guard has kept us safe for as long as I remember, and they will still. You should join the Lion Guard, not some farce.

I know what I'd *like* to do, except she knew I did it - a big black cat lives behind the barracks. If you could lure it to her house, it'd scare the roosters. Cats love rabbit, if you can find one it'll follow you anywhere!

I've been thinking about this for a while... a big black cat lives behind the barracks. If you could lure it into his house, it'd likely eat the rats. Cats love rabbit, if you can find one it'll follow you anywhere!
Odette's gonna get you for this!
Really? Great work. Now please pardon me, I need to go to the market to purchase more roosters. The louder, the better!
Yes, praise the Divines that you've come! Let's get out of here...
Yes, please!  Let's get out of here as soon as possible...
You've done all this? Oh, you're in for it now! Come to us, bog queen! Come destroy the infidel!
But... you don't understand. She doesn't allow us to leave. The wolves will tear us to bits.
You'll really...? Oh no. It's Mother. Mother's coming!
Aye, although I may not be for much longer if these bandits hear you yammering away.  Keep your voice down!

*I* did, but my possessions did not! They looted the chest from my shop upstairs. When they realized they couldn't open it, they just took the entire thing... luckily, I keep the key on me at all times.
I'm sure they'll find a way to do so eventually. Tell you what - i'll give you the key. Bring its contents back to me and I'll reward you handsomely.

Vandica's my friend who came from the fountain! She's a little girl, just like me, but not everyone can see her. Only special people!nnMommy says she's not real. Vandica gets real mad when she says that, and turns all purple. Hee...

She's not! I know she's not! She flips coins and we have tea parties and she shows me... oh, I thought you were a special person, too.nnI know. I can prove it! I'll show you where we play. Then you'll see she's real, just like I say she is!
Try and keep up this time!
Excellent.  I'm encouraged by your success; now onto bigger things.nnThe source of the Wyrd's power is their tree.  To strike against it, there are some spell components you will need.

Collect three hearts of the spriggans that guard the Wyrd camp, and also some of the local Worm's Head Mushrooms.nnTake this catalyst, and put them in it.nnThen use the resulting potion on their tree.
As you like. I will not move from this spot until I can win Guendeline's heart!

Oh, the Inquisitor sent you? Right then, you'll want to start up by the temple-- you can see it up on the hill there, to the east. There's usually a priest out front, just let him know you're patrolling for us so's he doesn't get worried.
Ew, why would you want to talk to her?
Finally, after checking on the crafters, head on by the front gates. It's always busy there, and I generally keep an eye on the tavern-- far too much drink in some people there of late.

After the temple, you want to check on the crafters in the southeast part of the city. It's usually pretty quiet there, but occasionally some fool will try to break in somewhere and do a runner out of town.
Propitious timing. I fear they are in more trouble than they know. They think they have the west front sealed up, but that isn't the real danger.
As usual, it's from within. We suspect many of the 'residents' in Crosswych have actually been lycanthropes for some time.
We've developed an accurate method of distinguishing between the infected and the pure. If you could bring several villagers to us under whatever pretexts you need invent, we can test them.
They aren't immortal. They bleed and die just like we do. They're hoping for a bloodless coup — and if they infect enough of Crosswych's populace, they'll get it!
What?! We're utterly defenseless... what am I to do?
Oh, excellent! Thank you-- I was getting worried that we wouldn't have our usual watchful eyes keeping the peace around here. Good to see the trouble hasn't hindered the Lion Guard overmuch.
Then return to me when you can. I wish you luck. Stay safe.
Then return to me when you can. I wish you luck. Stay safe.
Then return to me when you can. I wish you luck. Stay safe.

The King of Worms? I fear for my brother…nnBoth Lion Guard and Hands of Northmoor have a stake in this matter. The alliance is fragile, and a break at this point could allow Shornhelm's invasion to succeed. I must not appear to favor any side.

I'm too emotionally invested to decide that. I trust you to handle this.nnSpeak with Barnard Danvers of the Hands and Inquisitor Ephin of the Order. Also, speak to Caretaker Villas. He has connections at Cath Bedraud. Tell me what you decide to do.

You were wise to come to me. The Hands and the Order despise each other. Neither is poised to look into this graverobbing.nnI know the ex-chapel keeper of Cath Bedraud well. His name is Gui. I say, investigate things with him. Keep matters neutral.

My advice? Way I see it, you crack a graverobbing ring using its hired help. They're the most like to talk with a sword under their chin.nnI say we shake down every bandit and mercenary in King's Guard. One's bound to turn us on whoever hired them.

Obviously, a spy within Eagle's Watch is sending tips to Shornhelm. How else could they find our dead?nnI believe a Shornhelm spy hides among the refugees. I say we round them up. Interrogate them. With the right persuasion, the spy will surely talk
Wha? What're you... talkin' about?nn<Braen is having difficulty focusing on you.>
Wait... Jaine is actually mad? I thought we was jes' playin'! I'm so sorry Jaine, I didn't really mean it, I jes' thought...nn<Braen begins mumbling to himself.>
Ol' Braen -is- in his cups just a bit, isn't he. You're right, I'll lay off. Sorry for the trouble, sir.
I'll believe this when I see it.
It mentioned reaching Annalynne? I do believe that's Warden Godwin's fiancee. Perhaps you had best warn him, they may be aiming to hold her for ransom...
We've developed an accurate method of distinguishing between the infected and the pure. If you could bring several villagers to us under whatever pretexts you need invent, we can test them.
As usual, it's from within. We suspect many of the 'residents' in Crosswych have actually been lycanthropes for some time.
They aren't immortal. They bleed and die just like we do. They're hoping for a bloodless coup -- and if they infect enough of Crosswych's populace, they'll get it!
I didn't... oh, Bal take you! I'm just trying... what? Ah!

Adwyn his name is, and he's in trouble. The Magis dogs were waiting for him, and took him soon as he arrived. They've got him in a storehouse east of town, holding him tight: a brace of Watchers guard the place, threatening any who come near.
While my scouts search for the courier, you might help our Innkeep, Nathaniel Varle.  Poor man has had troubles ever since the goblins returned from Glenumbra.
Inquisitor Roche ordered his arrest.  I am sure Roche wants to retrieve the sword before the Hands - to protect Averos from the murder charges.

The vampire… he sent us ahead, just as you. You're walking into a trap <<1>>. It's he… who wishes to control the power of the Lightless Remnant.nnWe must stop him before he manages to destroy all of Rivenspire. Help me… we'll fight him as one.
The Coldharbour Glyph behind you… activate it. I have already destroyed the Dark Council member who held dominion over this part of the Doomcrag. nnHurry… before it's too late.
Bless you, stranger!  Let's go south to the forest - I can reach my home in Glenumbra from there.
Namira's blight!  I should burn the forest down - it would end all of my troubles.
I'll have his corpse recovered.  There might be a way to speak with him yet, but that will take time.

I anticipated the courier's demise.  I will send a group of Magis Order Watchers to transport his body to Westtry.  There they will prepare a ritual which will allow you to communicate with his spirit.
Oh, this is awful!  My Annalynne!  Could you please check on her? She should be in our house overlooking the town... I cannot leave my post!
What is it? What's this about?

As I said, these are hard, desperate scum. They've thus far professed their innocence, but I can see the guilt in their eyes. nnHave no worries, friend. We'll have a confession soon enough. For now, go gather a few more refugees - just to be sure.

No surprise. These scum are like starving dogs - they'll snap at any moment.nnI've good news. A refugee admitted to helping a necromancer steal bodies. My aide, Heaton, took him to Cath Bedraud to reveal his master. Go meet him behind the chapel.
You're sure, then? We'll clean up after. You'll need to tell Lady Kallath that we found the ones who killed Dalomar.
Good. Let's be done with this, then.
You're sure about this? I don't want to drag you into something this ugly. If we live, you'll need to tell the Sergeant while I keep Wayle safe.
My thanks. I could not have stood against the two of them by myself, much less three if you had sided against me.

Heaton, a spy? I'd not believe it if not for his absence. To think, he was hiding under our very noses. It's too bad you could not bring him back to be put to the question.nnStill... the threat is ended, for now. Tell Captain Blayne of our success.

Luckily, Sevarian has created an elixir that will expose any werewolves in human form. Take it.  Sprinkle it on any villager and if they are infected they will be transformed.  We need to see how far along the infection has spread...

I need to speak to Sevarain. He is concocting an elixir that, when splashed upon a human-form werewolf, will reveal their true nature.  Return to me later and we shall continue on. (Player Level = 17)

What in Daedric hell do you want me to do with that sludge? It smells like horse ass. Speaking of a horse's ass… old Thetis might know what to do. That little grubber can't handle his drink worth a damn, but he's handy with concoctions.

According to my Watchers, Countess Virolynn hired a courier to deliver the weapon to a town in Daenia called Grayborne.  I sent word to Inquisitor Roche of Grayborne - if you want the weapon and the courier, he'll have intercepted both.
Countess Virolynn governs the town of Aldcroft in Urvaius to the east.  Her family was slain by King Ranser.
Watchers are the lowest ranking members of the Magis Order.  We Inquisitors command them, but ourselves answer to the noble High Inquisitor Averos, the leader of the Order.
Ah yes, Mr. Varle. A "charming" man. Let me see that… well, we do have a problem with this sludge and the goblins who made it. I can offer some suggestions, but not all of them may be to your liking.
Well, the direct approach is just that. Find some friends, go directly into the goblin camp, kill them all, and break the barrels of sludge.
Well, I just don't know what the reaction would do. You would need to find some ingredients for me, Ella Blossom and Neri tears, take them to the lake and use them on a sludge barrel.

Goblins have to eat. It would not be unheard of for me to use certain ingredients to make their food "unpalatable." I would need you to collect those ingredients. Then, we could use the goblins' food, rabbits, to give the goblins a disease.
You may take the direct approach, but that may take more than just yourself. The other option may be the safest, albeit unpleasant.

You can either force your way into the storehouse or take the uniform from one of the Watchers and enter in a disguise.  nnEither way, you'll need to escort Adwyn to safety, so the Watcher's don't over hear the weapon's location.

Only briefly, there were Watchers everywhere.  The courier's name is Adwyn.  He did not have the murder weapon when they arrested him.  You will have to free him, then find out what he did with the murder weapon.

Gerard is in the Shornhelm camp below. Enter the camp, find his tent, and steal his plans.nnYou could fight your way in, but I'd suggest a sneakier approach. Slay a soldier and don his uniform. Just avoid the werewolves - they won't be fooled.
This ritual will summon nearby spirits, the courier's among them.  Everything should be in place by the time you arrive in Westtry, you will simply need to make contact with his bones.

In the last war against Shornhelm, Ranser killed Ulorion the grand battlemage, High Inquisitor and founder of the Magis Order. Averos was Ulorion's ablest student, and Ulorion's successor. Averos swore vengeance upon Ranser years ago, and now he has

Averos leads the Magis Order, he's their High Inquisitor. He's dangerous: he and his Magis Order lackeys will be the doom of all Northmoor, if left alone. But there are some in Northmoor who will not leave them alone...
No...  however, you should eavesdrop on the Magis Order.  Those thugs are always crowding the Inn.  I am sure you will find Watchers boasting of Averos' deed.

I knew it! Why flee Camlorn and hide his sword if Averos were not the killer? If he can be proved guilty, the entire Lion Guard could fall. Their abuse of Northmoor would end. You must find that blade - it may be the key.
If the blade is bound for Grayborne, seek out my friend Brennoc there. I shall send word ahead , so he will stop the courier and end Averos' game before it's begun.

We are working on a method that will… coax any werewolf masquerading as a villager out of their human form. The method is not perfected yet, return to me in some time and we can set the plan in motion (Player Level = 17)
Emeric sent you to check on me? That's sweet of him. I imagine he can't get free of the city what with how much of the Order was posted in Kingsguard, but I appreciate his concern. Thank you.
Shortly after the Magis Order moved north to Kingsguard, Camlorn started seeing small raids by undead. We're here to fend them off. You should talk to Commander Blarae, he'll tell you more.
<Laeran closes his eyes and sighs.>nnWe had all feared that, but hoped it would not come to pass. If we cannot have an accord in the city, perhaps we can come to one here, where our goals are mutual.

The Magis Order is painfully short on manpower. The Hands of Northmoor have started sending our militia to bring relief for the Order soldiers. There are bigger problems afoot than our petty squabbles. Commander Blarae could tell you more.

Now I make the poison. Simply use it on at least five rabbits near my garden. The goblins that kill them for food will sicken and die.nnI sincerely hope they don't die right on my noxious herbs and crush them. This is very stressful for me.
Oh, thank you! I've been trying to find my way back to camp for hours now.
I see lots of people. Spare a coin, friend?
I am. Thank you for finding me and showing me the right direction!

You are ever so generous, sir. I'll tell you something— I did see two Magis Order men drag something that looked heavy into the lake here just down there. If you don't mind a swim, you could probably find it.

Sadly, the size of the lake makes a search impractical. The minty smell, however, is common among Greenfoot Roots. A large colony of such grows beside the lake.nnBring me a sample of water from the area. I shall test it for traces of the bog witch.
Go talk to Tactician Veraul. He almost certainly has work for you.

I was ambushed by angry spirits as I tried to pass by the ruins! I had to leave my cart behind and just run for the city. I thought they were going to tear me apart! As if that weren't bad enough, well...
I saw bandits sneaking up as the ghosts gave up the chase. I think they've been robbing carts! It's especially bad because I was bringing weapons to one of the lords in town!

I was just 14 when my parents disappeared. I came looking here for them and then I... forgot.nnMother Murk visited often... she brought sweet things. Oh. They were bugs. Ugh, she made us eat bugs!nnWhen she left, she went north. Into the lake.

I remember... one day, my parents just left. Then one night I heard them calling to me, from the swamp. I went into the swamp to find them, and then... she took me.nnWhenever she came to us, she smelled... minty. Like she'd been rolling in mint.

She said... our parents? Mother had... but she said... my mommy's alive?nnOoooh, that witch! She tricked us! She made us think everyone was dead! Oh, brave knight, I'm so sorry I doubted you! Please! Will you help us find our parents?
Oh, thank you! I've been trying to find my way back to camp for hours now.

The Lion Guard claims Virolynn's chamberlain, Gargast, is a spy. The Hands deny it. If you want details, in this inn are a couple of men at the bar who know all about it. Ask them - if you can get them to stop arguing long enough to listen to you.

We're in the very Shornhelm you fought to protect.nnThe chaos in these people's hearts has turned rotten and black. A dismal sight strains heavily on their souls and twists their visions.nnThis will only get worse. We must put a stop to it now.
Ha! Not me - the Hands have her place buttoned up tight.  If someone could settle this break between Virolynn and Spencer, maybe you could get in to see her. But not before.

I can't help you. We're under siege. Those zealous Lion Guard think I'm some sort of spy.nnI'd give myself up if I thought it would stop them, but the Countess won't allow it. But if you help me run the Lion Guard off, I'll ensure you can see her.

We'll release her docks as soon as she gives us the spy, Gargast. We have indisputable proof he's working for Shornhelm, and I won't have him escaping by sea.nnYou want to see Virolynn? Help us reveal Ghargast. Do that, Virolynn gets her docks back.
Fine! Speak to Chamberlain Gargast, in the mansion up the hill. If you can get the Lion Guard off our doorstep, I'm sure the Lady Virolynn - and Gargast - will be grateful.
I suspected you might have a scrap of sanity about you. You'll find our leader, Spencer, to the east at the docks - he'll tell you what he has in mind. Good luck!

I'd not expected to need such a rare elixir out here - but I can certainly mix it for you. I would ask a favor in return.nnBog lurkers are a constant nuisance to the caravan. Go slay them while I mix your elixir. I'll have it by the time you return.

Indeed I have. It has been some time since I was able to work with such rare ingredients. The elixir shall be, I believe, sufficient to your needs. I wish you luck in your quest to root out the unnatural elements that threaten the innocent.
Elsie Dolban?nnI'd stay away from her.  She's in league with those Wyrd women up on the hill, almost a certainty.nnWoman living alone like that, potions and poisons... up to no good!
At last! Those zealous fools came to their senses!
I didn't expect the Redoubt Camp to be in such good shape. Blarae's last report was much less positive. You must have done an excellent job there. I do in fact have something you can help with.

I really appreciate it. Take them to the innkeeper, Nathaniel Varle. Inquistor Roche in town is quite busy, and probably doesn't need the interruption. Varle is also a good man, and will be able to direct you to anything Grayborne needs.

I need someone to make a run to Grayborne, in Daenia. One of our inquisitors is there with several soldiers, and they're running low on magicka potions, as well as some others. I realize it's fairly mundane for someone like you.
Not a problem. Give me just a moment to inject it with one of my poisons... nnOk, all done. Here you go.nnYou can find Scar's Den to the southwest.
You must intercept Gargast before he reaches his masters in Crosswych. May Gargast pay! I cannot leave Virolynn's side - I'll not fail her again!
Thank you, but wait a moment before you leave. There's more I must tell you.
Fine, help Eliana if you wish! I'll hire hunters to chase him down myself!
We must heal the Countess before she expires. I have managed to slow her bleeding and delay her death - but I cannot leave her side or she'll expire! I need your help!
Thank you! I must ease her bleeding, first. In the meantime, speak with Caldrun. There is more that you must know.
How can you say that? Virolynn's life is more important than revenge!
Of course, my friend. I will summon her.

Now that you mention it... yes.nnFor a most intrepid soul, a real challenge.  The Wyrd have stolen my staff.  If you can find it and bring it back to me, I will tell you how to use it to your advantage against them.

Ah, excellent, you found my staff!nnThis bodes very well for you and I, very well indeed.  I will entrust you with this staff for your next task.  Take it with you back to the camp and kill the Wyress Jacinta.

So I see Roche's poison has not infected everyone.  He is blind, but we know a higher truth.  We have the age and wisdom of the trees to guide us.nnYou helped Elsie Dolban.  Perhaps you will also help us?

We think the goblins fled here. They have powerful shamans with them. Destroying their effigies and weakening their power would be a good start. You could use this thread to make a disguise from goblin parts.
That's a good question.nnI'd say bandits. Wolves. Goblins to the southeast, near the lake.nnOther things are here, but we will speak of those in time.  I would start with the goblins.
All in time.  Leaves are patient for the rain and so should you be.
Did my Father send you? Really? Huh. I thought he'd be too busy drinking to give a damn.  nnHe's gone mad, I tell you... mad!nnI'm surprised he's noticed she's gone.
Let us hurry. Arkay has favored us thus far-- let us not waste his blessings.

The Bloody Eye who are located in the mountains behind the village. They are not your typical bandits, but their leader Sly is a good man.nnThe others are the Nomads in the woods to the north. They are .. different then what you will be used to.

I must think on this for awhile. If you truly wish to help, there is something you can do for me.nnI am but one man, and there are two messages that must be carried with urgency. I would ask use of you as a messenger to one of these camps.

William's madness is new. He tied me up here, said I'd be safer here.nnWe're all looking over our shoulders now, frightened by the wind. William's frightened. We all are. That's what the Daedra are doing to us. Scaring us.

I appreciate your help, but keep a better eye on my pups here, would you? nnIt's dangerous enough out there. I don't need my hounds turning into meals for the scamps.nnI've had my hounds for years. I just met you.
Let us be done with this. I worry about the forces behind these undead, that they can send assassins against us.
I'm glad to hear your opinion, and equally glad of my capacity to disregard it. Elsie *will* leave, my men shall see to it. Good day.
Clearly you require instruction in your methods of persuasion. Meet me at her house and I will demonstrate how the Order deals with situations such as these...

Certainly. This war was started with the swing of a sword. Our King, Vincintian, slew the criminal Ranser from Shornhelm. Although no one wants war, this invasion from Shornhelm probably averted our own civil war.

Ah, there's a tale. The High King, he's a clever one -- he has nine daughters, and married them all off to forge his alliance. Northmoor, Shornhelm, Evermor, Wayrest... all have queens from Hammerfell. Politics! I've no head for it.
There is a ravine, an ancient alcove, cut into the earth, in the forest northeast of here. The ritual is taking place there. I will mark your map with its location.

Lord Ranser is a noble from Shornhelm, and was a member of the Shrouded Throne. Ranser was here on the pretext of diplomacy, but word is that he was threatening King Vincintian. Apparently the Shrouded Throne oppose Vincintian bowing to Fahara'jad.
I appreciate your concern, but i'm not going anywhere.
I appreciate your concern, but i'm not going anywhere.
I appreciate your concern, but i'm not going anywhere.
High King Fahara'jad wears the Adamant Crown. The Adamant Crown rules over all of High Rock, and he's even brought Orsinium  into the kingdom.
The Hands of Northmoor? A recent militia put together by the Nobles opposed to being questioned and brutally handled by the Magis Order. They generally have the support of the common people.

The Magis Order is the local army of King Vincintian. Started more as a mercenary group by a man named Ulorion, they are somewhat fanatical about stamping out the dark arts. Ulorion offered their services to King Vincintian, who accepted.
Well, certainly unrest was brewing… it may not have come to war. The Hands of Northmoor oppose what they consider to be the oppressive and invasive methods of the Magis Order.

Shornhelm attacks because King Vincintian slew Lord Ranser. Lord Ranser was overconfident coming to Northmoor and threatening our king, either that or Ranser was duped. I believe Shornhelm was going to attack no matter the outcome of that meeting.
King Vincintian sits on the Throne of Northmoor.

The Shrouded Throne? They are rumored to run Shornhelm and some say they've been around High Rock for years working behind the scenes in all the nine kingdoms. I know they feel The Adamant Crown is threatening their power.

I'm told Countess Virolynn took the murder weapon to her manor in Aldcroft until she and Vincintian could prove the Shrouded Throne's existence to High King Fahara'jad. It turns out her advisor was working for the Shrouded Throne and attacked her.
The murder? Apparently High King Fahara'jad sent a man here to look into who killed Ranser. It wasn't revealed that it was King Vincintian until the Shrouded Throne revealed themselves in Aldcroft.

He didn't just attack her. He turned into one of these damn werewolves damn near ripped out her throat. I suppose he did it to keep her quiet, but Fahara'jad had an agent there. So now that the Shrouded Throne is revealed, they are attacking.

Can't say for sure... but it feels like eyes are on these farms, watching us. nnFather must have crossed someone before he went all mad in the head.  nnWhy would someone go through the trouble of unleashing scamps and letting our cows out? Who knows?

When you one day pass on, be it in combat or of natural cause, you will come to a crossroads.  Several paths reach out of from here, all leading to different destinations. Some say you will be guided to the right path if you lived a good life...

Leaving? More like forced out! I had the best price on goods in the city. The other merchants didn't like that though. nnI saw their eyes as they passed by my store. Conspiring to get me out of the business permanently if you catch what I'm saying.

Coldun channels power through statues erected about the town you refer to as Alaygon. Only they have placed them within the realm of the Veil. nnThey use this power to attempt a ritual to summon the demon forth into our lands.

What do you have there? nnGrut-Nak's blade? You managed to defeat him? I'm impressed, but why bother? He plagues the nearby lands for days and before Alcaire can stop him, some stranger with no reason slays him. Are you after my position as a guard?
This... this is my mother's! nnHow did it break? Where did you find this? Where is she?

You bring me a broken piece of metal and ask me if I'm familiar with it? Is this a threat? Are you indicating that I too will soon be like that blade - broken and shattered in your hands? nnLet me ask you, are you familiar with my fist?
Please, I have no gold! Do not slit my throat! I did nothing, I swear it!

Coldun uses its dark magic to attempt to turn those who oppose them into slaves of their army. These wolf creatures you see about.. they were also human at one time.nnThis is what they wish to do to the town of Alaygon.

It looks like any other blade I've seen. You might want to head toward the keep though. Word has spread that one of the guards has her eye out for a very specific dagger. Couldn't tell you why though.

Are you deaf as well as dumb? You will assist me in gathering up the goblin's treasure and we will return to Wayrest. If you refuse… the blame in my imprisonment will fall on you. The rest of your days will be spent in the dungeons!
