You will not face the Serpent alone. When you confront it, I will be at your side.
In my experience, there are but two methods for luring a wild beast. There is the simple, easy way and the difficult but praiseworthy way.nnWhich way would you like to know about?

You shouldn't be here. Mother doesn't like it when people trespass. You're a trespasser. You're bad.nnDo you want to talk to her? You want to talk to Mother? Keep going.nnGo deeper. You'll find her... or maybe she'll find you.
Naturally the High Kinlady would send you to me. In matters of every category I am an expert undisputed. What is it this time? An outbreak of Knahaten Flu? Another Gem Spider infestation?

Ah. Indeed. Obviously the Ancestral Labor of Phynaster must be recreated.nnIn three catacombs there sits three pieces of an ancient and powerful relic, the Shattered Crown. Recover these and return them here.

Well enough. We have contained the Maormer to the beaches, though they seized Sunhold Island.nnThey do not press hard, doubtless due to our Oyinaam and their need to reinforce Sunhold. They constantly send Zombies up the bed of the Liriel on raids.

The Oyinaam are works of Isquer sound-magic. They turn in the currents of the Varlines, and as they move, emit a noise noxious and terrible to the ears of Maormer.nnOthers could explain better than I: my strengths lie in the School of Destruction.

The work of the Maormer's revolting Sload allies, I do not doubt.nnZombies have no hearing, at least not as you and I do, and are immune to the effects of our Oyinaam. By walking along the riverbed, the water protects them from our arrows and spells.

Yes, the island off our southern coast. It held little more than a fishing village, but it is defensible and well-placed to serve as a staging point for invasions.nnThe Maormer have erected siege engines on Sunhold that are devastating our gardens.
Do I look like a Wyress? All I know is I asked Alene what she needed, and she said spriggan limbs. She knows her stuff.nnYou still wondering? Go ask Alene.

The Dresan Ruins hold an ancient brazier the Wyrd use to communicate with forest spirits. We burn sacrifices upon the altar to summon them.nnBy burning spriggan limbs, we can summon a spriggan spirit.

We're horribly undermanned - we couldn't protect these refugees if we got got hit. I'd train them myself if I had time.nnI want your help because you know how to fight. It was obvious the moment you walked in. Our recruits can learn a lot from you.

I've been a forester for years, but I've never seen anything like this. Trees don't just come alive and start attacking woodcutters!nnWe've been so busy fighting for our lives that we can't look into what caused it. Someone should.

Life wasn't always like this. nnThe spriggans just started coming out of the forest one day. First a few, then more and more. nnNow we can barely go into the woods to work, except when we're in groups... and armed.

I've been a forester for years, but I've never seen anything like this. nnTrees don't just come alive and start attacking woodcutters!nnWe're so worried for our lives that we don't have time to find out what caused it. Someone should.

They were once peaceful creatures, communing with the trees they called home. nnThe Wyrd lived in harmony with the forest, and the foresters left them alone.nnNow spiggans attack all who draw near. They're filled with hatred, and we don't know why.

Spriggans and their smaller cousins, the rootlings, are forest spirits bound to Daenia's trees.nnThe easiest way to anger a spriggan is by cutting down its tree. nnOur foresters know how to recognize spriggan trees, so we never cut them down.
The spriggans are making it impossible to get any work done.nnBefore all the troubles we're having, these woods yielded the best lumber for miles around.nnThey still would... if we could get at it!
Well, the spriggans have kept us all from working.nnI want to know what caused this.nnWhy did the trees suddenly come to life?

I don't know what's causing this, but I know about something far worse. nnI've heard rumors of an invasion in Daggerfall and Aldcroft. nnThey're asking for more wood than we can supply. They're fortifying something. I just know it!

This mill has worked the same way for centuries. nnWe don't cut spriggan trees, and spriggans don't stop us from cutting the other trees, the ones they don't need.nnSomething's changed. We've had plenty of spriggan attacks. No one knows why.
I've heard those witches talking!nnThe Wyrd say the earth itself is being turned against us. nnThere's something to give you nightmares, eh?
They're a sisterhood of witches. They were forced out of their home by recent troubles there. nnYou should speak to the Wyress Alene. The Wyrd could use your help.

Daedra worshippers! I don't like them.nnNoemi says I have nothing to fear from them, but they're strange, and I'm certain they'll put a curse on me.nnThey give me warts, or turn me into a toad, or something horrible like that!

I suppose they're all right, those witches.nnThey live in the trees and worship nature or some such thing. We keep clear of them. They keep clear of us.nnOne thing, though. Late at night, their songs make the hairs on the back of my neck stand up.

The Wyrd are grateful to us for keeping an eye on them, especially after they were forced from their home. nnSome of the men weren't sure about having witches around camp.nnYou know what? They've been good neighbors.

We are tree and forest. We are water flowing over the earth and wind soaring through her branches.   nnWe were forced from our home, but we will reclaim it.nnKnow this: the woods hold greater dangers than the spriggans.

Yes! They're helpful mystics and wise women. One of the wyresses gave me a charm for finding my way in the forest. nnI had my doubts, but I haven't been lost around here since. nnEven when the spriggans are chasing me, I can always find my way home!

They're witches. They're called the Beldama Wyrd.nnThey told me they worship the Goddess. I think they mean Azura, but I'm not sure about that.nnSome men fear them, but they just follow the old ways. Their ways are strange, but nothing bad.
This appears to be what is left of an Enchanter's Staff.nnFrom the markings, it cannot suggest anything other than the Maormer were trying to control The Serpent.

Thierry said something about losing his ring by the docks. I think it was a family heirloom.nnIt's difficult enough working under these conditions, much less searching for lost belongings.nnToo bad someone can't find it for him. We're just too busy!

I'm worried about that young Daggerfall nobleman who goes out to fish on the western shore. nnThe woods have turned dangerous. Someone should go out there and check on him. nnWe can't. Our hands are full here!

Daggerfall and Aldcroft are ordering more wood than ever before. I hear it's to fortify against an invasion.nnImagine that! An invasion on top of everything else... or is it all connected? Is it one and the same?nnSinister forces are at work.

Keep clear of the abandoned town to the north.nnAll sorts of folks have gone in there looking for loot, but it's not worth it. nnIt's haunted, I tell you. No sane soul should face those restless spirits.

Want to know why Westtry is haunted? The armies of two kingdoms met in battle there. Westtry was caught in the middle.nnNothing but ghosts left now! The bloodshed is over, but the ghosts will be there forever.nnDid you just feel a cold chill? I did.
I'd swear those trappers to the north are poaching deer.nnSeleine Brehat usually handles the poachers, but her hands are full.nnHey! Maybe you could help her!
Amaury came in one night hollering about a tree monster.nnThe others said he was drunk, but I was the one who found him and talked him down.nnHe was serious... and sober.

My cousin in Daggerfall says there's trouble along the western coast, north of Daggerfall. nnI know what you're thinking. No, it's not spriggans. It's something else!nn Whatever it is, it's bad news for the fishermen!

They say I'm drunk, but I swear I saw it!nnOne of those infernal trees, as tall as a tower, chased us halfway back to camp. It's the truth, I tell you! nnI'm not drunk! You want to smell my breath? Yeah, I didn't think so. nnIt's true!

Everyone knows the trappers to the north have been poaching. nnSeleine Brehat usually handles the poachers, but her hands are full.  nnHey, I have an idea! Maybe she could use your help!You should go there.
Daggerfall's ordered more wood than we can get to them. nnI bet they're preparing for an invasion. Fortifications need wood!nnAs if we don't have enough problems.

An impressive treasure, my stalwart <<1>>, and proof that the Maormer are driven forth. I will grant my Baton of Fidelity.nnI would not have you carry this artifact overland. Speak to Vartisan Guyeron oustide about an alternate travel arrangement.
Then you are direct, if nothing else. Artulion stands to the northwest, watching over the conflict on the beaches.
If you can disable the Maormers' spellfire pillars, I will be free to help you defeat the Serpent.
I would relish the chance to assail the Serpent, but these Rogue Discarnates claim the priority. If there were fewer of them, I might be free to assist you.
If my soul gem is damaged, I can provide little support. Please check on it first.
Make haste, Optimate. With this book we shall start the rebirth of The Orrery.nnHurry to Vilmo or the book will consume you too.
So you agree, the choice is mine to make?
The shore swarms with bodies from the sea! Anuiel's grace protect us - I barely escaped with my life!
No... but my companion has been gravely wounded. The creature which attcked us seemed intent on him, but did not harm myself. I feel that this is a sign from the stars.

Once, the coast was a serene retreat - many Exultants spent time contemplating the rise and fall of the constellations from the horizon. Now the sands are covered in corpses long rotted, pollutinng the sea for the rest of the living.

All of Glenumbra has been corrupted.nnTwisting vines are sprouting from the earth, spreading corruption and death, killing beasts, trees, and even people.nnThis corruption has even taken our great Wyrd Tree. Whatever its source, this must be stopped.

What is this? It's... magnificent! Where did you find this? No, it matters not.nnNormally I'd charge a fine bit of gold for this, but since I'm so low on supplies....nnLet's see what we can do. Please, abide for a moment.
Felballin is the eldest of the Altmer kinships, and known for its achievements in the art of sculpture.nnHigh Kinlord Langdruun is blessed by the stars to lead such an auspicious kinship.

It is solely by the grace of Auri-El that we have survived this long. The Varlines flicker and sap our power. We look to the Queen for guidance, but she seeks the counsel of lesser mer. I fear for our future.

Oh, wondrous tidings! I shall take the Varla Lens into my care this very moment.nnAt last we shall be able to restore the Varlines of Varyllis. I will prepare for the rite - will you meet me in front of the Kinhouse?
Foul undead assault our lands from the south, and the thrice-cursed Maormer continue their onslaught unabated. I advise you to seek sanctuary at the Kinshouse.

If you travel due east you shall come upon the Tower of Verdant Grove. It sits perched on the edge of the Stonewake, and therein lies the shattered ship Landbreaker.nnShould the stars align favorably, you shall find a Varla Lens aboard.
The Imagerie is the largest of the Felballin Imago Serries.nnAn Imago Serry consists of statues of Altmer arranged in patterns that symbolize the perfection of the Altmer form.
I have been blessed with the task of supervising the maintenance of the Imago Serries and the Imagerie. The Imagerie is the crowning achievement of the Felballin Kinshouse.

Verily he has lost his way. Those who have encountered him of late indicate that Hainen is attempting to create his own Imago Serry out of living creatures turned to stone. To think my wise teacher could fall so far... it is utterly tragic.
A rend in the very earth, carved by a Maormer ship called the Landbreaker.nnFoul leeches brought up from the depths of the sea prowl the Stonewake, and Maomer Scouts lurk in ambush.
Nimbleberry bushes grow under the dome at the northern end of the Imagerie.nnOnce you have collected enough in the flask I gave you, you need only use said flask on Ameralee.
A Sapiarch is one of the Wise, the recognized authority in a given area of knowledge. For example, Lilia is Sapiarch of Alchemy.
This coast was a serene retreat where scholars contemplated the stars and planets as they wheeled above the horizon.nnNow the sands teem with shambling corpses!
I could not explain it to one such as you, and I am not obliged to do so. Suffice to say I am privy to much you are not. It is not your place to judge my decision.
Dispense with vague implications. What do you speak of?

The Deadsands were once a place of beauty and serenity. We called it the Alabaster Strand, in celebration of the shimmering sand that graced its shore. Now, the dead have been wrested from their slumber, and walk the shores as mindless monsters.

The Imagerie was created in order to celebrate the grace and form of the Altmer. The Felballin Kinship is the keeper of the Imagerie, and welcomes anyone to admire it and meditate upon the sublime perfection of the Altmer.
Sky-Cursed fiends!nnThey are no more than animals, destroying everything in their path. May they suffer a blight upon all their kin!

The Sea Elves, a fierce race of lesser mer who have invaded us repeatedly. Our warriors easily repulse their ill-planned attacks, but with Undead on the rise and the Varlines in flux, this time we are... finding it hard to expel the Maormer.
It is a tumultuous hour for the Altmer. Contact with the Ascendants is severed and the Varlines are wavering. We must hold fast to our traditions, and weather the storm.

I know of the problems with the Varlines, Optimate. But before you label me insane, have you not considered that perhaps it is only now, without the influence of the Varlines, that we are in our right minds?

I do not understand. What are you saying? All your words are coming out backwards, pouring over one another. Red on green. Star patterns.nnDo you feel the lines in the sky? They are twisting. Wincing. Every quiver sends knives down my spine.

Hainen was undoubtedly the most talented Vartisan in all of Summerset. He was among those... unbalanced by the disruption of the Varlines.nnHis genius persists. Now puts it to the more dubious purposes.
They are revolting.nnSload are bloated abominations from the island kingdom of Thras. They practice the vile art of Necromancy, raising and commanding the Undead.

You refer to the madman running about our Imago Serries, turning his own people into stone grotesqueries?nnYes, I have heard. Hainen the Once-Great, the supernally talented Vartisan, jewel of the High Kinlord's Court. An Ouster if ever I knew  one.
This appears to be the hilt of an ancient Direnni blade. The markings put it near the time of the battle of Glenumbra Moors. Please, let me examine it.

We of the Wyrd draw our power from the great Wyrd Tree. She defends and provides, but now the Blood Thorn cult has corrupted her.nnThe corruption spreads from her into us and on to all of High Rock. We cannot return home until it is cleansed.

Wrought of sky iron! Forged in the heart of a glacier! nnThis dreaded blade had an uncanny power over ice and cold. It protected its wielder from ice magic and froze the blood of its victims.nnThis blade was last borne by the Aldmeri Lord Meaglath.

The legends say Meaglath died at the battle of Glenumbra Moors.nnHigh Priestess Vardra of the Alessian order turned the sword's own power against its wielder, freezing Maeglith and shattering Maermacil.

They are Altmer mariners, esteemed Optimate - the bodies of our drowned sailors, returned to shore for vile purposes.nnI am certain that High Kinlord Langdruun, praise his name, has already dispatched one wiser than I to determine their source.

Kinlord Langdruun of Varyllis is a patron of Imagoform -  the art of sculpting and arranging statuary in pleasing patterns. It is not unlike the creation of flower gardens in other lands.nnWe call our sculpture gardens Imago Serries.

Who would dare to challenge us?  Who would dare to threaten our very Mother, whose magic is older than even these temples that have risen and fallen again all around us?  Who dares to poison the Great Tree against her loving daughters?  Who?

We sisters have kept to ourselves, for longer than these forests have known man's influence.  A darkness came to our Tree Mother, and transformed Her into something foul.  For once, we could not fight it.  So here we are, until it can be banished.

Our secrets are our own, stranger. Our sisters do not look past our Wyrd Tree or her circle anymore. We appreciate your help, and we reward it, but do not ask questions when the answers may not please you!

Once, none would dare come close enough to we sisters to ask these questions.  Once, we sisters would not answer.  But now there is a darker and greater magic than our own, and I tell you this: we must be rid of it before it destroys us all.

Our ways are the old ways. Our sisters do not keep with the company of men. We forsake their temples and brash upstart magics. nnIf you can restore our Tree, the Wyrd will return to the land. Then it would be best for you to leave us alone once more.

There is a witch in the bog who styles herself a queen.  We sisters do not like her.  Her magic is that of the Reach, and she is greedy for power.  Yet it was not her magic that took our home from us.

Baridan Bloodsail, the infamous corsair who terrorized the Iliac Bay.nnIt is said he sailed across the Western Sea, exploring the remnant of Yokuda and even stranger lands. He must have used the Waystone you found to navigate.
Egil was one of Vrage most trusted warriors, a Giant-killer, terror on the battlefield, who was eventually slain by a Direnni wizard at the Battle of Meri Darguard.

The trees whisper of ships on the western shore.  What fools men are, who wage their wars while the Mother languishes and the land rots under their feet!  When the battle is done and bodies bleached to bone on grass, we and our Tree will remain.
Egil was one of Vrage most trusted warriors, a Giant-killer, terror on the battlefield, who was eventually slain by a Direnni wizard at the Battle of Meri Darguard.
The horn's name is Taarund, or 'Thunder' in Old Nordic.nnSome say that Egil himself made the horn, and breathed his thu'um into it. To this day, nobody else has been able to blow it.

Duke Roddard Rielle of Normar? He was a vassal of the King of Shornhelm.nnHe fought with distinction in the siege of Orsinium. In fact, he was one of the first through the Iron Gate.nnWe know he participated in the sack of the city with wild abandon.
The skull belonged to Kurgen gro-Agluk, a warlord of the Orcs and hero ancestor of clan Agluk. nnMost of that clan were slain in the siege of Orsinium, but a few still survive.
Telain is said to have wrought the harp out of white wierwood and strung it with hair to given him by Azura.

The music fosters love, either for the singer or the subject of the musician's song.nnTelain used the harp to win the hearts of queens and empresses.nnHe even tamed the wrath of Morrighail, the Shadow Queen of Karrengar.

Tales relate that only the greatest of Breton musicians could make the strings sound.nnAll others who try get blisters on their fingers. nnIf a bard does make it play, it lets him sing with several voices, harmonizing perfectly with himself.
To the west on the shore, a fool and his servant brave the harpies to catch fish.  Fish!  He should hope someone saves him, before the hunter becomes the prey, and well deserved!
Have you seen the fishermen on the western shore?  Those harpies will eat them alive if they're not careful.
When I first came to the Great Tree, I thought nothing could ever threaten Her magic.  I was wrong.  Now we will be more vigilant.  This will not happen again.
Before the corrupting spirit came, the spriggans were friendly and peaceful creatures.  Now they must either be purified or destroyed.
I'll try not to slow you down.
Tell Vestrial I tried my best.
Optimate Telenger was dispatched to rid the shores of the undead, but I wonder if his force is enough to destroy them. Such a concerted attack must be the orchestration of some greater threat.
I do not know who we should look towards to reconstitute our Varline junction. The esteemed High Kinlord must have a course of action for us in these trying times.

It is a magical focus, chiseled from the glass of a fallen star. The Lenses channel the magicka of the stars into our Varlines. Through the Varlines, magicka flows to Kinhouses and monuments throughout Summerset.

I have heard that the waves of undead are even reaching some of the southern Serries. I worry for our Intricants. Especially Liralen, since he has naught but Discarnates to protect him. They have become less reliable as of late.
Vile slug-men from the coral kingdom of Thras! They ooze through my nightmares, abusing the dead and appalling the living. Almost I fear to sleep!
No, I don't know anything about an artifact.
Some of the scholars in the Mages Guild are always looking for that sort of thing.nnThere's usually a Mages Guild Emissary woolgathering near the well in front of the lumber mill.

I've heard of one in the Camlorn area. He's near Aldcroft.nnHis name was... Dalnish? Dalnith? Something of the sort. Yes, search in Aldcroft.nnPersonally, I've only worked with those skilled enough to master the fine needlework nobles require.

You won't find tailosr here, unless they've somehow figured out how a way to whittle wood into clothing.nnI would check north of here if I were you. Search in Aldcroft, near Camlorn.nnThere's many different types of trade going on in those parts.

His name is Dalnith. He does wonderful work. nnHe's been doing a lot lately for the refugees of Camlorn. He's always very busy, but he keeps his chin up.nnIf you need any needlework done, I highly recommend him. He's by the merchants' carts.
Though I have studied the Varlines, those rivers of Magicka that flow across our land, I have much yet to learn. For instance, can a damaged Varla Lens truly be repaired?

I believe so! A tome, Varlines and Vartisans, describes the process in detail - but alas, it was taken by Hainen the Deranged.nnSeek the book in Hainen's mountain retreat, up the path northeast of here. And tread lightly!
You tell me! I've seen stranger things in my lifetime.nnMy eyes may grow weaker with each passing day, but I know a mudcrab when I'm speaking to one!nnWhere is your shell?
I can sense from here that this stone has a magical essence. May I have a closer look?

Why do you want to know? Are you here to steal my shells? I know you're up to no good! You're just like that crazy woman to the north of here.nnThese shells sell for a good bit of coin; you won't take them from me! nnLeave me and my shells be.
To the north of here, along the beach. Crazed lady trying to plunder riches of the dead. She's wild as can be.nnI'd stay away from her if I were you. Something is not... right with her.
From here that horn appears to be of Nord craftsmanship. May I have a closer look?

It will be a mere trifle for me to speed you along your way, now that the power of the Varlines has been restored. When you are ready, I will instantly transport you to Verdant Grove Tower, which lies but a short stroll away from Teriskor Kinhouse.

The Harmonium Fortress is our bulwark against the foul Maormer that invaded Sunhold Island to the south.nnIt is only the Oyinaam along our coast that keep the Pallid Devils at bay. They find the music of the towers most unpleasant.
Is that a bronzed Orc skull. May I have a closer look?
Is that a bronzed orc skull. May I have a closer look?

Eccentricity is tolerated, but I fear Hainen has quite lost his wits. He is said to be attempting to create an Imago Serry by turning living people to stone. What madness! To think my wise teacher could fall so far....
The Maormer are formidable enemies. Their knowledge of engineering and the sea allowed them to design a massive ship with the ability to churn through earth as easily as water.

If you travel due east, you will come upon the Tower of Verdant Grove, which sits perched on the edge of the Stonewake. nnThe Stonewake was created by the magics of Landbreaker. Follow the wake north, and there you shall find the shattered ship.
They wished to destroy our blessed Crystal Tower. However the arrogant Maormer underestimated the power of the mages there, who were able to destroy the ship just short of its intended target.
Be stationary a moment as the Surveilling Aura ascertains your composition. The process is rarely fatal.nn ...Ah! You are, in fact, one of the Numinous.
Be stationary a moment as the Sureilling Tendrils ascertain your composition. The process is rarely fatal.nn ...Ah! I see that you are one of the Numinous
And honor it is, according to the Queen. By her decree, all Numinous are awarded the status of Optimate, with access to the Mulberry and Turquoise districts of Alinor.
If you were, for example, a Maormer infiltrator, the Aura would congeal your blood in your veins.
Accept this Turquoise Medallion, which enables entrance to authorized districts. Retention is mandatory: do not lose or sell it, or the consequences will be dire.
Quest NPC always told me to steer clear of that puppy.  I just wanted to pet him and he ate me!  I'm going to go back to him... he is probably sad without me next to him.

Since I must, I welcome you to Alinor, and to the opportunity to serve your Blood-Kin. My sister the Queen believes you Numinous may be of use in repelling the Maormer. Perhaps. She awaits you within.
Just so. Once again, the accursed Maormer invade our southern shores. And yet the Queen thinks we can intervene on the continent when the Home Isles are under attack! Folly.

Indeed! Each Kinlord speaks for the interests of every mer in his or her domain. In this time of trials, we must stand united.nnMenaced as they are by the Sea Elves, the Kinlords decline to support Our goals. Yet I am convinced we must aid Tamriel.

Indeed! Menaced as they are by the Sea Elves, the Kinlords decline to support Our greater goals. Aid them in My name, and they will embrace Our policies. In this time of trial, we must have Altmer unity!
My Intelligence service doubts the Pallid Devils really have sufficient forces for a major incursion. I suspect this "invasion" is a mere feint. Prove it, and earn Our gratitude!
My spymasters doubt the Pallid Devils truly have sufficient force to conquer our isles. I suspect this "invasion" is a mere feint. Prove it, and earn Our gratitude!

The Varlines power the Oyinaam, which play a music the vile Maormer cannot abide. The melodious sounds weaken their bodies as well as their minds.nn'Tis astonishing such beasts respond to music at all....

Trinimac was the mightiest Altmer hero, a knight of the et'Ada. In the Battle of the Hundred Mer, he held his position against a swarm of lesser enemies. You will need similar courage to face the Maormer.

I am one of the fishers of Sunhold. Every dawn, my discarnates would cast nets into the sea.nnWhen the Maormer invaded, I managed to escape and take shelter here. Others were not so fortunate. Now the Pallid Devils sleep in my very bed.
Rolperil is overdue to report from our last sally against Sunhold Island. I pray that no grievance has befallen him.
Panoit said what? Why that little....nnWhat I did... well, I was desperate. nnYou couldn't understand. The money wasn't worth trading away my values. Please, don't tell Ormax.

I thank you sincerely.nnI feel awful about Thierry and putting you in danger. I can't make it up to you, except by never doing anything like this again.nnI'll do my best to make it up to Thierry, whatever it takes.
I suppose it is comfortable to sit upon that throne of self-righteous indignance. nnDo as you will. I'll not explain myself any further to you.
My wife is sick. Panoit offered me a lot of coin if I helped. nnWith the coin, well, I was going to buy a healing unction from Sibellec up near Aldcroft.
You're right. It is absolutely no reason.nnI feel awful about Thierry and his ring being gone. nnPlease, I sincerely regret what I did, but turning me in won't help anyone.
I feel awful about putting you in danger.nnCould you take this money and keep this matter between us?
Here, take this coin. I don't want any it any more.nnI can only promise you I'll never do anything like this again.nnAs for the Thierry family, I'll find a way to make it up to them... somehow.
My wife is sick. Panoit offered me a lot of coin if I helped. With the coin, well, I was going to buy an unction from Sibellec up near Aldcroft.
Here, take this coin. I don't want any of it any more. I can only promise you I will never do anything like this again.nnAs for the Thierry family, I'll find a way to make it up to them somehow.
You're right. It is absolutely no reason. I regret taking part in Thierry's loss.nnPlease, I sincerely regret what I did, and turning me in will help no one.
I suppose it is comfortable to sit upon that throne of values. Do as you will, I'll not explain myself any further to you.
Thank you, sincerely. I feel awful about stealing from Thierry and putting you in danger.nnI promise that I won't act so recklessly again. I'll do my best to make it up to Thierry, whatever it takes.
I feel awful about putting you in danger. Will you take this money, and keep this matter between us?
On what do you base these charges?
This confirms my suspicions. Damnation! nnWe thought the thief might have been Panoit.nnHearing Moreau might have been involved sickens my heart.
Panoit is a known thief and brigand.nnI fail to see how his involvement implicates a good family man like Warden Moreau.
The Orchestrated Gardens are carefully arranged to play melodies as one walks through.nnAlas, its beauty has been marred by the Maormer assault.

The Fane of Breath is a temple to Mara, the goddess of beauty and love. nnThe mountain winds blow through the canyon the Fane is built around. Instruments are strung between the walls to create a melodious piping for the glory of the goddess.

The Maormer have managed to sweep up the southern shores of Sunhold Island and only the Oyinaam keep them from advancing.  nnThe music created by the Oyinaam repels them. Obviously their taste in the arts is as muddled as they are.

Greetings Advuenturer, I am the great and all powerful Important Mage. I see you have managed to find the magical tome.  That tome would increase my powers and allow me to become the most powerful mage in the land...
Fantastic! HAHAH!  Quickly, dig out the tome and give it to me!
What?!  I MUST have that tome.  You shall regret that decision... I shall return when you least expect it!
I want that tome.  If you give it to me, I will reward you handsomely.  What is your decision?

The Discarnates? They probably went rogue - there was another flicker in the Varlines, so I imagine their binding spells came undone. Watch out for them: they may want revenge for having been pressed into our service.

When the Maormer launched their initial attack, The Serpent, one of our Constellation Exemplars, slithered from its cave, coiled around the kinhouse, and swallowed the model planet Nirn. nnNirn is our Varla Lens!
In the sky directly above the Orrery whirl planet models which replicate their celestial counterparts. The Moarmer smote the Auri-El model from the sky and replaced it with their own foul Orgnavar!
An Exemplar is a magical incarnation of a zodiacal symbol -- a living constellation, if you will. They serve the Orrery, though in time they develop minds of their own.
I am an Exemplar, the embodiment of the power and glory of the constellations. However, I am but one piece in the grand orchestra.
One for each sign of the Zodiac - twelve, plus the Serpent. Excepting the Serpent, each has its own shrine in the Orrery, wherein abides its soul gem: the Exemplar's focus and source of magicka.
I shall help your cause as I am able, though I am but an Exemplar - a mere image of the lissome Lover that sways through the stars.nnWhat do you wish of me, my dear?
It is done. Go with my blessing, and may you be victorious!

An Exemplar is the magical incarnation of a constellation. They serve the Orrery and overtime have developed minds of their own. There are thirteen of them - twelve spread about the Orrery and The Serpent in its lair.
Welcome, exalted creature. This one sensed your approach from afar, and we have prepared for your request. You may speak your purpose freely.

Shall we try and guess your purpose, Optimate? We sense flaw and falsity, and we awake. An enterprising soul comes for assistance. But this is an easy riddle to solve - do you have one that is more challenging?
Fivefold venerations upon you and yours, Optimate. Have you come because of the trespasser in the sky? Even my strength was not enough to sustain Auri-El, and now the impostor stains the heavens.
I sense that you bear a Welkynd Stone, already brimming with the essence of my brethren - but your purpose is shrouded. Will you illuminate me?
Dear Optimate, how brave you are! Your noble purpose clothes you in a celestial aura. Please, let me lend you my aid to restore the Orrery to its rightful order!
Finally! Cannot stand being chained here. Held still. Held to ground. Want to run! Race across the Firmament.nnWhat do you want? Speak!
The magicka flows easily around you, Optimate. From this, I know you are a friend. What can a humble servant of magic like myself do for such a powerful Numinous?
Ah, is that all? I was hoping you would need more personal attentions.nnShow me your Welkynd Stone. I shall infuse it with my essence, and leave it to your brave soul to wield as you will.
And it is granted. Our essence infuses your Welkynd Stone. Walk with purpose, exalted one.

Ah, you've spoiled your own surprise! And now we must reveal that we intended to aid you all along. Thus, I infuse your Stone. Now set all to rights - we wish to return to contemplation of the glory that is the Tower.
If it will aid our purpose, I will give every iota of strength I have! There: I infuse your Welkynd Stone with my essence. Go with glory at your heels!

I find being an Exemplar of the Mage quite delightful!nnThe Mage's three charges are The Apprentice, The Atronach, and The Ritual. Those born under The Mage obviously possess the greatest potential for spellcasting.
The rogue planet eclipses the sky, darkening heaven's glory with malevolence. I shall lend you my essence if it will help divine the purpose of this uninvited spectre.
I know that you will succeed. You must, for all of our sakes. A moment... and there! I have infused your Stone with my heavenly essence!
Yes! Orgnavar. Here. Your stone. My essence.nnNow go. Go! Want to run.
A trivial matter for one as versed in the magic arts as I! Nabuc faernu shindish urunus... and it is done. Your Welkynd Stone pulses with celestial magicka!
Orgnavar somehow bent Suuniqwe's mind. Now she leads the wretched Starblind Altmer. nnThey are intent on remaking the Orrery... once they have destroyed it.
Have you made your decision? Give me the gem, before it is too late!
The Orrery is infested, rotted to the core by Maormer and far worse. I shall start anew, purging the land with my power. But first, I require that soul gem!

Mara is a goddess of beauty as well as love.nnIn the Dawn Age, Auri-El created the bounds that protected Old Ehlnofey, and Mara, his wife, played a melody on the flute to create order and beauty within.
Glorious Numinous, the Kinships of the south do not revere me. By aiding them, the Numinous will be able to unite them under Our banner.
An infernal device of the Sload that the weak-minded Altmer cannot even begin to understand! Its retrograde orbit tears apart the Orrery even now. I laugh to think of it!
The Master commands the ruin of the Aldmeri Dominion! He, and he only, do the Sload obey!
This one is no air-huffing Sea Elf! Tender your question to King Orgnum of the Maormer - if you can find him.
This is the first conversation widget
Begone yourself, dryskin! This one is the reality - you are but a dream!
Speak now, for your power to hold me here will not last forever!
Because the Beacon drove the Discarnates Rogue, which makes it permissible to slay them and harvest their Daedric Soul Gems. Why else?
The wind that blows through the Fane is the breath of our Goddess. nnYet... I hear to the west the Priestess Ahlotica cursing at each gust.
You found one of Commander Lafavre's soldiers. He did not make it.
Truly? That is rather disappointing. Are you sure you won't reconsider?
Five thousand lamentations! All is over - but Altmer dignity requires making an appropriate end.

You think I linger on cliff sides for fun?nnMy comrades and I were trying to climb this cliff but met some peril on the way. I broke my leg and now I have no way back down or up. nnI'll give you the information if you help me up.
To get behind your defenses, you fool.nnThe Oyinaam keep us from advancing directly. Your music is a horrible thing that somehow manages to devastate our minds and strength.nnNow help me up.
So much death.  I'm afraid I can't make it any further myself.  Please tell Vestrial I tried my best and it was an Honor knowing him.

Yes, I saw that Maormer devil - but not until he put me on my back. A wonder he did not finish the job then and there.nnThe failure is mine, yet perhaps I may be redeemed. Find that blasted thief, Numinous. He was headed east, towards the harbor.

The Kirin are often praised by the Altmer as embodying all that we hold dear.nnTo kill one of these majestic creatures would be a crime but if it is the only way then I cannot fault you. They are seen north of the Maze of Obliquity.
The Giant Sea Serpents infest the water off the Tessellated Shores, to the east. nnThey are powerful beasts. To kill one is a feat of honor; its Fang could be crafted into a fine weapon.

To recover Auri-El's Welkynd Stone, which is secured within the fallen planet itself. I must ask you to follow me down into the wreckage and act as my protector until I am able to extract the stone from its bindings.nnLet me know when you are ready.
Prepare yourself. I cannot account for the motion of waves!
That is to be expected. What do you wish to know?
Prepare yourself. I cannot account for the motion of waves!
Mm? You swim, I suppose. You could just as easily swim out. It is not that far, but you could not scale the hull of the ship.

Other Numinous may be able to assist, but there is an alternative.nnTalrien the Archivist possesses a singular item which may aid you. Seek him in the depths of the Umbral Tower, which lies across the bay to the east.
You swim. You could just as easily swim out. It is not that far, but you could not scale the hull of the ship.
The Zombies are quite persistent and will continue on their deadly course unless you stop them. nnTake heed, when they are close to death they will explode!
The Zombies are persistent and will continue on their deadly rampage unless you stop them. nnTake heed: when close to death, they explode!
The Zombies are quite persistent and will continue on their deadly course unless you stop them. nnTake heed, when they are close to death they will explode!
The Zombies are quite persistent and will continue on their deadly course unless you stop them. nnTake heed, when they are close to death they will explode!
It would not be wise to speak of it here. Open it when beset by enemies, and not a moment before.nnThis is not hyperbole, but a sincere warning.

We were colleages, classmates at the Psijic Academy on the Isle of Artaeum. We even shared lodging for the last decade of our schooling....nnMore than that I do not care to discuss with strangers. You have a ship to board, do you not?
I am under no obligation to answer. I have provided aid, as Rolantae wished me to.
It would not be wise to speak of it here. Open it when beset by enemies, and not a moment before.nnThis is not hyperbole, but a sincere warning.
No. Rolantae and I never required more than one.nnAnd thank the Firmament for such meager graces as that.
We were collegues. Classmates at the Psijic Academy on the Isle of Artaeum. We even shared lodging for the last decade of our schooling.nnMore than that I do not care to discuss with strangers.
Ha ha, yes! But the so-very-proper Kinholders look the other way when they need us. And since the Varlines are under attack, and I was once Sapiarch of Astronomy, they most certainly need me.
A most impertinent question, for an Altmer! ...I like you, Numinous. I will watch your future career with interest.
Naturally, since they employ Varla Lenses of my own design. The Sea Elves know that if they disrupt the magicka-flow of our Varlines, Altmer magicka-based society will come apart at the seams.

I applaud your bravery. This method is simple enough. If you make a creature mad at you, it will invariably chase you down.nnIf you have ever seen an angry Kirin though, you might reconsider your options.

This is the Phidian way. Long ago we keepers devised a spell which would tame even the wildest of beasts.nnI now give you a scroll which contains this spell. Once used, the Kirin will follow you to Oblivion and back.
In my experience, there are but two methods for luring a wild beast. Which way would you like to know about?

I applaud your bravery. This method is simple enough: if you make a creature mad at you, it will invariably chase you down.nnHowever, if you have ever seen an angry Kirin, you might reconsider your options.

This is the Phidian way. Long ago we Keepers devised a spell which would tame even the wildest of beasts.nnI give you now a scroll which contains this spell. Once used, the Kirin will follow you to Oblivion and back.

I once read an interesting text detailing the peculiarities of Kirin behavior. The author claimed that Kirin repeatedly sought out the shelter of the Bonfom Benla Tree, which can be recognized by its distinctive yellow foliage and white bark.
A Kirin? I don't believe such a creature exists!

Hmm... a Kirin? Are those the lovely quadrupeds I always see lying under the Bonfom Benla Trees? Those trees have the strangest appearance - with those yellow leaves and white bark. I never understood why we even cultivated such plants.

After many days of searching, I finally came upon a Kirin lying placidly under the yellow leaves of a Bonfom Benla Tree.nnIt seemed to ignore me, until I laid a hand upon its back. Even now I am not sure how I survived.nnBest of luck to you though!
The circumstances were inopportune, but I cannot bear the thought of the Heldarmo going without. If you are not unwilling to try again, I am certain we will succeed!

The Sapiarch of Astronomy at the Crystal Tower has nearly always been a Syldarim.nnGenivra, now High Kinlady of the Syldarim, held that position herself before the Ascendance of the previous High Kinlady.
The Orrery draws magicka from the sky and delivers it across the Varlines to Summerset. To do this the model planets must sync up with the celestial spheres.

Unlike the twelve other constellations, The Serpent bows to no master as it slithers through the sky. It is as shifting as the sands. nnThose that are born under The Serpent constellation are thought to the most blessed and the most cursed.

Nirn was created when the god Lorkhan tricked the other gods into creating a mortal plane, thus upsetting the balance of the planes.nnThe creation of Nirn caused us to lose our link with the spiritual realm.
There are eight celestial spheres which orbit Nirn - the most honored of them is Auri-El.nnThe Elven King Auri-El led a war against the tyrant-god Lorkhan and created the first Altmer kingdom.

Orgnavar is a planet created by the traitorous Maormer. nnThey have named it after their seemingly immortal and self proclaimed king, Orgnum. It is said that he was a Aldmeri noble that rebelled and was exiled along with his followers to Pyandonea.
Those born under the sign of The Tower are able to unlock hidden treasures with relative ease.nnAlways be wary of whose locks you are breaking before you embark on your task.
Those that are favored by The Shadow are able to blend themselves into the darkness. nnWhat you cannot see can be the most dangerous of all.
I run. My favored run.nnFaster than anything on Nirn.nnFaster than wind.nnFaster than lightning.nnYou are still here?
Those born under The Lord will have a faithful advocate in their path to glory. nnThe Lord grants its favored the vitality and might to conquer all.
Those born under The Ritual have a variety of abilities that change depending on the aspects of the stars and celestial bodies. nnLook to the skies, young Optimate.

You wish to... know me? My, but you are bold! Come close, I shall whisper in your ear.nnGrace and passion are blessed to those born under the sign of The Lover. It is said their kiss can steal one's breath away.nnWould you care to to try?
Whoever is born under The Lady is both tolerant and kind. nnIt is often those who stay calm and persistent who are the victors at the end of the day.
Those who are favored by the Apprentice have both an affinity towards magic as well as a weakness to it. nnThey may be more intense than their masters - and perhaps a trifle less cautious.

The Warrior's charges are The Lady, The Lord, and The Steed. He protects them all from the devious nature of The Serpent.nnThe Warrior's favor grants skill with all weapons as well as its bellicose temperament.

From time immemorial Scintillants have been revered as masters of metalcraft. This forge is the instrument of our greatness. Through it, we channel the celestial energies of the Firmament into items both magical and mundane.
We Scintillants hold precision to be the greatest virtue, and prefer clean geometries: lines, angles, planes.

It was horrible. When Orgnavar replaced Auri-El, the Skyharkers bound to Auri-El wailed hideously and tore at their eyes... they became the Starblind.nnThen Prime Skyharker Suuniqwe disappeared! Skyharker Vilmo is the new Prime Skyharker.
Our ancestors built these defenses several centuries ago. The lines of stone channel the power of the Varlines to enhance our protective magics.
I am no metalwright. Perhaps another could tell you more.

The Queen sends a Numinous when I have called for an army?nnVery well; you will need to perform the deeds of an army yourself. Prove your ability in Varyllis' service, and I shall give you Felballin's Baton of Fidelity.

Contemptible mer, they seek only to destroy the beauty and grace that we have created on this Blessed Isle. Stories say that the Maormer seek revenge for wrongs done them in aeons past, but why should the Altmer be held responsible for that?

Never will you experience a more harmonious sense of space than within the Maze of Obliquity. It was designed nearly twelve centuries ago by the Optimate Corbusano, one of the Scintilla Kinship's greatest progenitors.
Here, here! Three cheers! You have done an old man a good turn, and now I must repay the favor.nnBehold! A Daedric monster from the planes of Oblivion! Wawoosh!

Our young Queen may amuse herself by moving pieces on her chessboard, but my Kinship will not be her willing pawn.nnAid my people. Rid our shores of Maormer, and recover our Varla Lens. Only then shall I consider Ayarynne's petition.

Our sky has fallen, <<1>>. You are an outsider, and cannot understand the significance of this. As above in the Firmament, so below in our Orrery - and vice versa.nnI cannot give the Queen my loyalty our sky is mended.

It is without a doubt the most definitive text on the Vartisans' craft. Hainen stole it from the Kinhouse several days ago, for reasons I cannot fathom. What could he stand to gain from a Vartisan's knowledge?

I desire the Queen's support against the Maormer invasion of my lands. She cannot expect my aid while we fight Maormer on two coasts. n nIf you are all she is sending, I suggest you get to the beaches and take a sword.nnYou are dismissed, Optimate.
I do not know where Hainen has gone, though I suspect he lurks somewhere nearby. Go with caution!

Words have power, Optimate. With Altmer books, that is literal truth, not mere poetic license.nnThe disruption of the Varlines has corrupted magical objects. Animated books were once common manuscripts on which powerful incantations were scribed.
The Landbreaker was a massive ship the Maormer sent to destroy the Crystal Tower. nnOur mages destroyed it short of its goal, but it left a scar in the earth we call The Stonewake.
The Isquer Kinship has long been protectors of Mara's Shrine, The Fane of Breath. nnI am honored to be among those protectors, but our focus has shifted to repelling the Pallid Devils in the south.

Today I roam the landnI'll always lend the weak a handnI am a soldier know me by my armsnI trust I will be kept from harmnnA title of respect precedes my namenI'd rather die than have to suffer shamenIn stories and a game I live todaynnWhat am I?

Our most skilled warriors and mages have transferred to the Harmonium Fortress, our southern stronghold against the Maormer.nnIf I were able to return from Coldharbour after death like a Numinous, I would be more valuable to Battlereeve Tariella.
Wow.... You really are an idiot
Your such a wait.... You actually got it right?  Umm... Still get out of my face!
You must be the biggest idiot in the world.  I was right about you!!!
The Daedric altar grips Farmer Vanne tightly, refusing to let go.

Perhaps one. Take this summoning stone. Go east to the Vanne farm and look for Inwold. If you find him, summon me.nnI searched the farm and found no sign of Inwold, but the Daedra there severely limited my search. Maybe you'll have better luck.

Who are you to deliver this to me?nnMatters in the keep must be worse than I feared. Now Lakana entrusts her letters to strangers.nnWait... this letter speaks of a threat to her life. Apparently, she doesn't believe Duke Nathaniel can protect her....

What? She says that if I do not cease my underground market activities she will report me to the Duke. This is preposterous, I will be ruined. I do not have a license to operate in Alcaire. I suppose I have no choice but to comply. Go, tell her.

Lakana betrayed Sentinel, and all Redguards, by marrying that cur of a Breton, Duke Nathaniel. They say the marriage was entered to strengthen the Daggerfall Covenant. I say at the cost of Redguard pride.nIs that all you need of me? I am very busy.
Ha! Ignorant knave, you do not know of the Daggerfall Covenant? It is the alliance stricken between the Breton, Redguard, and Orcish states. Now be off, I have no time for your education.
You're from House Tamrith, correct? I've been given strict orders to keep our supplies for our soldiers until this whole thing blows over.
Nah. I like my job. No need to scrounge, got a good roof over my head, and guards at the door. Lord Dorell knows how to keep a man loyal.
You... you wouldn't! I mean, he wouldn't believe you... Oh, fine, have your blasted supplies.
We charge a hefty markup for selling supplies, I'll warn you. But if you're bent on this fool's errand, I'll sell you supplies for, let's say, twice the normal price.
Well? What're you still bothering me for?
Not unless you can feed my family. They're hiding in the ruins of our home, waiting for me to return with something to eat.nnDeath is all around us. Only the carrion birds feast these days!
Truly? I'm no beggar, but I won't refuse help for my family. Many thanks, kind sir!

Inwold and I live east of here on our farm.nnI've only been gone for a few days! Oh, I'm so worried about him. What if something happens to him while I'm trapped here? I should be out searching for him!nnMay Arkay protect him! I pray he's all right.

No one believed me when I told them the scamps took my husband. nnThey accused me of plotting against him. They even said I might have murdered him!nnNo one is right in the head anymore. Everyone's blaming everyone else, and for what?

It's the same here as all over Alcaire. People are throwing wild accusations as casually as they talk about the weather. Even Duke Nathaniel is paranoid.nnIt all started a few months back. My superiors think it may be some sort of magical madness.

Daedra worshippers, as I hear it. Some say they worship Molag Bal, others Hircine.nnWhoever they serve, Duke Nathaniel has forbidden us to touch them. They made some sort of deal. That's part of the reason I came here to investigate.

Duke Nathaniel rules Alcaire from his home in Alcaire Keep. Like his subjects, he's grown increasingly paranoid in these past months. nnWhen he made a deal with the Glenmoril Coven, it was the last straw. High Inquisitor Averos wants answers.

Our column had just passed beyond sight of Shornhelm's gates when we were swarmed from all sides. nnValen drew his blade, screaming in rage. The rest of our unit fell apart, and we were cut down. It all happened so quickly ....

Shornhelm is at war. The alliance that held the noble houses together has fallen apart. Now they fight over the city like stray dogs over a bone.nnLion Guard soldiers were coming to offer help and keep the peace. They never made it.

We dispatched the last of the free militia of Shornhelm to meet the Lion Guard's soldiers.nnMontclair got to them first. When we drew up, the Wracked Plain was covered with corpses. Most were wearing the colors of the Lion Guard.

I lived by the skill of my blade! The Montclairs had surprise on their side ... and numbers ... and darkness.nnIf you get them on equal terms, they're actually pretty poor fighters, especially when compared to someone like me.

Oren ran back toward Shornhelm when the Montclairs attacked. I heard a scream, and  ... well, I can't say it's likely to have ended well.nnJared fled east, yelling at the top of his lungs. I don't suppose he fared much better.
I knew it! Go get him!
Wylon Montclair is one of the lords vying for control of Shornhelm.nnHe didn't seem that bad before this. Something has changed. Something's … not right.

She's the one who offered aid to my family in these dark times.nnOne noble's as bad as another, but I'd rather have one in charge that cares about the little people.nnIf she wants to help Shornhelm, she has my support!
Cray? Of the town militia? I had wondered where he got off to. Men and women die from the horrors of this land every day. It would be a shame to lose one such as him.

I am the leader of the House Tamrith. My father was of Rivenspire blood, my mother of Stormhaven. A lesser house, but I intend to change that. When we heard word of the happenings in Shornhelm, we marched here. It is time people know of us.

We have to strike back at Montclair, but we must take care of those around us. When we reclaim this city in our name, it will be those who toil, the shopkeepers and the smiths, who bring Shornhelm to its feet once more.

Montclair sent them away. He broke the treaty that held them... then stabbed them in the back, slaughtering them to the south. My house could do nothing. We barely hold onto what we have and try to shelter the innocents within these walls.

That's disturbing news, but not unexpected. Lord Montclair will wait for someone to release the captives.nnThis could be the first major move against our interests, especially if these people are infected with blood fever. We must strike first.

Have you lost faith in House Tamrith so quickly?  nnIf the affliction spreads through the city, we'll be as good as dead. We cannot let the infected escape alive.nnIf you want to help, then tell me: who did she send you to rescue?

Is leaving the townspeople to simply rot any better? Shall they be fed upon in Montclair's holding grounds?nnNo, <<1>>. Sickness does not concern us. We must get to them, and quickly. nnWe will deal with this Blood Fever when the time comes.
Uhn... the altar's true name? It's... jakay-jhe. Speak that to banish the altar and its spell.nnThat's all I know. Please, don't hurt me anymore.
You say you've found a witness to these alleged kidnappings? Bring him before us as soon as you can.
I don't have the time or resources to investigate rumors based on whispers around the city. Find me some hard evidence, and I'll be able to commit my men.
So you've found this vagrant who escaped Montclair's fortifications? I knew he was hiding something. Whatever he plans, I will foil.

My family has lived and ruled in this place for generations. The Treaty allowed Montclair to smile to our faces while he built up an army to bring Shornhelm to its knees.  No more!nnAll around are outsiders, traitors.  Shornhelm needs my rule.
Yes. Now that we have the altar's true name, breaking the altar's power is child's play. I'll have Farmer Vanne free soon enough. Are you ready?
Yes… it should. Daedric magic is always tricky, but there's a good chance this will work.nnAssuming, of course, it doesn't flow back and suck us both into Oblivion. Small chance, but… still ready?

The only thing I know is that we're to bring the bodies to the <<1>> behind Montclair's mansion. He doesn't care if they're alive or dead. nnI'd say the dead are the lucky ones. I can't close my eyes without hearing the screams of the dying.

I've only heard whispers, but they say Lord Montclair uses them to feed someone … or something …  I don't know which!nnI fear they may take me away someday. I've seen our own men go missing, only to be replaced by ones we've never seen before.

The Bloodsworn? Never have those words crossed my ear. I wonder what dark magics they supply to Montclair... enough to give him an advantage. I shall send my soldiers to find more of this... Bloodsworn.nnThank you.

All Daedra have both a true name. These are words of power to banish it back to Oblivion.nnThe altar holding Vanne is a Daedra - though not intelligent. It resists traditional magic. But if a coven member reveals its true name, we can banish it.

It's tricky, but I've learned a thing or two about manipulating Daedric essence. Simply put, we need more Daedric essence than powers the altar - hence why you'll collect the hearts.  I'll extract their energy and use it to break the altar's power.
I know what this looks like, but I'm not responsible. nnRemember the letter you delivered to me from Lakana? It exonerates me... and it incriminates someone else.
Not so fast. I can't resist leveraging a business opportunity....nnSome brigands have taken a foothold in one of my storehouses. Take out their leader, and I'll give you the letter.
Good. My storehouse is the southernmost building on the east side of the creek. nnI'm sure that ruffian will be no trouble for you.
That may be, but I still do what I can to make my way in this world.nnIf you won't help me, I have more pressing matters to attend to. Good day.

By Ruptga! You are a good friend to have, <<1>>.nnI'll bring these lists to Captain Rodrick. I'll expose these Bretons for what they really are. nnI can't wait to see the look on his face! Now I'm certain to get a license.
Now that her shrine is whole once again, you must show your reverence. nnDrink from the basins of crimson and violet. nnIf you are worthy, you will know the glory of Meridia.

Meridia looks favorably upon you! nnI am compelled to grant you this: the Phylactery of Pureblood. It is a potent weapon against the necromancy plaguing Rivenspire. nnKnow this though: what you face here is only the beginning.
Of late I noticed how Sir Hughes would eye my wife. She was a most rare beauty - the type of beauty a man would kill to possess.
I trusted Sir Hughes with our lives. I never thought would betray us! I fear he killed that which he could not have...nnHe will pay. By the Divines, he will pay with his life.
What else would you like to know?

One of my spies said that Ra'ud at-Mara contacted him. He's trying to sell information about a threat to Alcaire.nnRa'ud is a slippery fish. I don't like dealing with him, but he's our only lead. He's at the Mule and Bull. See what he knows.
They are an association of assassins for hire. No one is safe from their blade if the price is right. They are a very dangerous group but my contact might help us.

Go to the Mule and Bull, there you will find a woman known simply as Sosia. Speak the words, "Sanguine my sister," and she will answer your questions. Don't ask why or how I know her, I cannot disclose that.
Who spoke those words to you? Who sent you?nnYou tread on rocky ground.
There's a short list of people who know those words are important to me. I'll have to pay each of them a visit. nnSo, you have my attention. What do you want?
Tailas and I will have a conversation about the virtue of silence. nnDoubtless he sent you with good reason. Tell me why you're here... and what you want to know.

Have a care. Attentive ears are everywhere.nnNo, the Brotherhood didn't act against her. However, I do know the party responsible for this indiscretion. nnI can tell you... after you fulfill a contract for me. One bloodstained hand washes the other.
Then our business here has concluded.nnOn the topic of our conversation, know this: Discretion is best for your health. You will be silent... or you will be silenced.
Be careful of the guards. Sometimes, they are displeased to discover the murder of upstanding citizens.nnIf anything goes wrong, you do not know me.

A merchant whose name I can't disclose has requested the elimination of his competition.nnYou'll remove that target before he ever gets here. nnHere's the plan: you'll follow a Alcaire merchant to a secluded location and then dispatch him undetected.

Master Ahtah's Book of Circles is an ancient copy of Frandar Hrunding's venerated Redguard tome. It predates the reign of Reman III. When he took power, he altered passages in the book.nnUnaltered versions are rare. They cannot easily be replaced.

Rin and Makana are sister and brother. They came from Al'akir to study with Master Ahtah. Christophe is a young Breton, one of Master's most promising students.nnChristophe and Rin met here and fell in love. I doubt Makana ever got used to that.

Doesn't matter. I have a sworn statement from Ganise Oscent that Dabienne Vanne bewitched her beloved.nnYou doubt that, ask Ganise yourself. She's on the docks, with her brother. Unless you can prove Ganise wrong, Dabienne's staying in the stocks.

It's true! Inwold loved me - until a year ago. He suddenly asked Dabienne to marry him. I know the Glenmoril Coven helped her bewitch him!nnI told Brother Stental not to marry them. He didn't listen. Don't believe me? Go to the wayshrine and ask him.

Dear Ganise. Such a sweet girl. She set her cap for Inwold, but he never had eyes for anyone but Dabienne.nnInwold told me many a time how much he wanted to approach her. He was so shy. He finally got up the nerve a year ago. Then I married them!

Bewitch? By Arkay, no. Wait. Are you saying Ganise's claims are why Dabienne's in the stocks?nnThis is intolerable! Go north to the Nurdin farm. Find a copse of three thin trees. Dig between them to find proof Dabienne is innocent. Take it to Sal.

Love poetry? Why would Inwold hide...nnOnsi's mercy. These are horrible. "Dabienne, be my mother hen?" Really?nnThis parchment is many years old. If Ganise claims Dabienne bewitched Inwold a year ago, she's wrong. So was I. Take my key and free her.

Excellent, I have something for you. nnFor recruitment purposes the Brotherhood keeps track of all those who kill in cold blood. This particular list contains the name Lakana. Next to her name is that of her killer's. You may have it.
That is fine; all other murderer's names have been redacted. nnDo not think to use this list to incriminate me. I have another list, upon which your name is written.
What would you like to know?

It's the same here as all over Alcaire. People are throwing wild accusations as casually as they talk about the weather. Even Duke Nathaniel is paranoid.nnIt all started a few months back. My superiors think it may be some sort of magical madness.

Duke Nathaniel rules Alcaire from his home in Alcaire Keep. Like his subjects, he's grown increasingly paranoid in these past months. nnHigh Inquisitor Averos is convinced this paranoia has a magical origin. He sent me here to find answers.
Daedra worshippers, as I hear it. Some say they worship Molag Bal, others Hircine.nnThere's been rumors flying around that they're planning something big, but we have no idea what they're up to.

Nonsense! Speak with my head councilor, Juillen. He can vouch that I've been in court all day. nnIf my court is spreading whispers about me, I will certainly do something about it.nnThank you for bringing this to my attention.
I've heard strange sounds on my watch. It could be a bloodfiend, or it could be something more.nnAre you here to help?
That depends on you. Do you follow the ways of war? Do you prefer the art of healing, or are you one with the shadows?

When the vampires came, I stayed behind to fight. My younger brother remained, acting against my wishes. nnWhen I fell, he gave me a proper burial... at the cost of his own life.nnI am caught between worlds until I can repay him for his sacrifice.
Then your best course of action would be to slay the bloodfiends feasting on my brother's body.nnBury his remains in the grave adjacent to mine.

Then your best course of action would be to heal one of the bloodfiends feasting on my brother's body. nnThe other bloodfields will turn on it. They'll sense the false life your healing imbues.nnPlease bury my brother next to the grave he dug for me.

Then your best course of action is sneaking into one of the homes nearby. nnSteal the Amulet of Holy Light. Use it as you approach the bloodfiends. They should scatter long enough for you to retrieve my brother's remains.nnThen bury him next to me.

Then I can only offer you this advice: beware of the bloodfiends. In groups, they're vicious. When they're feeding, they're worse.nnHowever you choose to retrieve his remains, please bury him in a grave next to the one he dug for me.

What terrible news! I saw her run to the healer's tent, but I didn't thin-nnWait, a vampire? Now we're fighting vampires, too? As if all the undead weren't enough. I hope that creature didn't spread its vile curse!
Not much of a rumor, but they've got a witch over in the stocks. She killed her husband, they say. Some Lion Guard soldier named Derelle is taking her side. If you ask me Derelle is a witch too.

As soon as I heard the news, I knew someone would be coming for mennMy heart grieves for what I must do. I cannot betray my duke, but Sir Hughes is family.nnI had no idea his irrational fears would lead to such a tragic end. If only I'd done more....

He fled to Windridge Cave to the northeast. It's a sacred place. nnInside is the Flaming Fissure. When one of us dies in honorable combat, we cast his sword into the flames.nnIf you find Sir Hughes, please be merciful. He's not in his right mind.

Sir Hughes believed Lakana was planning a Redguard invasion. nnI told him we needed evidence before we could act, but he left. He said we had to act immediately.nnHe returned with blood on his hands. I don't know what Duke Nathaniel will do next....

Names don't matter in these dark times. What does matter is what the group I work with fight for. We are known as the Ravenwatch and if not for us, this town would of been overrun weeks ago. nnOur leader sent me to assist you against the Bloodsworn.

The battle of Shornhelm is just a glimpse of what is to come from the west - the Doomcrag. nnYou should investigate it youself. Come to your own conclusions. When you return... seek us out in the under city. We'll have the answers you search for.

He thinks you to have a special ability that could aid us. The Bloodsworn you slew was just one of many who wait in the shadows, eager to strike. You defeating him was a test to prove yourself to us - in which you succeeded.
I would do anything in my power to help my fallen brother.
As a spectre, my resources are limited, but you can take some of my void essence. Perhaps that will suffice for your task.
There's still sounds coming from the east. Are you and Jerwinna going to do something about this?

I know about Dabienne, but I've had no luck freeing her. The townspeople are agitated. If you know some way to free her, I'd welcome your help.nnConstable Sal's at the center of town. Convince him to release her, and I'll make sure she's protected.
Back again, I see. Are you interested in taking up my offer? I will give you the evidence you seek, if you take care of a contract for me.
Be careful of the guards, they sometimes frown upon the murder of upstanding citizens. If anything goes wrong, you do not know me.
Then our business is done. On the topic of our conversation, discretion is best for your health.

A merchant, whose name I cannot disclose, has requested that we eliminate some competition before he moves in to the region. All you must do is follow an Alcaire merchant to a secluded location and dispatch him undetected.

Not so fast. I never pass up a chance to leverage a business opportunity....nnThanks to Lakana, I can no longer do business in the shadows. I require a license to operate in Alcaire. nnHelp me get one, and I'll share what I know of Lakana's murder.

The duke only allows a small number of licensed vendors in his lands. nnHowever, if the duke found out about the local merchants fixing prices, he'd revoke their licenses.nnGet me the price lists from three corrupt merchants. I'll expose them all.
Good. And here's a friendly warning: Alcaire's guards react strongly to any threats to the local merchants. nnIf you're going to do anything illegal, you'd best do it out of their sight.
I don't care. Bribe them. Intimidate them. Rob them. Kill them.nnDo whatever you feel must be done. Just don't fail me. I want those lists.
Preposterous! Price fixing is illegal. I don't know what you'e talking about.
I would be willing to part with a certain list for a modest sum.nnA thousand gold pieces would suffice.nnThat is, of course, as long as no one knows where this list came from.
Please don't hurt me. Let's be civilized about this!nnI knew this tactic was a bad idea. He's the list.
And here's the list!nnTell no one where you found it.
The blood of an innocent - indeed, this will please our Prince greatly. Be a lamb and place it on the altar, dear. We'll step from the shadows once you've placed the sacrifice.
<<1>>, you've helped me so much, and I want to thank you for it. It's just that I … I don't know what to do now. nnI'm cursed. I'm going to become one of the damned.
How can I face them? How can I tell them that my kind killed their friends and families?nnI've become the monster I once despised.

And where would I go? What would I do?nnEven now, I feel bloodlust poisoning my thoughts. Is it only a matter of time before I become a monster? My thirst for blood will become overpowering. How long can I hold out?
I know my body is betraying me, and my thoughts are dark, but … I don't want to die.nnI worked so hard to save everyone. Why can't I find a way to save myself?

Vampires, you say? Surely you don't believe such creatures exist, do you? nnEven if they did, why would they bother assaulting a city? nnWe do not mean to doubt you, for you have been extremely resourceful, but the notion seems somewhat farfetched.
Your words strengthen my hope. I still have my morals, my thoughts, my identity.nnThis disease is not what I imagined it to be. Then again, what is?

I can't deny it. I'm a monster now.nnPerhaps this is for the best. It means one less abomination will be plaguing Rivenspire. Who knows what horror I might become? Who knows what I might do?nnHere. Take my dagger. Take my life. Kill me swiftly.

Perhaps you're right. Once again, you've saved my life. I can fight this disease and not give in to its madness. I'll do what good I can.nnReturn to <<1>>. Tell <<2>> why I can't return. I pray the Eight continue to bless them.
You must be swift. I'm changing into something hideous, something that will fight viciously and live for carnage.nnDon't let me live that way. Kill me now!

Do you still believe there's a cure for this disease? Can we take that chance? What if the bloodlust overwhelms me? I couldn't bear the thought of killing the same people I protected.nnI've decided. Take my dagger. Take my life.nnStrike swiftly.
I don't feel like a monster. I feel afraid, but I also sense … a gnawing hunger … an endless thirst ….nnI'm afraid of what I might become. I'm afraid of what I might do.
I'm at a loss. I don't whether I should live or die. Maybe I don't care anymore. Why do I have to make this choice?

Honestly, it worries me. Long ago Sotha Sil made a pact with the Daedric Princes, forbidding casual summoners from unleashing them.nnHowever, the Glenmoril Coven have ancient ties with Hircine - if they asked, I don't know that he would refuse.

The coven meets at stones east of the farm. Nissa will be guarded. Take friends, unless you're *very* good.nnTo get Nissa's attention, put this fake sacrifice on the altar. If you decide to face her alone, I have some ideas: a disguise, and sabotage.

From what Inwold said, the coven member who was to sacrifice him was named Sister Agnes. The other coven members may not know she's dead.nnI'll stay here for a bit. If you bring me the robe of a coven member, I can spell it to disguise you as Agnes.

Daedric Princes are fickle, and Hircine prizes only mortal sacrifices. Sacrificing one of his prized Hernes may enrage him.nnIf you gather a fresh Herne heart and place it on the coven's altar during their ritual, I bet *bad* things would happen.

Excellent. This will do nicely. Give me just a moment... there.nnDon't put the robe on until you're going to use it. The enchantment will only last a short time. And don't get too close to the coven - they know magic, and they may see through mine.

I would think you mad for what you say, but you have done more than enough to earn my trust, <<1>>. nnIf this is true, Shornhelm faces a larger threat than I imagined. My scholars shall research more on this matter. For now, I have a request of you.

Stuff and nonsense. No doubt you are weary from your travels. nnWe must focus on the matters at hand. Citizens are losing faith in our protection. Word spreads of a "Resistance" mucking about in our city, giving false hopes of oblivious safety.

The people of Shornhelm have begun to place their faith in certain rumors spreading about the city.nnStories are passed in the inns, telling of a secret "Resistance" that holds a cure to the Blood Fever. We must find if there is any truth to this.

I am the answer you seek. A member of the "Resistance."nnI assure you, <<1>>, our interests are mutual. Our leader requests a meeting. You know a great deal about the true threat that shadows Rivenspire. You can be of use to us.

We're the only survivors from <<1>>. <<2>> of the Mages Guild led the retreat to this more defensible site.nnThey call this place <<3>>. Most of the people here are injured or dying, but I'll fight to make sure they survive.

Bloodfiends swarmed from the northern pass, slaughtering mages and peasants alike. We collapsed the pass to stop the undead horde from completely overruning Rivenspire.nnI led the survivors here, so we could defend ourselves.

It's coming back to me. It was late, and everyone was asleep.nnI heard shouts from inside Ahtah's study. I entered to find Christophe crossing blades with Rin. He had Ahtah's Book of Circles clutched in his free arm.nnNaturally, I helped. He fled.

Rin protected Christophe, even when he refused to take the Dreamless Potion. She didn't want him exiled. When I found out, what was I to do? Turn in my own sister?nnChristophe did this. He thinks he can summon a Shehai. We had to try and stop him.

I do tend to keep an eye on things around here. Someone needs to protect the town!nnAnyway, Martin's been running around with a bad crowd. I don't have proof yet, but I'm certain they're involved with the Bitterhand bandits.

A madness afflicting Menevia. We believe it comes from the dreams of its people.nnThose with the fervor think of nothing but the wants of the day, with no care for future or past. Immediate gratification is more important than their own lives.

We do not speak openly of her, for many in Stormhaven would frown on our beliefs. She cares not for empty worship. She values the defense of the people over credit for her grace.nnShe is dusk and dawn, mistress of twilight. I say no more than this.

Long ago, our benefactor gave me a recipe - a Dreamless Potion. All Spirit Wardens imbibe it nightly. We cannot permit ourselves to dream, you see, or we could fall into nightmare. We live only in the waking world, as our benefactor has charged us.

We are protectors. We do not dream. To do so exposes oneself to threats beyond those most can see. These are what we stand against - the smoky black tendrils of the nightmare.nnYou may have seen the fervor throughout Menevia. We work to stop it.

You have been a great friend to us. Now, I need your help.nnMy initiate, Fahjiri, went to the shrine to the east to complete her rite of passage as a Spirit Warden. She has not returned.nnSearch the shrine for her. Bring me news of what you find.
Dusk and dawn watch over you.
I understand. If you change your mind, please speak to me again.

A Shehai is a mighty spirit sword, created by a master Sword Singer by weaving magic, artistry and the powers of one's own mind. It is a deadly weapon, unseen since the days of Frandar Hunding, who wrote the Book of Circles.
I...I've been drinking for so long now, everything in my past is a blur. Some days, I don't even remember my own name.

A Shehai is a mighty spirit sword, created by a master Sword Singer by weaving magic, artistry and the powers of one's own mind. It is a deadly weapon, unseen since the days of Frandar Hunding, who wrote the Book of Circles.

We were Ahtah's apprentices at Pariah Abbey. My sister Rin protected Christophe. She did not want him exiled by the Spirit Wardens, despite his odd behavior.nnChristophe stole Ahtah's Book of Circles and summon the Shehai He must be stopped!

Several nights ago, I heard two Knights of the Flame talking.nnThey claimed Lakana was raising a revolt against them. They said Sir Hughes should "take care of it."nnI tried telling James Tailas, but he paid me no heed. He should have listened to me!

You mustn't be from around here. Everyone knows how King Ranser declared war on Wayrest. Tried to show High King Emeric what for!nnTruth be told, it didn't go so well. After about a year, Ranser was defeated. Happened right up there on Traitor's Tor.

If you're working for Blaise, you can go to Oblivion for all I care!nnOn the other hand, it has been pretty boring standing up here all by myself. It might at least pass the time to humor you for a while.

Fahjiri was trapped by dro-m'Athra. You slew it. This one is grateful to be free.nnYet Fahjiri worries. The evil used this one roughly. It learned things about Durak. It hungers for him. nnThere is danger. Go warn Durak, now! This one will follow!
What would you ask of Fahjiri?
