This one came to complete the ritual. All Spirit Wardens do. This one drank the potion, and the dro-m'Athra came - a nightmare! The potion was to stop dreaming, not summon it!nnThis one was bewitched, held, hurt. Fahjiri wishes never to dream again.

It is a Khajiit word. Nightmares. dro-m'Athra have haunted Fahjiri since this one was but a kitten.nnFahjiri fled Elsweyr to be free of them, and lived many years in Stormhaven without nightmares. Months ago, they came again. Durak offered help.

Fahjiri's mother was once trapped in a nightmare by the dro-m'Athra when Fahjiri was still in her womb. Mother escaped, but was forever scarred.nnFrom birth, Fahjiri has been tormented in dreams. Only leaving Elsweyr allowed Fahjiri to escape.

For many years, the dro-m'Athra let Fahjiri be. Fahjiri heard rumors of Pariah Abbey, of those who do not dream.nnWhen the dro-m'Athra came to Stormhaven, Fahjiri came to Durak for help! Fahjiri fears Durak's help left him open to the dreams.

Poor souls in Elsweyr have been trapped like Durak, asleep without waking. The dro-m'Athra come and trap them in nightmares. nnDurak searched Fahjiri's soul to try and sever the link to the dro-m'Athra. This one fears they found him through the link.

Could it be? Could the dream world have taken Durak, even while he was awake?nnThere is only one way to find out. If Durak is indeed trapped in the dream world, I must go there. I must free him, even if costs me my life.

You would risk yourself, for us?nnSep's skin. If you weren't right, I would try and talk you out of it. With Durak gone, I must lead the Spirit Wardens.nnIf you really wish to do this, you'll find a potion in our shrine to Azura beneath Pariah Abbey.
You have done all you could. If I live to see another day, we will speak again. I must prepare.

The Dreamless Potion is not all we have learned. We have a potion of dreaming as well - endless dreaming.nnAt any other time, I would not think of using it. There's a good chance anyone who drinks it will never wake. Even so, I must try.

Not told... not told the truth. Bound to this world we are... bound by the nightmares. Picked those of his choosing... gave them his... his protection. Not us... left us to rot.nnThe Ravenfeld... traitor... betrayer... will not have our secrets.

I only... wish to be free. The Raven... he told them... told them the power of the Doomcrag. Those necromancers... he helped them. He must... not be trusted! Left us... to die. Take this.. get far away... fight the power of the Doomcrag.
You... wish to use us too? No better than... the beast! Do you side... with the Raven?

You've collected the writ? We'll examine it right away. n nThe information Ranser's Council held on the Doomcrag is extremely valuable. It's the key to many questions left unanswered for us. nnI apologize for making you go through all this.
My brother? That stupid Blaise, he let his position on the town watch go to his head. He threw my brother in the stocks!nnMartin's the only family I have left in the world. But why do you care?

Martin's taken care of me ever since our parents died. I know he's gotten involved with a rough crowd, but he's always been good to me.nnPlease, you have to help him! If I lost my brother, I don't know what I'd do.
My brother rarely tells me anything lately. He seems restless... I worry for him. If only father was here. Martin idolized him more than father knew.
Mother? Surely you jest. Our mother has been dead for years.nnI was a young girl then, but I remember it well. How can you forget the day you became an orphan?

My brother is an honorable man! If he's done something, it's because I'm keeping him here. In a way, this is my fault.nnSometimes I wish he'd stop worrying about me so much. He needs to do something that will make him happy.
Wake. Yes. That would be wise. Come with me, friend.

They're just some of the locals, but Martin rarely tells me what he's up to these days.nnHe should leave this place. I would miss him dearly, but being here, so close to where our parents died—it's like poison to him.
Yes. He gives me money to survive, and I know he earned it!nnIf he didn't earn it, it's this cursed place's fault for turning him into … this! Oh, Martin! What have you done?

Don't you know the story of Traitor's Tor? Martin's father was Ranser's general. He betrayed the mad king and got killed for his efforts. Happened right up there on the tor.nnIf you ask me, the whole family is a disaster waiting to happen.

Some of the local young men and women. They've been sneaking out to meet up with those Bitterhand bastards. At least, that's what I think they've been doing.nnMartin needs guidance and discipline. Trouble is, he's finding it in all the wrong places.

Martin and his friends broke into the inn. Helped themselves to a keg of ale and a wheel of cheese. Had a grand old time, they did.nnHe's as bad as his father! He's going to stay in the stocks until he tells me where to find his no-good accomplices!

Martin's troubles began when I died. King Ranser's vendetta against Wayrest was in full swing, and he wouldn't let my husband leave to take care of our children.nnAnd when Ranser cursed our family name, things got even worse.

Martin became angry and rebelled against … everything. I could not depart this world knowing he was on such a dark path.nnI only want Martin to be happy. To find his way in life and return honor to our family name.

They became orphans. I died, and then my husband fell at Traitor's Tor.nnMartin was too young to understand. He grew up hearing the tales of how his father betrayed Ranser. He couldn't handle that shame.

King Ranser led us into a war we couldn't win. My husband watched Ranser's madness grow, until he eventually decided to act against him.nnRanser killed him and cursed our family's name in retribution.
Brigands? Is that what Blaise told you?nnI've put up with a lot of lies and insults over the years, but I'd never turn to a life of crime. It isn't in my nature.
What do you know of my parents? My father was a general! He knew what it took to get things done. He knew how to protect the people closest to him.nnI don't think I want to talk to you any more.
I have good news.nnI just got back from a foray in the Barrows! I think I found what you're looking for!nnHowever, I've already found a buyer. I'm sorry, but you're out of luck.
Whoa! No need to get violent! nnHere, take it. It's probably just some worthless trinket.
Ha! Do you see any guards here? Report all you want. I'll be gone by the time they get here anyhow.
A thousand gold! No less! nnAnd I'll even polish it up for you, free of charge!
My mother's necklace? How did you find this?nnI cannot even begin to thank you for bringing it to me.

I had a dream when I was born. I was to found an order and lead it against a great evil.nnIt was only after growing in Orsinium that I realized I was not destined to lead orcs. I came here, to Stormhaven, and it is here the Moonbird came to me.

The Moonbird taught me of the Dreamless Potion, and of the nightmare that lurks in the dream world. It showed me where to build Pariah Abbey, and I carved it from rock with my magic. It told me one day, Azura would call on what I had made for her.

Like Azura herself, it is a wonder to behold. Its crystal feathers glitter like cut diamonds, and its center glows with light. It is wet and slick to the touch, like glass in rain. It speaks inside my mind, and in the minds of those who serve me.

Like all Daedric Princes, her motives are unknowable. I like to think that Azura cares for all her children, and foresaw the madness Vaermina would unleash upon them. Whatever her reasons, we serve her with all our heart and soul.
S'Rashi will not forget your generosity.

S'rashi is known throughout Wayrest. Ask anyone where they would go to find out something. They say, "S'rashi knows! Go to S'rashi."nnIf you can't trust S'rashi, this one has no desire to do business with you. Trust S'rashi.

S'Rashi's honesty and sources are known throughout Wayrest. Ask anyone where they would go to find out something not many know, and they say "Come to S'Rashi'."nnIf you doubt S'Rashi's honesty, this one has no desire to do business with you.
Let me see. Ah, this is a platinum-level invite. The count says you get to come and go as you please.nnThat's more leeway than he usually gives his guests these days.
He's in the manor with his betrothed, <<1>>.nnTonight's festivities have already resulted in four deaths. Better hurry.
I welcome you. I'll open the gate.
I'll open the gate without delay.

I'll open the gate, but be warned. The lands beyond these gates aren't safe for outsiders.nnInside, you're protected by Count Hosni as one of his guests. nnOutside, you're trespassing on Midnight Union and Supernal Dreamer territory. Take care.

Most people of your status aren't worthy of my husband's time. nnHe has the ear of the High King himself! He moves in circles entirely beyond you!nnStill, I'll let you see him ... if you play a game with me! Hosni's so busy, and I'm so bored.

My husband collects rare artifacts. He recently hired a team to excavate ruins to the northwest. nnThey found a rare Altmer statue of Auri-El. Then dreughs attacked, and they all fled!nnYou must bring me that statue. If you live, you win!

You found it! You're not dead! Well done.nnMy last servant wasn't so lucky. He lost. Not everyone can win, after all. Then it wouldn't be a game!nnIt's a shame, though. My husband's still busy. Let's play one more game!
Oh! It's the best kind of game!nnThis one involves my husband.

They've begun fusing my soul to the Book of Circles. We're already merging as one.nnThe book's power can save or destroy entire villages, but it can only be activated when it's joined with a spirit warden.

We had men traveling through Hinault farm when they came across some of Montclair's men. Montclair is usually our ally, so we thought nothing of intermingling our troops. Then in an instant there was belowing and Montclair had drawn blades on us.

Ahtah's Book of Circles is a rare tome, stained with the blood of the Ansei, Makela. Sadir will infuse her blood with a Spirit Master's soul - mine, though I am but an apprentice.nnHe must fail or we will fall to Vaermina.
Sadir leads this band of Supernal Dreamers. They're thieves, and worse.nnThey worship Vaermina, the Daedric Prince of dreams and nightmares.

What? I should betray my king? No, that's not fair. My father was a great man. And a great general.nnIf you're suggesting I join the High King's army and leave this place behind me, I think I see the wisdom in that plan.

I've tried to protect her, but I've done nothing but cause her pain. She's always telling me I should leave this place. Maybe I should listen to her.nnI should find a place I can call my own. Aubrey always was the smart one in our family.
If you want the Moonbird, then make me a good offer!

Oh ho ho! What a grand tale you weave. The fate of Stormhaven rests on you acquiring my Moonbird? If only I'd known!nnI applaud your bravado. However, the fate of Stormhaven doesn't reimburse me for my time. Make me another offer!

My menagerie lacks one creature: the rare and angry Wyvern. They are vexatious to capture and impossible to tame. However, if you gather an egg from cliffs to the north, I could raise one as my own.nnSo, shall we trade? The Moonbird for a Wyvern Egg?

While I am sorry we could not do business, I welcome you to think on my offer as long as you wish.  Please feel free to come and go from my estate at your leisure. You have done great service to my friends, and will always be welcome here.

Now that is an offer! It just so happens I need a warrior of your prowess.nnI would not be loathe to part with the Moonbird for a creature of equal value. I am wary of Daedra. The clever creatures can turn on one at any time.  I propose a trade.

<It would be difficult to escape were I in my true form. I will transform into an egg. Place me in your satchel.nnOnce transformed, I will be helpless - but should any guards search you, they will have no way of knowing I am inside such a small egg.>
<Very well. Return to me when you can... but hurry. Every moment that passes, The Fervor consumes more of Menevia.>

Oh ho ho! Well done, hero, well done.nnThis wyvern will be raised by me, loyal to no one else. Imagine, being the only noble in all of Wayrest with a tame wyvern!nnMy men brought the Moonbird out to the pool. Per our agreement, you are welcome to it.

<It is dangerous to cross Menevia in my true form. I will transform into an egg. Place me in your satchel.nnOnce transformed, I will be helpless - but should any search you, they will have no way of knowing I am inside such a small egg.>
<Very well. Return to me when you can... but hurry. Every moment that passes, The Fervor consumes more of Menevia.>
Some nonsense about breaking into the inn. Blaise's trying to scare me into talking. Wants to know where to find my friends.nnBut it won't work—I'm no tattler!
By the Divines, I haven't done anything! How did I get myself into this mess? Perhaps Frelie would believe me if I said I was innocent. nnDo you really think I should serve my time?

What's done is done. I've thrown my lot in with these men. There's no way out of it now. nnI know Frelie plans to convict me with the rest of the bandits, but I don't want to die. That's why I'm running.

A Shehai is a Sword Singer's weapon, forged by training, meditation and devotion. They are rare; even Master Ahtah has not created one. I was a fool to believe that I ever could.nnSadir will create one by destroying both the Book and me.

I do not need Ahtah's forgiveness! He has never created the Shehai and cannot defeat Vaermina...only I will be able to do so!nWhy do you prattle on so? I will create a Shehai and rule Pariah Abbey. My strength will be legendary! Leave me be.
Now that I am free from their spells, I have enough strength to take us to the Maw's entrance.nnAre you ready to leave this place?

The tor is surrounded! Even as we speak, the Orcs are strengthening their siege. Their force is well-armed and well-trained. We have no hope of breaking through.nnPlease, take my report. We can't hold the tor much longer.

An interesting development! It is likely Dathieu knows where Ranser fell, seeing that he himself delivered the fatal blow. Seek this apparition out. It spoke with you before, perhaps it will speak with you once again.
Are you mad? My plan is flawless! I just need more time.
Yes. I shall return to Pariah Abbey soon to gather my belongings.
With enough funding, I could someday create my own training facility for Spirit Wardens.

Yes...I know you are right. I've tried and tried and cannot create a Shehai. I fear the Cultists will steal the Book if I continue along this path and weaken.nnReturn the Book to Ahtah. I will come soon and apologize myself.

Sir Hughes claims he was under a spell. Ensorcellment drove him to murder my beloved Lakana. nnWithout her, my nights are too long and my days too numerous. nnI can't think clearly. You saw Hughes. What do you think I should do?
I trust your conscience. nnIf you feel Sir Hughes must pay for his transgression, then I'll prepare for his execution.
I trust your conscience. nnIf you feel Sir Hughes wasn't responsible for his actions, I'll prepare for his immediate release.
I'll tell you everything that I can, but we must hurry. They stole Ahtah's Book of Circles, and now they are stealing my soul.
Yes. I shall return to Pariah Abbey soon to gather my belongings.

Yes...I know you are right. I've tried and tried and cannot create a Shehai. I fear the Cultists will steal the Book if I continue along this path and weaken.nnReturn the Book to Ahtah. I will come soon and apologize myself.
With enough funding, I could someday create my own training facility for Spirit Wardens. My family is poor...I can barely afford to train with Master Ahtah as it is.

The basecamp is through the door over there. Keep going up the stairs. I'm holding the creatures off as best I can.nnThey left me behind, and I wasn't fast enough. One of the bloodfiends grabbed me. I feel cold. I feel ... hungry.

Azura is a Daedric Prince and ruler of Moonshadow, a twilight country of shades and half-thoughts. While the Divines remain distant and aloof, Azura touches our lives every day.nnWe believe, unlike her Daedric kin, she wants what is best for us.
Fahjiri stirs but does not wake.

Yes. Sabotage. Daedric Princes like Hircine value mortal sacrifices only. Sacrificing one of his prized Hernes may enrage him.nnCollect a Herne heart, and place it on their altar during the ritual. If Hircine reacts, it may distract Nissa's guards.

You'll need a disguise to get close to the altar. Take a robe from a Glenmoril Coven Initiate. Put it on before you place the Herne heart on the altar.nnThe disguise should keep the coven off you until it's too late. Then, it's just you and Nissa.

Ah, yes! My legendary bloodfiend cure! nnIt's made from a very rare plant that only grows in Summerset. Very expensive!nnHere is his order. If you'd like, I could order you a case of it as well! In exchange, I would only require a modest deposit!
I won't let this stand. That man murdered my wife, as clear as if he wielded a blade to do it.
The packets of bone and ash that were buried in the past, they need to be dug up and destroyed.nnThen you need to kill King Rancer once more to let these soldiers finally know peace.

When I came in this morning, I saw signs of a struggle. Master Ahtah's study was in disarray, his Book of Circles gone. Dried ink covered the floor.nnI saw three sets of inky footprints leading to the window: two sets chasing one, as if in pursuit.

I think Makana fought Christophe, and Rin tried to stop them.nnMakana hated Rin's romance with Christophe, especially since Rin's first husband died in a duel defending her honor.nnI bet one of them took the book. Maybe a Spirit Guard saw something?

I saw a scuffle on the road: two chasing another. I thought they were bandits!n nA mob took one to Hammerdeath Arena. They took the other to Baelbrone, a den of drunkenness and debauchery. nnWhere will you start looking?
I wish I'd done something to help them, if I'd but known who they were.nnI wish you luck tracking them down, my friend.
I wish I'd done something to help them. If only I had known who they were!nnI wish you luck tracking them down, my friend.

This is an amazing find! It will need to go to a major city. Jacel Thorin in Wayrest, Ilian Elante in Elden Root, or Ulare Telvanni in Mournhold should be able to interpret it, depending on your preference. All three of them are highly skilled.

This is an amazing find! I don't have the translations I need to make heads or tails of it, but you should get this to Ulare Telvanni in Mournhold. She'll be stunned. I'll send a runner ahead so that she can expect you.

This is an amazing find! I don't have the translations I need to make heads or tails of it, but you should get this to Ilian Alanwe in Elden Root. He'll be stunned. I'll send a runner ahead so that he can expect you.
You're right. But my poor Charlotte! She never deserved this!nnCurse that man! Curse the beasts that did this to us!

They're kept in cells downstairs until the other jailers come for them. They'll be sent to the <<1>> before the week is out.nnWith all that crying and wailing, I came up here to get some peace. I've no wish to join them. I just do as I'm told.
You're right. I can't be a part of this anymore.nnLord Montclair is wrong. I don't know why he's turned against his own people, but I won't help him do it.
<The captain fails to notice you pick-pocketing the slave key>

Can't say as I know any of those, but as far as Redguards go, Moric Nirine has this beast of a woman in his stable. She fights like no woman I've ever seen!nnWhen she's not drawing blood, I hear he keeps in the slave pits beneath the arena.
Haven't heard of any of those. Couldn't hurt to keep asking around, though!

Your interest intrigues me. I admit, Rin doesn't excite me as she once did.nnShe slays every woman I put her against, but she lacks real bloodlust. She pities those she slays. Imagine! My women should hunger for the kill.nnSo, let us make a deal.
I obviously misjudged you. Be on your way.

I seek Daedric souls to enchant a powerful sword, one that will devour the very life of those it cuts. I have sent others to collect souls. They have failed.nnFill this soulstone will five Daedric souls, and you may trade it for Tahn and his mother.

How laughable! You think to intimidate me here? In my tent? Surrounded by my guards? nnIf I didn't find your insanity amusing, I'd have my guards tear off your skin and make me a coat.nnQuit your posturing. Leave my tent before I am no longer amused.

What is the world coming to when ruffians like you can come into a man's tent and threaten his well-being?nnYou're lucky I'm feeling generous. Fine. Take the ungrateful little wench and her spawn. I tire of them. nnJust get out of my tent.

Well, now you're speaking my language! You wish to purchase Rin and her son for your own amusement? We'll make a deal.nnI paid a great sum to acquire them. I expect a return on my investment. Pay me 100 gold, and they're yours to do with as you wish.

I see she's worth far more to you than she was to me. Very well. Take her. I can easily find another who better suits my interests.nnLob's men will instruct Rin to meet you at the gates. You'll find her son there.nnTake the boy and his mother and go.
Then you're wasting my time. Maybe we can speak again when you aren't poor.

Your competence is refreshing. nnThe sword I'll create with these souls will be without equal. I cannot wait to see it draw blood!nnLob's orcs will instruct Rin to meet you at the gates. You'll find her son there. Take the boy and his mother and go.

Because I was a fool. You really want to hear this?nnWell, it started with Christophe. He refused to take his Dreamless Potion. It made him very sick, you see. nnWe told no one. I thought it was a silly ritual. Then he started talking in his sleep.

I decided to stop him myself, but he was a better swordsman. Makana heard us fighting and showed up. nnConfronted by two of us, Christophe fled.nnWe chased him to the crossroads, where a mob ambushed us. Then I woke up here.

It's a spirit sword made from the wielder's soul. Making one is a lost art. nnNone have managed to summon a shehai since Frandar Hunding, who wrote about his ritual in the Book of Circles. nnMaster Ahtah is obsessed with learning to summon one.

He talked about summoning a shehai. As if anyone could do that! He said he would "take Ahtah's book and learn the secret."nn I should have told someone, but then I'd have to tell them he stopped taking his potions. nnWe'd both be banished.
They say that their grazing land has been flooded. They don't understand the nature of progress; the river must be dammed to irrigate our crops. Many people live in Stormhaven, they must be fed.
Who knows why ogres do anything? Perhaps it is just because they don't like anything that is bigger than they are. All I know is that they must be stopped.

Save me? They need us both! Without my soul or the Book of Circles, the ritual will fail.nnAhtah can use the book to restore all of Menevia, but I am just one man.nnYou can save me or the book. Breaking our bond will destroy one of us.

Makela Leki was a Sword Singer, one of the legendary few who could summon a Shehai.nnI do not know who had saved her blood, or how it came to be on Master Ahtah's Book of Circles. That would be another tale.

Then Ahtah's Book of Circles will be destroyed, and they can never use it to destroy Menevia.nnAct swiftly! Release me from this spell before their ritual is complete.nnI can get out of here by myself. I'll meet you at the cave exit.
Then I go to the home of my ancestors, knowing that the Supernal Dreamers cult has been defeated.nnAct swiftly! They have nearly completed the ritual! The book is over there....

To defeat the Omen of Time's Passage, we must confront it inside the Dreamworld. nnDurak, his initiates, and I will use our powers to open a portal to the Dreamworld.nnTo cure the Fervor, you must enter the portal and slay the Omen of Time's Passage.

Durak and I will rally the magically gifted of Pariah Abbey. nnThey'll meet you below the abbey in the shrine to my mistress, Azura. Enter it through Ahtah's study.nnWe'll link to them from here. When you are ready, meet them inside the shrine.
Very well. Don't be long. nnThe suffering of the Fervor won't end until the Omen of Time's Passage is destroyed.
I am authorized by the Duchess to take you to Northpoint, and that's it. nnAre you itching to leave this cursed place as much as I am?
My advice to you is to stay as far out of this as you can.  Start walking and don't stop until you reach Wayrest.
Suit yourself! I'll be here when you want to leave.
Of course. For all you have done, I will gladly grant you passage to Farpoint Landing any time you want.
All right, all right!  It's over, regardless.  House Montclair has crushed any opposition, and Shornhelm is ours.  I'd watch yourself in the city.  Now let me go.
Some nerve you have to threaten me, after everything that happened here.nnThis army is invincible!  Now pay the price for your impudence!
Never better! I'll have this lil' thing tickin' before you know it.
I'll get this working for you, but then I'm leaving. Bother this nonsense.
One of the constructs cracked a rib, but once I'm bandaged up I'll be more than fine. I can get things fixed in here, no problem.

There's a good chance my... body may be drawn to something that belonged to me.nnFailing that, a fresh corpse is an option. Place the flesh in the Diviner's Collapse and you're sure to draw out a bloodfiend. It may take several tries to get mine.

The ones around here are dead and rotting. The bloodfiends disregard them, preferring something fresher, I imagine.nnI know scavengers and bandits roam the area near here. You could kill one and use its body, if you have the stomach for it.
If you look in the houses around Crestshade, I have no doubt you will find some of the mages risen as ghouls. One of them probably carries it with him.

I kept my personal belongings in our supply cache. When the others fled, many of them were left behind all around Crestshade.nnIf you search them, you may find something my ghoul would be attracted to.
I am Azura's messenger and may speak on behalf of my mistress.
All ghouls crave human flesh, so you could find a fresh corpse, as ghastly as that sounds. There's also a small chance my... body may be drawn to something that belonged to me.

The village would have held, but for the abomination. A dark presence now stalks our homes, holding us in this place. We need to rally Crestshade's dead to strike at this creature!nnGo talk to the dead of the village. Help them however you can.
Surely not. You would have me think this is the end of the world!nnWe've added guards to the watch. Everyone should be quite safe very soon.

We were sure we were safe. <<1>> and <<2>> led the bravest of the troops to the pass, so they could stop those bastards at the source.nnWe thought we'd have the threat contained here by the time they returned. We were so, so wrong.
I remember. Undead swarming through the village, flooding houses... tearing through women and children....nnScreams rending the very air! So much blood! So much pain!

You would not visit a mere dream. You need a vision of Moonshadow, Azura's realm. nnI have a potion that makes one dream endlessly. You can go there yourself!nnPerhaps if we summoned Azura to the shrine, she would save us.

Azura's messenger sent me home. She will likely do the same for you.nnEnter my home and drink the potion. Then seek her mighty messenger, the Winged Twilight. nnThrough her, Azura will speak with us. She will tell us how to summon her to Nirn!

Ah, yes. Noleon Velain wishes to summon Azura to Gavaudon's aid.nnGather Glow Dust from the Will-O-the-Wisps, then place it in the bowl at the Shrine and pray.nnFaith is always rewarded, though perhaps not in the way one imagines.
Dreams are a place where the fabric of your realm and ours sometimes overlaps.nnVaermina is twisting what dreamers see into obsessions. Those obsessions sometimes ended in murder.
Azura is Queen of Dawn and Dusk, Mother of the Rose, and Queen of the Night Sky.nnShe is the Daedric Prince of the twilight.
Then I shall return you to your own realm.

The Mages Guild can't help you right now. <<1>> led an expedition to investigate an undead infestation in <<2>>. Until they return, we can't spare anyone.nnHead west out of Shornhelm and follow the road. Ask <<1>> if anyone is available.

I must have a word with Gerard for his courier choices... Fine, then! A modest delivery stipend. And since you seem to be in the business of deliveries, take the items to my client, and he will provide the payment.
A scavenger with a heart of gold! Fine, then! Go bury them in the dirt for all I care, or strew them about the town! I'll have to have a word with Gerard for his courier choices...
Stealing is such a harsh, judgmental word. I'm simply reviving these lost artifacts, and providing them to people who appreciate their value!
Were you now? Well, I was expecting the delivery from Gerard, whom I already employ, so I do not see why I must pay for his laziness.

The creatures must have infected them while they were held captive. nnWhy did my visions not show me this? The power of Montclair's magic must be clouding my sight!nnYes! That has to be it. We still have time to stop them.

Tristan is at the crossroads between life and death. nnEven after drinking my elixir, his body and spirit are still apart. Normally, he'd be lost to us, but something odd has happened. nnIt's as if the effects of another elixir are keeping him alive.
I think … I think Hinault's son is right. I think I did attack his father.

Rumors? Is that what you call them? I call them facts. My boy was murdered in cold blood up in those Pits. House Dorell sent someone up there to kill them all. He was worried they had already been infected. No chance for any of 'em! No chance at all!

Did he? You'd look a father in the eyes and tell him that his son had to die from necessity? There's always a chance. Always. My boy didn't get that chance. All he got was a cold blade to the heart. The last I ever saw of him, he was so happy...

He... did? I... how do you know? If that's true... please, just leave me be. I wish to remember my boy by the smile on his face and that cheerful spirit of his. Not him as a crazed lunatic. I'll stop the talk of House Dorell. Please, leave.
Do you know how many Altmer diplomats he's sent to me? How many thees and thous I've had to listen to? It's enough to drive a sane mer to the Shivering Isles.
Yes, yes, the same thing every time. "Thee wisest o' Treethanes, t'would further the goals of both our kinships were we to twain our destinies, thou."nnPfaugh!

I like him. He's a leader of quality. It's the fancy Altmer he sends that I don't care for.nnIt's been fun turning him down and seeing them huff and sputter. But the joke is over. May it die in peace.

The Pretender - may worms refuse his flesh - has allied himself with the blasted Blacksap. Everywhere clans are pushed from their ancestral grounds.nnEven worse, he openly courts the Imperial invaders.

Bosmer would keep the Green Pact. Imperials don't perceive the living wood. They see it as a thing - like they see rocks.nnThey murder trees to build walls to keep us out. Set wildfires just to drive us from our hidden places.
Now that is an interesting proposition. Shadowhiskers wishes to hear more. How much are you offering, exactly?
Now that is a smart proposition, my friend. Come, come. Step out of that trap and let us talk like gentlemen.
Hmm. Either you are having a joke with Shadowhiskers, or you are an extremely poor adventurer.nnNeither will get you out of there.
And why would this one consider doing such a thing?
This is true. Perhaps a favor is owed here.
Yes, an astute observation. This one has a greater purpose in mind for his hapless prey.
This one has much use for his arms. It would be most unfortunate to lose them, especially in such a violent way.
Ooh, frightening! And yet… my arms still seem to be in place. How peculiar!

It's stained with an ancient master's blood.nnThey will infuse the blood on the Book with a Spirit Master's soul - mine, though I am but an apprentice. Then, the Book can be used as a weapon, or a shield.nnThey must be stopped.
A Shehai is a Sword Singer's weapon, forged by training, meditation and devotion.nnThey are rare; even Master Ahtah has not created one.

Makela Leki was a Sword Singer, one of the legendary few who could summon a Shehai.nnI do not know who had saved her blood, or how it came to be on Master Ahtah's Book of Circles. That would be another tale.

Ahtah's Book of Circles is imbued with ancient powers that not even Ahtah will invoke. This copy has the power to affect entire villages.nnThe Supernal Dreamers will use that power to destroy Menevia, one village at a time. That's why the stole it.
The Prince? He heard about the Honey Incident? Look. that's just a rumor, all right? I swear on my mother's bones, those Khajiiti females were there when I woke up.

I hired a Khajiit - Shadowhiskers - to recover something the Thorn Gang stole from me. Only fair I steal it back, right?nnWell, Shadowhiskers got caught by the Thorns himself. You free him, I'll do whatever Aeradan wants. Deal?
With Khajiiti? Just tell him to nibble the nape of the neck and hold on tight.nnWhat? Oh! Against the Pretender. I'd love to. Really. I just need a favor first.
At the Thorn Gang's headquarters. It's just east of here on cliffside of Elden Grove. He's locked inside, and there are guards at the doors.

I don't know. They're thugs. They respect money and fighting ability and... well, not much else, really.nnAs you can see, I come up a bit short on both of those. Lucky for me I'm so popular with the ladies.

The prisoners we freed!nnSeveral of them went back into the city against our warning, insisting they were fine. My visions did not say otherwise. nnWe'll need to find them and see if they are infected! I know of three. They could endanger us all.
Very well. Shadowhiskers will let you go. It will make my employer most upset. I trust you will inform the Aldmeri of Sorcassil's treachery.nnI may call on you again, <<1>>. Until then, stay clever.

Will that man give me no peace? Ghak and Irne are driving me insane!nnThere's nothing I can do about it. Wayrest declared that all lands belonging to Ranser's supporters have been bequeathed to the immigrating Orcs.
Then you will remain Shadowhiskers' prisoner.
A greater purpose. Are you familiar with the Horn of Molag Bal? It is an artifact of great power - so great that even Shadowhiskers cannot capture it alone.

I've written a letter of eviction, but to be honest, I don't know who I should evict. I'll invoke the ire of Shornhelm or Wayrest. I honestly don't know which is worse.nnYou should decide. Deliver the letter to whichever one seems more dangerous.

They gave him compensation, though admittedly not nearly as much as the holdings were worth.nnI don't agree with the Orcs coming in and taking our land. I just want to make sure things don't get violentnfor Irne or Ghak. One of them has to go.
What's this? I've only just arrived, and Normar is forcing me to leave?nnHow typical. My people were driven from their homeland. Now we've placed our trust with our persecutors!
Thorkan will hear of this treachery!nnWhat Wayrest gives, Wayrest thinks it can take away. This insult will not stand!
Of course it's a mistake! Take your papers and politics and get off my land!
Eviction? Normar can't do this to me! Doesn't he see what Wayrest is trying to do?nnOrcs are nothing but two-legged beasts! How can he think to trust them in our town?
If that's the way it is, then I don't want to live here anyway.nnYou can tell Normar that my family will not accept this insult lying down!
You'd best do that! I've got my rights, and no fool with a foreign crown can take them away!
And you must be the dupe Sorcassil hired Shadowhiskers to eliminate!
What else would you call it, when one's prey lies prone and helpless before him?
A tempting proposition, but this one must decline your offer. Perhaps another time.
Ugly, is it? And smelly? Why...!nnStep forward, you hideous wretch. You're going to pay for those insults.
Yes. I know.nnWhat is your point?
He a friend of yours? We caught him trying to steal some from us and locked him up inside.nnHe's the worst thief I've ever seen.
That's generous of you. Real generous.nnWe'll take a walk. I think we can trust you to watch the door while we're gone... here's my key.nnPleasure talking to you.

Me? Ha! No way I'm getting in there. You see the claws on those things?nnWait. I've seen you in the pit, haven't I? You beat one of the tigers!nnThe Khajiit's a friend of yours? Here, take the key. Just don't tell anyone I gave it to you, eh?
Just because you're more experienced and better armed than us doesn't mean you can push us around!nnYou'll have to catch us first.nnHere's the key to the door. Goodbye!

Within Aphren's tomb you'll find <<1>>. His dreams hold a Daedra: the Omen of Counting Stars.nnRead this scroll when you're near <<1>>. It will put you to sleep. Then I'll send you into Godrun's dream, so you can slay the Omen.

Sorcassil hired Shadowhiskers for this job, yes. Normally this one does not take assassination contracts... but the Canonreeve made an impressive offer.nnSuch treachery! The Canonreeve must be exposed, no? Go then. Tell your people.

Uncle Henri doesn't let me take Jenny outside. Aunt Ilise doesn't care, but I have to listen to Uncle Henri.nnJenny's in my toy box. You can go see her if you want. I don't play with her much anymore.  It's no fun having a doll you can't take places.
Wind Keep isn't as big as Wayrest. The grown-ups are even sillier there, though.
In Wayrest, all the grown-ups do is laugh and go to parties. My parents went to a party…and they never came home.nnHere, they're all busy with stupid things, like counting coins or stacking papers.
I liked Wayrest because my parents were there. We had a nice house. My friends came over to play.nnThen the grown-ups acted silly. I didn't like it after that.
The door gives way before your might!

I looked everywhere and couldn't find them. A week after they left…I don't like to talk about it. They died.nnUncle Henri and Aunt Ilise sent for me to live with them in Wind Keep. Aunt Ilise is Lady Mayor. I don't have any brothers or sisters.

You owe my visit to a Telvanni mage, the ancient wizard Galthis. He is a doppleganger, one who can disguise himself as others.nnGalthis is in Stormhaven even now, disguised as one of you. He influences Cumberland's dreams with not a soul the wiser.

High King Cumberland remains out of my reach. I cannot call to him. Someone interferes. I now believe it to be the same one who summoned me.nnI will not tolerate such insolence. No one may keep me from the nightmares of another. You will fix this.

I can no longer send nightmares to Galthis. He has developed a charm to keep me from his mind.nnThis was never part of our agreement. No mortal may keep me from the nightmares. Galthis grows insolent.nnWe can help each other.

Weigh this one life against the fate of so many. Is it really so great a cost?nnEnter the dream world, bring me the skull of Galthis, and I will trouble Stormhaven no more.nnRefuse me, and my Omens will plague Stormhaven until it burns.

Do not mistake my intent. It is Cumberland's nightmares I desire, not his life. If you take his head in his nightmares, your High King will suffer not a bit in the waking world.nnRefuse me, and my Omens will plague Stormhaven until it burns.

If I knew the method, it would not stop me. It is powerful magic, more powerful than I have encountered before.nnOnly a few mortals can hope to thwart me. I will not tolerate it. After you break his spell, the traitor will never sleep soundly again.

I was bitten by... a creature! Clawing, biting, a rabid monster! Soon after I began to... hunger for flesh, for blood! I couldn't take it anymore, so I tried to leave before I hurt someone... but I was too late.

Sorcassil hired Shadowhiskers for this job, yes. Normally this one does not take assassination contracts… but the Canonreeve made an impressive offer.nnSuch treachery! The Canonreeve must be exposed, no? Go, then. Tell your people.
I'll go away. Far away. I'll find a place to hide, someplace where I can't hurt anyone.nnI don't trust myself. Stendarr help me! I'm so hungry!

One of the three noble houses of Shornhelm. <<1>> tried to persuade <<2>> to grant him control of the town. Instead, King Emeric forced him to sign a treaty that shared power equally.nnMontclair always chafed under that treaty. Now's he's scratching.

Oh? nnHe's been standing at that same spot for quite some time. I was beginning to wonder if he was all right Perhaps he simply lost something. nnIt's beginning to get quite unnerving, honestly. Maybe Scarlette has put a curse on his legs?

What a sweet thing to say! I do wish he had said it himself.nnIt's not a burden at all. I rather enjoy my research. The Cursed Ones are so mysterious! So intriguing! Researching them is a guilty pleasure of mine. nnI do appreciate his concern.

I... well... thank you. I'm flattered. Really, I am.nnI apologize, though. I'm committed to my research. I study... Vampire lore. nnI'm afraid I have little time for any other diversions. You do seem sweet, though. I'm sure we could be great friends!

Pardon? I don't even... I don't know the man that well! What... wait... I... no. nnWhat's wrong with him? What's wrong with you? How could you deliver a message like that? I'm not that kind of girl! nnBesides, my heart belongs to my research.

The Treethane is a fine customer, yes. Very gracious to think of Shadowhiskers while so busy drinking and lying with females.nnShadowhiskers thanks you from the tip of his tail. Blessings upon your home. Many fat kittens. That sort of thing.

From Hotspur? It's been a while since I've seen him. He's not someone you'd soon forget, if you know what I mean!nnYes, I have some nice grain. For the Horsemen, it's free of charge. You can take it.nnOh, and... tell Hotspur that Nathalie said hello.

I'm not surprised! Though my clan has tended its herds in <<1>> for hundreds of years, we keep to ourselves.nnThey say we're descended from the giants of <<2>> because of our courage and strength. We're like our horses: proud and enduring.
It's Jenny! Whenever someone touches Jenny, she hurts me! That's why I put her in my toy box. nnPlease, make the bad things go away so we can go home again. I want to go home!
Yes...thank you. Can we go home now?
Do we have enough soldiers to fall back? Ha!nnOkay, I'm going. Be careful out here.
I don't like leaving my post, but I can see the wisdom in it.nnWhen my men are ready, we'll go back to Oldgate.
Too little, too late.  nnThe best we can hope for now is defending Oldgate.

Obviously, I didn't make it as far as I would've liked.  nnGetting in here was easy enough, but those damn creatures swarmed me. I fought them off, but they kept biting, and I kept bleeding. nnCan't even get bit by the right damn beast. Just my luck.
Okay. I'll see you back at the base. nnBe careful.
Have you ever been in love, <<1>>? nnYou're right. It was foolish of me to come here alone... but I must live on! Surely, Verandis can help me. nnI can't die! I must live on! For Leah! For love!
Only Godrun has the key. You will likely have to take it from him by force. You will not stand a chance with his men around; you will have to wait for them to go on patrol.

I am in your debt, but I still need your help. Godrun may be insane but he is right, the dam must be defended. Perhaps he will see the light if we take care of the ogres.nnMeet me at Camp Gavaudon, to the north, and together we will deal with them.
Hah.  Well.  Nathalie.nnShe's a fine woman.  A good friend.  nn... why, what did she say?
Hrm.nnSo... all right, then.  Other topics.nnToo bad about the weather.  And the corpses.
Nathalie?  Well.nnI suppose.  Yes.  Somewhat.  She's charming, you know.  nnMaybe once, some time ago.  I seem to remember.  Possibly.

Once I was the pack mother of the wolves your kind call the Cinderfen. I left this world many moons ago, but my spirit was compelled to return.nnI cannot rest until I know my children are no longer corrupted.

Young Bosmer used to summon me and pester me like some manner of oracle. "King Faume, how can I be happy?" "Toad-Eye, does being dead hurt?" "Is your eye a toad or an eye, I'm confused."nnMy apologies. You were saying?

Bosmer bring the bones - and only the bones - of their dead here for interment. There are some rooms reserved for Treethanes and Spinners, but no discrimination as to which tribe is laid where.nnIn death, we're all equal.

The Fatesinger is a musical instrument that was played by a Spinner to reveal the true nature of things around him. nnIt reveals only current truths, not future fates. Bosmer live in the now, and have no interest in events yet to come.

By her royal decree, I am to return to Elden Root to face judgement? This is rather unfortunate. I must say I am quite content where I am.nnInform her majesty I must decline the summons. Will there be anything else, messenger?

Every tribe or clan has its own Spinner who interprets matters relating to the Green Pact. nnSomehow a Spinner gets fed when he tells a Meal Story, is given gifts when he tells a Generosity Story, gets drunk when he tells a Drinking Story.
The cultists command them to transport the bones to Haventown, where they are building some foul device.nnThey tried to command me, but I'm old and stubborn.
Do you honestly expect me to return, knowing what awaits me?nnI imagine Ayarynne did not expect me to obey either. Tell me, what are you to do, should I refuse the Queen's will?
I answer to none but the God of Schemes! His will I follow, not some foolish young Queen.
target: Non rispondo ad altri che al Dio degli Intrighi! È il suo volere che seguo, non qualche sciocca giovane Regina.

source: Is that so? And why would you harbor such a hope?

Why would he do that? That fool is going to get himself killed!nnIf you must follow him, leave our quarters and turn right. Follow the tunnels up, and you should find a passage into the manor. nnBe cautious. We don't know what awaits you in there.
My life is not my own; it belongs to my lord Molag Bal.
In that case, I have a proposition. Spare my life, and I will divulge to you my secret knowledge of the Horn of Molag Bal.
Death does not frighten me. But perhaps my living could prove useful to you….
I knew you would see reason. What do you want to know?
I see. It does not surprise me that the Queen has enlisted a more sordid sort for her errands these days.nnA bribe suits my purposes well enough. Take the money and be gone.
What would you like to know?

The Claw serves as an anchor to Molag Bal's domain of Cold Harbor. It allows the planemeld to manifest so strongly here.nnI would not even think of taking it if I were you. The power of the Claw cannot be controlled by one such as yourself.

I know a powerful daedra guards the Claw, roaming the temple interior. More over, my lord Molag Bal long ago placed certain enchantments on his Claw, spells that would alert him to any malign actions directed at the artifact.
Tch. Alhas should have warned you to speak more discreetly, child.nnI can help you, yes. This is a town divided, neighbor against neighbor. You must watch and listen to discover who can be trusted.
Not far from here.nnThe Claw rests upon an altar in the deepest recess of our Temple.
To recognize each other we use... let's say, a pattern.nnIf you hear someone use the same word twice, they may be a loyalist discreetly asking what side you're on. Try to reply in the same pattern.

The Horn serves as an anchor to Molag Bal's domain of Coldharbour. It allows the planemeld to manifest so strongly here.nnI would not even think of taking it if I were you. The power of the Horn cannot be controlled by one such as yourself.
An enchanted barrier surrounds the Horn. Should this barrier be breached, a powerful Daedra will be summoned to protect the Horn.
The Inner Sanctum of our temple, which lies just east of this room. nnThe Horn rests upon an altar there, in the center of the Sanctum.

Just so, just so! And I'd find you a friend in cause, unless I miss my mark.nnShould you find yourself accidentally causing some kind of riot or rebellion, I just might join in. That's the sort of fellow I am. Giving. Always willing to lend a knife.
Well, in times like these you have to keep looking up!
Loyalists? Well, I wouldn't know anything about that. No, no. I swear upon my mother's grave. She's still alive, so I don't think she'll mind.nnShoo, shoo! Get out of here.

You seek my husband? I'm afraid you've missed him, child. He's taken Helethrun for a walk. Ah, sorry - Helethrun is our pet Senche-Tiger.nnI don't know when they'll return. If it's urgent, they usually walk around the roots of Elden Bole.
I think everyone in Leaftower needs help. Don't you agree, friend?nnIt's good to know there are others who feel like I do.
I'm taking a break. No point in wearing myself out.
Wh- what? Are you a spy? A traitor?nnCaptain, help! There's a rebel here!
As I lean in, Helethrun opens his eyes and draws a gurgling breath.

We'll need to bring his wandering spirit and his torporous body back together. nnYou should carry his body to his spirit to merge the two as one... or you could find the spirit and bring it back here. Yes, I suppose that would work better.

His spirit separated from his body and wanders these halls. nnLuckily for him, his experiments with potions appear to have worked in his favor. nnBetween the potion he drank and his will to live, there's a hope of bringing him back.
It has been a long wait indeed. I am loyal to Prince Aeradan, and if he needs me I'll be ready.
My sister went to go trade for imported wood but she hasn't returned yet. I've been itching for my new bow!
Bold words yield a quick death.nnYou should move on, stranger.

It's no feud. It's theft.nnThat Breton is using my land to let his cattle graze! If that's not plain thievery, then I don't know what is.nnIf he doesn't stop, I'm going to have... um... a talk with him. Yes. We'll... talk.

By her royal decree, I am to return to Elden Root to face judgement on charges of treason?nnNever. I answer only to the God of Schemes. Do not be so hasty to kill me though, <<1>>. I may yet be of use to you.
target:
Per suo decreto reale, dovrei tornare ad Antica Radice per affrontare un giudizio per tradimento?

Mai. Rispondo solo al Dio degli Intrighi. Ma non essere troppo precipitoso nell'uccidermi, <<1>>. Posso ancora esserti utile.

source: As you say. It seems you are committed to this murder. Be done with it then.nnUnless, of course, there is some other way I could dissuade you….
I know that you seek an artifact of Molag Bal, the source of the corruption which spreads from this place. Spare my life, and I will aid you in this cause.
My death will only please my master further!
I see. It does not surprise me that the Queen has enlisted a more sordid sort for her errands these days.nnA bribe suits my purposes well enough. Take the money and be gone.
What? Why? Are you- You're one of them, aren't you?nnGuards! I found a traitor!nnDon't forget my reward!
I knew you would see reason. The object you seek is called the Claw of Molag Bal. What do you wish to know?

The Claw serves as an anchor to Molag Bal's domain of Cold Harbor. It allows the planemeld to manifest so strongly here.nnI would not even think of taking it if I were you. The power of the Claw cannot be controlled by one such as yourself.

I know a powerful daedra guards the Claw, roaming the temple interior. More over, my lord Molag Bal long ago placed certain enchantments on his Claw, spells that would alert him to any malign actions directed at the artifact.
Not far from here.nnThe Claw rests upon an altar in the deepest recess of our Temple.

Separated? But my body is right here in front of you!nnYou're right though. Something does feel rather off. I just quite can't put my finger on it.nnIs it cold in here to you as well? Been freezing for what feels like days now!  Can't just be me.

Some Bosmer have been a little more sneaky than usual. There are rumors that someone's trying to start a rebellion. It's more likely to be a mass suicide.nnThe Imperials are here to stay. We may as well profit by it.
Sometimes I wonder that myself. nnI cheer up by remembering that those with an active lifestyle live longer. They can run faster from dangerous things.

Hah! Y'ffre help anyone stupid enough to admit that.nnThe Imperials keep a short leash. Anyone who stands up to shout "freedom" gets knocked down and beaten.nnI feel sorry for anyone who tries. It's safer to keep your head down.
Deal with me? Wait, you don't have to do that. I never wanted it to get this far!nnLet me go. I promise you won't see me around here anymore!
Thank you! May Stendarr bless you for your mercy. I'll leave right away!

Help? I'm afraid I'm beyond that point. You must listen to me or Tildus' life is in danger. I know what I'll become if I wait much longer. You must put an end to my life. I could not rest if I was to harm or even worse, murder, the one I love.

Tildus will not be pleased with my decision. He  may even try to stop me, but I will convince him it is for the best. Please, let me speak to him for a bit. nnI will meet you at the building nearest the east watch tower. Wait there for me.

Perhaps... perhaps you are right. Something Montclair's men spoke of caught my ear. They spoke in hushed voices of a resistance, one in which could challenge Montclair, but swore allegiance to no house. There were rumors that they held a cure.
Lots of people have been infected. We can't help them all.nnVerandis feels we should be in your good graces, however. I'm sure he'd be willing to help you... this time.
The Daggerfall Covenant is more important than life itself. It cannot support the admission of half-breeds, such as this Altmer.nnHe hides behind a Breton name, but his kind must be purged.
I am. nnThank you again, stranger. This is not an easy task for anyone. If... if you speak to Tildus again, let him know I'll always be with him.

Take this remedy. Hurry back. nnIf the infected becomes a Vampire inside the walls of Shornhelm, we could have a massacre on our hands.The deaths would then be your fault, since you wouldn't end her life. nnIf you're going to go, then go! Quickly!
Yes! Yes, they do!nnThank you for finding them! I suppose in the future, I'll have to be a bit more careful where I level my accusations.
What... what is this? It feels... feels as if my fever is breaking. I dare say it's too soon to proclaim a cure, yet I'm feeling better already. Wherever you got this, you have saved a life this day.
Are you mad? The sharpest weapon I've ever held is a scythe.nnIf the corsairs come to the farm, I'll be the first one running.
Thank the Divines! I'll have to apologize to a few people now; I've made some accusations that are obviously unfounded, because here you have my missing valuables! Thank you again!
My father's netch paperweight! This is a one of a kind; can't get them outside of the capital. Thank you for finding this.
Ah, the soul gems are intact! I was afraid someone would pry the gems out of my mother's earrings, but they look none the worse for wear. Thank you!
Some citizens in Wind Keep owe tax tokens. Altogether, they have shorted the treasury one gold. They must pay, or they will die.
Excellent! The debtors are plain citizens of Wind Keep. Without strict adherence to our tax laws, I would have nothing to count!
It can't be just any gold! It must be their gold! That's how the treasury works. Will you collect their taxes or shall I send the guard to behead them?

Long ago an underground river flowed beneath Leaftower. The dry bed of it forms caves under the town.nnIf you could bring digging tools from the Eledrim Camp, we could dig down to it, and pass information out to the Eledrim.

You mean, everything the Duchess owns? If that happens, I'll just find another farm to work on, and I'll still have my hide!nnFind another farmhand to help you. I'm leaving before this gets any uglier.
If the duchess is finally sounding the call to war, I suppose I have no choice.nnI won't let them take what we've built here!

Conscription?nnThis is adding insult to injury! I break my back every day putting bread on Northpoint's table. No one defends us here in the fields.nnNo. You go fight for Northpoint. I'm staying here.
Take up arms against them?  I've never fought before, but if there ever were a time, it's now.nnAye, I'll go. It will be an honor to fight, if they'll have me.

Obligation?  I want no part in this war.nnMy Andrew, if he still lives, is in the hands of the Nords.  He's been captured. You came here to send him into danger.nnYou want my cooperation? Then save my son.
I...  yes.  nnYes, I should. I'll go.
Recruit me? So it's true! The Duchess is about to declare war.  nnI'd be proud to serve my kingdom. I'll go. Thank you, and good luck to you.
Me? I'm nobody special. nnNot unless you know how to make a girl feel special. You wouldn't know how to do that, would you darling?
How could he survive capture and then put himself in peril again? I don't understand it.nnYou're right. He's a man now, and it's his choice. I'll abide by his decision.
What...nnNo; it doesn't surprise me.  Fine, take the both of us, then.  I can do no less than follow his example.
Yes.nnI'll report to the Northpoint keep by sunset.
Yes, I should. Thank you for your help.

We've been trying to get a look at the lower city. The massive statue platform in the middle of town is more than just a display - we believe it is some kind of elevator. We've read reports on the upper city, but no one seems to have ever gone below.

Look for machine buildings, spread out around the upper city. The notes we have suggest that repairing the machines in those buildings will re-activate the elevator, and maybe some other things as well.

We had split up to fix various machines. I was watching the lift in the center when I heard some kind of loud gong, and then the constructs activated. I ran back here to try and get help, but I'm cut off from my team.
I've been too busy to think about paying taxes, so I'm probably late. Here's my token payment.nnLord Henri's so particular. He minted special gold coins just for taxes!

When the constructs activated, Hurgen tried to fight them. He yelled at me to get in a building, because the constructs wouldn't go in them. So far, he's been right. I'm hoping my team has taken cover in the buildings, and I'd look there first.
I've been too busy to think about paying taxes, so I am probably late. Here's my tax payment token.nnLord Henri's so particular, he minted special gold coins just for taxes.

Despite everything, if we can get the elevator fixed I still want to see what's down below. We came all the way out here and we knew what we were getting into. My team knows how to fix the machinery up here, so if they can be found we can go deeper.

An old acquaintance you could say. I take it she got my message if she sent her lap dog to snoop around. Always putting others in danger while protecting herself. She hasn't changed one bit. I suppose I'll need a more direct route to settle things.

Oh, nothing without a little help from you of course. nnIf you manage to find your way out of this little mess alive, deliver this message to Scarlette. Tell her Jon will meet her at the gazing stars. She'll understand.

The giants were here long before any of us... before Bretons... before the Altmer....nnThe gentle giants keep their herds on the plains of Boralis. Long ago, they tended herds all over Rivenspire.nnThe horsemen are allegedly their descendants.

You, stop me? Haha!nnYou've fallen into her trap, haven't you? A love sick dog vying for her affects, doing her every wish. I was like you once. I learned my lesson the hard way.nnYou won't stop me. I will kill you and I will find Scarlette myself.
My lovely Gurz, I do so miss her. I do not regret my duty's here but I so long to see her again.
Let me see. Ah, this is a platinum-level invite. The count says you get to come and go as you please.nnThat's more leeway than he usually gives his guests these days.
He's in the manor with his betrothed, <<1>>.nnTonight's festivities have already resulted in four deaths. Better hurry.
So you are the reason the bombardment has ceased, thank you stranger. I shall leave for Orsinium at once. Please tell Borkul gro-Shatur, my second in command, that he will take over my duties here.
My Gurz lies ill? Malak, what should I do? The dam remains under attack from the ogre scum but I feel I must be by my wife's side.
Those letters are my only joy here in Stormhaven. If only the dam did not lie under siege from the ogres. Were it not for those curs I would go to here immediately.
I've already paid my taxes. Lord Henri should keep better records.
If Lord Henri wants my taxes, he can collect them himself!

I've been in the count's employ for almost a decade. nnMany call him a shrewd negotiator. People he's bested in negotiatons call him greedy.nnThat's not my call. The count's been more than fair with his guards and his staff.

If you ask me, the lady has a low opinion of anyone who isn't nobleborn. That includes us. nnIt's irksome to listen to her complain about us when we're the ones who keep her from harm.nnOf course, you didn't hear that from me.

Excellent! I've only threatened to kill two citizens for non-payment so far, but that still upsets my wife.nnMy wife, Countess Ilise, is Lady-Mayor. Please pay your respects to her and give her the treasury's key. I cannot see her while I'm counting.
Gil-Var-Delle has been taken, traveler. The top of the mountain is no longer in Grahtwood. It is within Cold Harbor - the realm of the Daedric Prince Molag Bal.nnYou must do something to halt this.
Centuries ago, Molag Bal was summoned by ritual pact and given leave to destroy Gil-Var-Delle. He left something behind, something which killed and rotted the wood, and bound that peak to his realm.
Gil-Var-Delle has been taken, traveler. The top of the mountain is not in Valenwood. It is within the Daedric Prince Molag Bal's realm of Cold Harbor!
I'm sure he'd be happy to help!
I have taken the countess away, but it was with no animosity.nnThe countess you see before you is the reflection. The true countess is in the mirror and that is where she will stay.
I am a spirit, bound to the mirror by an enchantment which can never be broken.nnWhy this is so is unimportant. What matters is that I make the mirror show the truth to those who wish to see it.
The mirror shows the truth of what is happening near it.nnIn this case, many wonder what is going on around them. By looking into the mirror, you will see the truth of recent events.
I will not go without a fight!
I will not. The mirror is the gift to her, but she is the gift to me. nnIf you wish to release her, you'll have to pass through to the other side into my domain. You shall find a warm welcome there.
I'm mourning my son. Now leave me in peace. I will complete the rites and then... join him in death.
My... daughter?nnShe must forget about me. Since death from the sea took my son, I lack the will to go on. I will join my son in death.
Elleste... my daughter. You are right. Though it grieves me to go on, I shall try - for her sake. nnI shall compose myself and then return to the Kinhouse. Thank you, Optimate.

Then death is my choice. Thank you for respecting that, Optimate. The sea shall take me, as it did my son.nnHis grave is at the bottom of the path on this island. As my last request, I ask you to please light the candle on his grave.
No... no, it is not. Nor, I think, is it what my son would want. nnBut how shall I live? Am I to abandon my resolve as easily as that?
My precious son... you, you cannot know...nnPerhaps... but, no! I will stick to my resolve.

Family is everything to the Altmer. Each is a member of an extended clan group called a Kinship, and owes allegiance to a Kinlady or Kinlord. All the members of a Kinship live together in a great home called a Kinhouse.
You will find them all over Varyllis. The largest is the Imagerie, to the east of the Felballin Kinhouse. nnAlas, many of our Imago Serries lie in disarray due to the depredations of the Maormer.

Just as the Discarnates concern themselves with the upkeep of Altmer designs aboveground, Aquiferi Elementals maintain Summerset from below - routing waterflow and pushing up nutrients. nnPerfection demands diligence!

Each great Kinhouse is home to an extended family of Altmer, a Kinship. For example, to the east of here is the Isquer Kinhouse, home of the Isquer Kinship. Kinlord Maldarawo, head of the Isquers, is the leading Altmer of his region.

The Crystal Tower, on a mountain east of Alinor, is home to the Wise, the leading Altmer in all areas of arcane knowledge. They are called the Sapiarchs, and they wield great influence with the Queen and with the Kinlords.

To power our magical civilization, we draw Magicka from the sky through giant patterns that mimic the constellations. Each starpoint is grounded by a Varla Stone, a meteoric gem. The Varla Stones are connected by lines of magical force: the Varlines.

A Battlereeve is a commander in the Altmer military. Only warriors who have served Summerset for at least four centuries may be appointed Battlereeves. Many a Maormer has met his end on the edge of my blade.

Accursed Sea Elves, the Maormer of Pyandonea have invaded Summerset time and again throughout history. Now the scum once again taint our southern shore - and they seem intent on damaging our Varlines!

Title and social status are of supreme importance to the Altmer! The Queen has granted all Numinous the noble title of "Optimate" - an honor indeed! You need defer to no one of lower status than a Kinlord.

Beneath the Queen are the Kinlords and Kinladies. Next come Optimates, then Exultants, then commoners such as guards and artisans. The Ousters are pariahs, Altmer who have left or been banished from their Kinships. I pretend not to see them.
I know you've done such good things for the people of Northpoint in their current woes.nnIt's a shame you don't know the whole story, though.

I would never speak out directly against the duchess, of course. Still, I'm concerned about war with the Nords, and I'm not the only one!nnIt's not for me to say. You could talk to my master the Baron, though.

Baron Chirane's manor is just across the town square, north of where we're standing.nnTake this insignia ring. We can't be too careful who we associate with, and that ring will prove your... trustworthiness.

Now you see, I'm glad you asked. After all, one man's sedition is another man's patriotism.nnWe can't afford a war with the Nords. There are too many of them. There are just too many to fight! If we want peace, we must accede to their demands.

Well, my friend, it may be more prudent to make sure we're on the winning side, if you know what I mean.nnI'm not the only one who thinks the Nords will make better friends than enemies. That's just between you and me, of course.
Hah! Good one. A good jest! You are not just a noble hero, but a noble hero with a sense of humor.nnNo harm done. Now on to other topics ….
Balcone? That bastard led us here.nnDon't believe anything he says. He's the cause of all of this!
Balcone? That bastard led us here.nnDon't believe anything he says. He's the cause of all of this!
What? Wait!nnYou're going to kill me? Why? What did I do to you?
There are old ruins on the hillside to the west. They're guarded by restless spirits.nnI wouldn't go near the place for love or gold, but I hear folks still find ancient artifacts up there.
Restless Spirits walk these lands, drawn to ancient artifacts of power.nnYou might find something of value up at those Breton Ruins on the hill, or you might not.
When my father was a lad, he found something strange at those Breton Ruins up on the hill. Now the place is guarded by Restless Spirits, but he thinks there are still items to be found there.
The western cliffs of High Rock are beautiful. Many young artists have climbed them to paint the alluring landscape.nnI hear that's not possible anymore with the harpy infestation. That's a shame.
The western cliffs of Glenumbra have a great view of the best fishin' hole in all of Tamriel.nnIt's a shame the entire area is infested with harpies, though. nnI sure hope they're taken care of soon.

In my younger days, I used to travel to the north. Then I'd walk along the western cliffs of Glenumbra. nnThe winds always lifted my spirits.nnThe other day, I went out again. To my horror, the land was infested with harpies!
Several folks have noticed missing items lately. We're not sure if it's a thieving ring or plain forgetfulness, what with the spriggans about and all.

I heard someone searching my things the other night. Gave me a scare it did; thought it was one of those spriggans!nnThe next day, I heard the Thierry family's ring was stolen. Do you think there's a connection?

We don't have many nice things handed down in our family so I'm not worried. Still, it's sad to think that someone would steal the Thierry's family heirloom. nnHope someone catches the evil-doer soon.

Ormax knows? I never should have stolen Thierry's ring. I didn't know what else to do. nnI needed the money for a cure for my wife. She's sick, but no one knows what's wrong.nnPlease, tell Thierry how sorry I am. After what I did, I can't face him.
Thank you. I won't fight you. I won't try to escape. nnLet me know when you've spoken to Thierry.

Very well. I've brought this on myself. nnTell Ormax I'll turn myself in, right after I tell my wife what happened. She does't walk too well these days.nnI was so foolish. After I'm gone, who's going to take care of her?
Roberte did this? How could he do that? We're friends!
Thank you for your mercy. nnThat ring was in my family for generations, but I won't trade my friend's life for it.nnSomehow, Roberte, Paulette, and I will work this out.

At least let me bring him in myself. He's saved my life so many times. nnIf anyone is going to take him to jail, it should be someone he trusts.nnCould you give us a moment? Let Ormax know that Roberte and I will be there soon.
That stubborn fool. If he had asked, I would have given him the money.nnPlease, <<1>>. Spare Roberte.nnWith Paulette as sick as she is, she needs him. Don't arrest him. We can work this out!
Greetings!  I'm the QA Talker, I like to converse about a great many things.

Ah, yes. In a few days, we'll march on the city, and that's just what we'll need. This will make things much easier.nnI'm sure the baron will be looking for his reward. Take this to him with our thanks.

He leads a group of bandits called the Red Rooks. They've been taking advantage of High Rock's troubles to poach the King of Daggerfall's game.nnHe's also killed several Wardens who tried to arrest him. Nasty character, as I hear it.
Melita? Why, she's probably upstairs in her chambers.

All of the Red Rooks wear uniforms. If you can steal one and put it on, you might be able to get close to Glenan without causing trouble.nnDon't get too close, though. If you do, or if you attack anyone, they'll see right through your disguise.

Chirane!  I should have known. nnI'll give you this chance to prove yourself.  Kill that meddling servant.nnReport back to the Baron first, so we don't arouse their suspicions.  Then find Marita and kill her.
Just because I can't clap you in Northpoint irons doesn't mean I can't take care of you myself.nnReport to your Baron.  Then meet me here.  And we will settle this once and for all.

Ah, excellent! A brave friend has become a loyal and trustworthy friend. How fortunate I am.nnPerhaps it's best if we keep these meetings to ourselves. After all, it's very hard to know who to trust these days.
Oh, <<1>>! Whatever you desire!nnPerhaps we can discuss some more... private matters.

Our party set out to investigate the Plane Merge. As soon as we crossed that boundary, it was as if our world shifted upon itself.nnMost of them simply vanished. The ones who didn't were set upon immediately. The undead swarmed us.

Laughter and darkness. nnWhen I woke up, a thirst for blood compelled me. I wanted to feed on someone... anyone... my companions weren't safe.nnI can't control this. You can't let me leave this place. I might hurt someone.
Not a word. And every day we sit here is more gold I won't be earning. And all because some noble or another decided he wanted to be king.
No, I'm their bard, but I lost my lute so I thought I'd improvise with a hammer and an axe.nnOf course I'm their blacksmith! Now go bother someone who likes to talk.

Yes, I am a priest of Arkay in service to the Shornhelm Guard. I've been tasked with giving the final blessing to the soldiers that died in today's battle.nnWithout Arkay's blessing, they could become enthralled by a necromancer.
They really aren't the most forthcoming bunch when it comes to revealing information. But I did hear a few of the soldiers say something about "putting the Montclairs in their place."
Haven't you heard? Baron Montclair has taken control of Shornhelm's upper city and his forces are on the march. It's like Ranser's War all over again!
Go on ahead! It's not like I'm going anywhere anytime soon!
I'm not grumpy. I have a wonderfully sunny disposition.nnNow get lost before I accidentally hit you with my hammer. Twice.

Nothing I wouldn't have against any other man, woman, or Orc who considers duty more important than soldiers' lives.nnIf she really cared about saving lives, we wouldn't still be here. We're just waiting to die.
Haven't had a chance to talk to a veteran <<1>> like yourself, so go ahead.

Thank you, but this task is mine to perform. I trained many years in Wayrest to become a priest. If I can't get through such a task on my own, I'm not suited for this calling.nnArkay tests me. I must prevail.
Arkay is the Divine of Birth and Death. He is the caretaker of the Divine Cycle all mortals must traverse—change and rebirth. Only through him can we fathom the meanings of these heady concepts.
More questions? I haven't done anything wrong!nnI don't care about Shornhelm's problems. I'm on my way to Fell's Run to meet my cousin. These soldiers have no right to stop me!

Because these soldiers are a bunch of empty-headed, magic-snorting imbeciles! I've half a mind to crush their heads together and just leave.nnI won't, though, because I don't want any trouble. I just want to be on my way.
My cousin said there would be work there for me. I think he owns a farm now. It's hard to imagine him farming!nnHonest work's getting hard to come by, so I'll take whatever I can get.
As long as I'm here, I might as well. What do you want to know?
To the Doomcrag? You're sure 'bout this? That's a bad, bad place over there. There's a reason ain't no one heading out that way no more.nnBut hey, a ride's a ride. Don't matter where you're goin'.
All right. Just let me know when.
Come aboard, then. I won't mind seeing this place from the stern of my ship, that's for certain.nnReady to shove off for Northpoint?
Well, come back when you're ready to shove off.

Really, <<1>>? How do you know I won't turn without warning and attack you? Even now, I can barely contain my rage.nnI trust you, though. We need to get back to Verandis. We won't have much time before I lose control again.
Terrible things happened in Moira's Hope… death… destruction… too much pain. nnI'm sorry. I can't speak about it anymore.

There was report from travelers on the eastern road from Shornhelm that something's wrong at Moira's Hope.nnLieutenant Gagnon's troop was patrolling in that area, but we haven't heard from them in days.  I'd like to know what the hell is happening.

"Know?" I do not "know." Sapiarch Lilia did mention a distillation of Nimbleberries known to remedy magical paralysis.nnNimbleberries grow under the dome at the north end of the Imagerie. Gather some in this flask, and apply the result to Ameralee.

Oh.  Yes.  nnWell, you could kill carrion harpies or the helhests or... well.  It's probable some of the corpses out on the battlefield will be tainted.  You could... harvest some of that flesh.nnSorry.
Gods! I thought I'd die in the street today. This will feed my family for at least a week!nnBless you, stranger. Perhaps there is hope, after all.

The Varlines aren't flickering here - they're down! Maormer spies have stolen the Isque Varla Stone and taken it to their strongpoint on Sunhold Island. nnFeeling ambitious? Then help the Isquers recover that stone before their defenses give way.

They hold magicka, much like a Soulstone. Of course, a Soulstone only holds raw power: the force of a spell. nnMy crystals also contain the pattern it should make: the spell itself. nnWhen a threat nears, it casts a spell: in this case, a firebolt.
Westtry lies in ruins, though it's near Daenia's center. nnAn ancient battle was fought there. The spirits continue their fight there to this day.

Right to business. I like that. nnWe've summoned you to arrange an agreement between you and the Ravenwatch, <<1>>.nnWe both hold a mutual goal in this entire affair. I have my reasons, as I am sure you have yours.
I remember Westtry as it was before the battle.nnIt's a place of spirits now, some in battle and some in fear.nnWesttry is a place of unrest.
If you see a village filled with spirits locked in battle, that place is Westtry.nnWesttry used to be a friendly hamlet, but now it holds only unhappiness.

This is the Felballin Kinhouse - the seat of High kinlord Langdruun's power. You may find shops, places of manufacture, and rooms to stay the night.nnThese days most visit to learn the progress of our war against the Maormer, and assist as they may.

Their homeland of Pyandonea is said to consist of islands, lush with greenery and shrouded in perpetual mists. The waters between the islands are shallow and treacherous with coral reefs. The Maormer use ships like the Landbreaker to clear channels.

Look to a small house in the west of the city. The basement holds the door to our sanctuary.nnIt will not be an easy journey. The spirits of those who have not passed on from our realm walk the halls below.nnConsider it... a test.
Thank you, <<1>>. We'll get back to work straight away.
No. Please, no. I knew I shouldn't have let her talk me into leaving. But she was the mayor of <<1>>. She said she needed to stay behind.nnPlease, tell me what happened to her. I must know!

Well, now! You're interested in Old Stenric's stories? nnI've seen more wars than most, but I've never seen anything like <<1>>. Grown men screaming in the streets, slaughtered like cattle …. I hope my boy died well.
I used to study in the Mages Guild in Shornhelm, but I came with Jerwinna's regiment to investigate Crestshade. nnI tried to save as many lives as I could. I only wish I'd been more successful.
That's right. Sorry, I don't really have time to chat.nnPeople need shelter, and I'm the only one skilled enough to build it for them.
Thank you, <<1>>. We'll get back to work straight away.
